. (AND))\nTest            :   false (9e6c4e1f-7d60-472f-ba1a-a39ef669e4b2 == 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\9e6c4e1f-7d60-472f-ba1a-a39ef669e4b2'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block credential stealing from the Windows local security authority subsystem.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-278648","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-278648","rule_id_src":"SV-278648r1144032_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDD007-6E2A-1014-8ABB-CD8CDF541317","group_id_src":"V-278648","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-278648r1144032"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278649","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"b2b3f03d-6a65-4f7b-a9c7-1c7ef74a9ba4\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"b2b3f03d-6a65-4f7b-a9c7-1c7ef74a9ba4\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000045","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting helps prevents unsigned or untrusted executable files from running from USB removable drives, including SD cards. Blocked file types include executable files (such as .exe, .dll, or .scr). ","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (b2b3f03d-6a65-4f7b-a9c7-1c7ef74a9ba4 == 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\b2b3f03d-6a65-4f7b-a9c7-1c7ef74a9ba4'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block untrusted and unsigned processes that run from USB.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-278649","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-278649","rule_id_src":"SV-278649r1144034_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDD39B-6E2A-1014-A486-FFDE7681624B","group_id_src":"V-278649","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-278649r1144034"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278650","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"c1db55ab-c21a-4637-bb3f-a12568109d35\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"c1db55ab-c21a-4637-bb3f-a12568109d35\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000046","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting provides an extra layer of protection against ransomware. It uses both client and cloud heuristics to determine whether a file resembles ransomware. \nThis rule doesn't block files that have one or more of the following characteristics:\n\n- The file is found to be unharmful in the Microsoft cloud.\n- The file is a valid signed file.\n-  The file is prevalent enough to not be considered as ransomware.\n- The rule tends to err on the side of caution to prevent ransomware. ","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (c1db55ab-c21a-4637-bb3f-a12568109d35 == 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\c1db55ab-c21a-4637-bb3f-a12568109d35'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must use advanced protection against ransomware.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-278650","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-278650","rule_id_src":"SV-278650r1144036_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDD87D-6E2A-1014-B71E-A65053B20B82","group_id_src":"V-278650","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-278650r1144036"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278651","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"d1e49aac-8f56-4280-b9ba-993a6d77406c\" is REG_SZ = 2, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 2, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"d1e49aac-8f56-4280-b9ba-993a6d77406c\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"2\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000047","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting blocks processes created through PsExec and WMI from running. Both PsExec and WMI can remotely execute code. There is a risk of malware abusing functionality of PsExec and WMI for command and control purposes, or to spread an infection throughout an organization's network.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (d1e49aac-8f56-4280-b9ba-993a6d77406c == 2)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\d1e49aac-8f56-4280-b9ba-993a6d77406c'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block process creations originating from PSExec and WMI commands.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-278651","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-278651","rule_id_src":"SV-278651r1144039_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDDC89-6E2A-1014-BA59-A6ED22144C05","group_id_src":"V-278651","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-278651r1144039"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278652","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"e6db77e5-3df2-4cf1-b95a-636979351e5b\" is REG_SZ = 2, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 2, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"e6db77e5-3df2-4cf1-b95a-636979351e5b\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"2\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000048","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting prevents malware from abusing WMI to attain persistence on a device.\n\nFileless threats employ various tactics to stay hidden, to avoid being seen in the file system, and to gain periodic execution control. Some threats can abuse the WMI repository and event model to stay hidden.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (e6db77e5-3df2-4cf1-b95a-636979351e5b == 2)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\c1db55ab-c21a-4637-bb3f-a12568109d35'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block persistence through WMI event subscription.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-278652","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-278652","rule_id_src":"SV-278652r1144042_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDE04C-6E2A-1014-AED3-C4CE64B61640","group_id_src":"V-278652","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-278652r1144042"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278653","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"01443614-cd74-433a-b99e-2ecdc07bfc25\" is REG_SZ = 2, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 2, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"01443614-cd74-433a-b99e-2ecdc07bfc25\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"2\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000049","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting blocks executable files, such as .exe, .dll, or .scr, from launching. Thus, launching untrusted or unknown executable files can be risky, as it might not be initially clear if the files are malicious.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (01443614-cd74-433a-b99e-2ecdc07bfc25 == 2)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\01443614-cd74-433a-b99e-2ecdc07bfc25'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block executable files from running unless they meet a prevalence, age, or trusted list criterion.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-278653","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-278653","rule_id_src":"SV-278653r1144045_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDE3E7-6E2A-1014-8956-DE3608116850","group_id_src":"V-278653","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-278653r1144045"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278654","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"26190899-1602-49e8-8b27-eb1d0a1ce869\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"26190899-1602-49e8-8b27-eb1d0a1ce869\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000050","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting prevents Outlook from creating child processes while still allowing legitimate Outlook functions. This rule protects against social engineering attacks and prevents exploiting code from abusing vulnerabilities in Outlook. It also protects against Outlook rules and forms exploits that attackers can use when a user's credentials are compromised.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (26190899-1602-49e8-8b27-eb1d0a1ce869 == 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\26190899-1602-49e8-8b27-eb1d0a1ce869'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block Office communication application from creating child processes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-278654","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-278654","rule_id_src":"SV-278654r1144047_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDE786-6E2A-1014-BAA7-FA79BC41AC59","group_id_src":"V-278654","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-278654r1144047"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278655","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules is set to \"Enabled\".\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\n\nCriteria: If the value \"56a863a9-875e-4185-98a7-b882c64b5ce5\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is other than 1, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Exploit Guard &gt;&gt; Attack Surface Reduction &gt;&gt; Configure Attack Surface Reduction rules to \"Enabled\".\n\nUnder the policy option \"Set the state for each ASR rule:\", then click \"Show\".\n\nEnter GUID \"56a863a9-875e-4185-98a7-b882c64b5ce5\" in the \"Value Name\" column.\n\nEnter \"1\" in the \"Value\" column.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000051","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting prevents an application from writing a vulnerable signed driver to disk. Vulnerable signed drivers can be exploited by local applications that have sufficient privileges to gain access to the kernel. Vulnerable signed drivers enable attackers to disable or circumvent security solutions, eventually leading to system compromise.\n\nThe Block abuse of exploited vulnerable signed drivers rule does not block a driver already existing on the system from being loaded.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (56a863a9-875e-4185-98a7-b882c64b5ce5 == 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\Windows Defender Exploit Guard\\ASR\\Rules\\56a863a9-875e-4185-98a7-b882c64b5ce5'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must block abuse of exploited vulnerable signed drivers.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-278655","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-278655","rule_id_src":"SV-278655r1144049_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDEB1D-6E2A-1014-AA19-AF13026D0034","group_id_src":"V-278655","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-278655r1144049"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278656","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Configure local administrator merge behavior for lists is set to \"Enabled\". Otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"DisableLocalAdminMerge\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is 0, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus  &gt;&gt; Configure local administrator merge behavior for lists to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000052","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting configures how locally defined lists are combined or merged with globally defined lists. This setting applies to exclusion lists, specified remediation lists, and attack surface reduction.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false ('Local administrator merge behavior for lists' is 'Enabled')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\DisableLocalAdminMerge'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must configure local administrator merge behavior for lists.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-278656","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-278656","rule_id_src":"SV-278656r1144051_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDEEAC-6E2A-1014-BFC1-81356B64283E","group_id_src":"V-278656","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-278656r1144051"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278658","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Control whether or not exclusions are visible to Local Admins is set to \"Enabled\"; otherwise, this is a finding.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\n\nCriteria: If the value \"HideExclusionsFromLocalAdmins\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value is \"0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Defender Antivirus &gt;&gt; Control whether or not exclusions are visible to Local Admins to \"Enabled\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nClick \"Apply\".","rule_version":"WNDF-AV-000054","stig_uuid":"6DB97E3E-6E2A-1014-834B-E06488169277","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Disabled (Default): If this setting is not configured or disabled, local admins can see exclusions in the Windows Security App or via PowerShell.\n\nEnabled: If this setting is enabled, local admins no longer see the exclusion list in Windows Security App or via PowerShell.O13.\n\nNote: Applying this setting will not remove exclusions, it only prevents them from being visible to local admins. This is reflected in?Get-MpPreference.I13.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:36:35\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false ('Control whether or not exclusions are visible to Local Admins' is 'Enabled')\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows Defender\\HideExclusionsFromLocalAdmins'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender AV must control whether exclusions are visible to Local Admins.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-278658","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-278658","rule_id_src":"SV-278658r1156519_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"6DBDF27F-6E2A-1014-883E-E71626C7945B","group_id_src":"V-278658","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-278658r1156519"},{"reference_identifier":"3985","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windowsdefav:def:278659","href":"U_MS_Defender_Antivirus_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV13-oval.xml"},"responsib