rity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of search engine settings\" to \"disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000022","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Allows users to import search engine settings from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the option to import search engine settings is automatically selected.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, search engine settings are not imported at first run, and users cannot import them manually.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable importing of search engine settings)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Importing of search engine settings must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235739","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235739","rule_id_src":"SV-235739r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D52ECC-6E2A-1014-A198-9CB3BC6D191F","group_id_src":"V-235739","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235739r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:118","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of shortcuts\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ImportShortcuts\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow importing of shortcuts\" to \"disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000023","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Allows users to import Shortcuts from another browser into Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, Shortcuts are not imported on first run.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, Shortcuts are imported on first run.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable importing of shortcuts)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Importing of shortcuts must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235740","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235740","rule_id_src":"SV-235740r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D53299-6E2A-1014-8F34-D06D571AB964","group_id_src":"V-235740","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235740r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:119","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay for websites\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AutoplayAllowed\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay for websites\" to \"disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000024","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy sets the media autoplay policy for websites.\n\nThe default setting \"Not configured\" respects the current media autoplay settings and lets users configure their autoplay settings.\n\nSetting to \"Enabled\" sets media autoplay to \"Allow\". All websites are allowed to autoplay media. Users cannot override this policy.\n\nSetting to \"Disabled\" sets media autoplay to \"Limit\". This limits websites that are allowed to autoplay media to webpages with high media engagement and active WebRTC streams. Prior to Microsoft Edge version 92, this would set media autoplay to \"Block\". Users cannot override this policy.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable autoplay)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"AutoplayAllowed must be set to disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235741","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235741","rule_id_src":"SV-235741r1007485_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D5372C-6E2A-1014-A83E-F0778D0FD1F8","group_id_src":"V-235741","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235741r1007485"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:120","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the WebUSB API\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to request access to USB devices via the WebUSB API\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DefaultWebUsbGuardSetting\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the WebUSB API\" to enabled\" and select \"Do not allow any site to request access to USB devices via the WebUSB API\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000025","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Set whether websites can access connected USB devices. Access can be blocked completely or the user asked each time a website wants to get access to connected USB devices.\n\nOverride this policy for specific URL patterns by using the WebUsbAskForUrls and WebUsbBlockedForUrls policies.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, sites can ask users whether they can access the connected USB devices ('AskWebUsb') by default, and users can change this setting.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (WebUSB must be disabled)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"WebUSB must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235742","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235742","rule_id_src":"SV-235742r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D53B1C-6E2A-1014-96B5-887B2931C524","group_id_src":"V-235742","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235742r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:121","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Cast/Enable Google Cast\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"EnableMediaRouter\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Cast/Enable Google Cast\" to \"disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000026","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Enable this policy to enable Google Cast. Users will be able to launch it from the app menu, page context menus, media controls on Cast-enabled websites, and (if shown) the Cast toolbar icon.\n\nDisable this policy to disable Google Cast.\n\nBy default, Google Cast is enabled.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Google Cast is disabled)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Google Cast must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235743","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235743","rule_id_src":"SV-235743r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D53EBF-6E2A-1014-80FF-C7B5FF45B102","group_id_src":"V-235743","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235743r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:122","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the Web Bluetooth API\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DefaultWebBluetoothGuardSetting\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Control use of the Web Bluetooth API\" to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API.","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000027","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Control whether websites can access nearby Bluetooth devices. Access can be blocked completely or the site required to ask the user each time it wants to access a Bluetooth device.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, the default value ('AskWebBluetooth', meaning users are asked each time) is used and users can change it.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- BlockWebBluetooth (2) = Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API.\n- AskWebBluetooth (3) = Allow sites to ask the user to grant access to a nearby Bluetooth device.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Web Bluetooth API is disabled)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Web Bluetooth API must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235744","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235744","rule_id_src":"SV-235744r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D5425F-6E2A-1014-B9C6-BBD812E4F267","group_id_src":"V-235744","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235744r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:123","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for credit cards\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AutofillCreditCardEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for credit cards\" to \"disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000028","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Enables the Microsoft Edge AutoFill feature and lets users auto complete credit card information in web forms using previously stored information.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, AutoFill never suggests or fills credit card information, nor will it save additional credit card information that users might submit while browsing the web.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can control AutoFill for credit cards.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable autofill for credit cards)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Autofill for Credit Cards must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235745","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235745","rule_id_src":"SV-235745r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D545F8-6E2A-1014-9E72-818B409B08DE","group_id_src":"V-235745","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235745r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:124","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for addresses\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AutofillAddressEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable AutoFill for addresses\" to \"disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000029","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Enables the AutoFill feature and allows users to auto-complete address information in web forms using previously stored information.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, AutoFill never suggests or fills credit card information, nor will it save additional credit card information that users might submit while browsing the web.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can control AutoFill for addresses in the user interface.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable autofill for addresses)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Autofill for addresses must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235746","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235746","rule_id_src":"SV-235746r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D549BA-6E2A-1014-A199-B4A0DBFF7AB0","group_id_src":"V-235746","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235746r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:125","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable online OCSP/CRL checks\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"EnableOnlineRevocationChecks\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable online OCSP/CRL checks\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000030","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"If you enable this policy, Microsoft Edge will perform soft-fail, online OCSP/CRL checks. \"Soft fail\" means that if the revocation server can't be reached, the certificate will be considered valid.\n\nIf you disable the policy or don't configure it, Microsoft Edge won't perform online revocation checks.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Enable Enable online OCSP/CRL checks)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Online revocation checks must be performed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235747","title":"SRG-APP-000175"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235747","rule_id_src":"SV-235747r961038_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D54E0D-6E2A-1014-AA13-FF86F96941A0","group_id_src":"V-235747","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235747r961038"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:126","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow personalization of ads, search and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PersonalizationReportingEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow personalization of ads, search and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft\" to \"disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000031","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy prevents Microsoft from collecting a user's Microsoft Edge browsing history to be used for personalizing advertising, search, news and other Microsoft services.\n\nThis setting is only available for users with a Microsoft account. This setting is not available for child accounts or enterprise accounts.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, users cannot change or override the setting. If this policy is enabled or not configured, Microsoft Edge will default to the user's preference.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable personalization reporting)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Personalization of ads, search, and news by sending browsing history to Microsoft must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235748","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235748","rule_id_src":"SV-235748r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D55265-6E2A-1014-AA85-ADBB78350D7F","group_id_src":"V-235748","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235748r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:127","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Default geolocation setting\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Don't allow any site to track users' physical location\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DefaultGeolocationSetting\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Default geolocation setting\" to \"enabled\" and select \"Don't allow any site to track users' physical location\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000032","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Set whether websites can track users' physical locations. Tracking can be allowed by default (\"AllowGeolocation\") or denied by default (\"BlockGeolocation\"), or the user can be asked each time a website requests their location (\"AskGeolocation\").\n\nIf this policy is not configured, \"AskGeolocation\" is used and the user can change it.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- AllowGeolocation (1) = Allow sites to track users' physical location.\n- BlockGeolocation (2) = Do not allow any site to track users' physical location.\n- AskGeolocation (3) = Ask whenever a site wants to track users' physical location.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable tracking user's location)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Site tracking of a userâs location must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235749","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235749","rule_id_src":"SV-235749r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D556EC-6E2A-1014-AC7F-F3876697A3D6","group_id_src":"V-235749","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235749r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:128","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable deleting browser and download history\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AllowDeletingBrowserHistory\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable deleting browser and download history\" to \"disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000033","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting disables deleting browser history and download history and prevents users from changing this setting.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Check to make sure that Microsoft Edge is set to not allow deletion of browser history.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Browser history must be saved.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235750","title":"SRG-APP-000080"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235750","rule_id_src":"SV-235750r960864_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D55AF6-6E2A-1014-A9CE-CCDFB0871DC0","group_id_src":"V-235750","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235750r960864"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:129","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Control where developer tools can be used\" with the option value set to \"Don't allow using the developer tools\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DeveloperToolsAvailability\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","severity":"low","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Control where developer tools can be used\" to \"enabled\" and select \"Don't allow using the developer tools\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000034","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"While the risk associated with browser development tools is more related to the proper design of a web application, a risk vector remains within the browser. The developer tools allow end users and application developers to view and edit all types of web application-related data via the browser. Page elements, source code, javascript, API calls, application data, etc., may all be viewed and potentially manipulated. Manipulation could be useful for troubleshooting legitimate issues, and this may be performed in a development environment. Manipulation could also be malicious and must be addressed.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Edge Developer Tools Availability must be disallowed.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Edge development tools must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235751","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235751","rule_id_src":"SV-235751r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D55E98-6E2A-1014-809F-DD2C8B9DDF52","group_id_src":"V-235751","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235751r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:130","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"If this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow download restrictions\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"BlockDangerousDownloads\", \"Block potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads\", or \"BlockMaliciousDownloads\". The more restrictive option, \"Block all downloads\", is also acceptable.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"DownloadRestrictions\" is set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"low","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow download restrictions\" to \"Enabled\" and select one of the following: \"BlockDangerousDownloads\", \"Block potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads\", \"BlockAllDownloads\", or \"BlockMaliciousDownloads\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000036","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This configures the type of downloads that Microsoft Edge completely blocks without allowing users to override the security decision.\n\nSet \"BlockDangerousDownloads\" to allow all downloads except those that carry Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings of known dangerous downloads or that have dangerous file type extensions.\n\nSet \"BlockPotentiallyDangerousDownloads\" to allow all downloads except those that carry Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings of potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads or that have dangerous file type extensions.\n\nSet \"BlockAllDownloads\" to block all downloads.\n\nSet \"BlockMaliciousDownloads\" to allow all downloads except those that carry Microsoft Defender SmartScreen warnings of known malicious downloads.\n\nIf this policy is not configured or the \"DefaultDownloadSecurity\" option is not set, the downloads go through the usual security restrictions based on Microsoft Defender SmartScreen analysis results.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n\nDefaultDownloadSecurity (0) = No special restrictions\n\nBlockDangerousDownloads (1) = Block malicious downloads and dangerous file types\n\nBlockPotentiallyDangerousDownloads (2) = Block potentially dangerous or unwanted downloads and dangerous file types\n\nBlockAllDownloads (3) = Block all downloads\n\nBlockMaliciousDownloads (4) = Block malicious downloads","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Download restrictions are configured)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Download restrictions must be configured.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235752","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235752","rule_id_src":"SV-235752r1156563_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D562BB-6E2A-1014-86A1-CD0E04A9ACCF","group_id_src":"V-235752","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235752r1156563"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.edge:questionnaire:6901","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-APP-000378","comments":null,"check_content":"This requirement for \"Allow pop-up windows on specific sites\" is not required; this is optional.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Allow pop-up windows on specific sites\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\n\"PopupsAllowedForUrls\" must be set as follows:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PopupsAllowedForUrls\\1 = mydomain.com\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\PopupsAllowedForUrls\\2 = myagency.mil\n\nIf configured, the list of domains for which Microsoft Edge allows pop-ups may be allowlisted.","severity":"low","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Allow pop-up windows on specific sites\" to \"Enabled\". A list of allowlisted URLs may be specified here.","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000039","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Define a list of sites, based on URL patterns that can open pop-up windows.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT III, V-235753, SV-235753r1015297, SRG-APP-000378)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"URLs must be allowlisted for plugin use if used.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-003980","CCI-001812"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235753","title":"SRG-APP-000378"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235753","rule_id_src":"SV-235753r1015297_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D5665C-6E2A-1014-B128-9501400908DE","group_id_src":"V-235753","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235753r1015297"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:131","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Control which extensions cannot be installed\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallBlocklist\\1\n\nIf the value for \"1\" is not set to \"REG_SZ = *\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Control which extensions cannot be installed\" to \"Enabled\". A list of blocklisted extensions may then be specified.","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000041","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"List specific extensions that users cannot install in Microsoft Edge. When this policy is deployed, any extensions on this list that were previously installed will be disabled, and the user will not be able to enable them. If an item is removed from the list of blocked extensions, the extension is automatically reenabled anywhere it was previously installed.\n\nUse \"*\" to block all extensions that are not explicitly listed in the allow list.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, users can install any extension in Microsoft Edge.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Enable the setting 'Control which extensions cannot be installed')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Extensions installation must be blocklisted by default.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235754","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235754","rule_id_src":"SV-235754r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D56A32-6E2A-1014-A81D-99367762F0BF","group_id_src":"V-235754","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235754r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.edge:questionnaire:7301","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-APP-000386","comments":null,"check_content":"This requirement for \"Allow specific extensions to be installed\" is not required; this is optional.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Allow specific extensions to be installed\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\n\"ExtensionInstallAllowlist\" must be set as follows:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallAllowlist\\1 = \"extension_id1\"\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ExtensionInstallAllowlist\\2 = \"extension_id2\"\n\nIf configured, the list of extensions for which Microsoft Edge allows to be installed may be allowlisted.","severity":"low","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Extensions/Allow specific extensions to be installed\" to \"Enabled\".  A list of allowlisted extensions may then be specified.","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000042","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"By default, all extensions are allowed. However, if all extensions are blocked by setting the \"ExtensionInstallBlockList\" policy to \"*,\" users can only install extensions defined in this policy.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT III, V-235755, SV-235755r961479, SRG-APP-000386)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Extensions that are approved for use must be allowlisted if used.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001774"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235755","title":"SRG-APP-000386"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235755","rule_id_src":"SV-235755r961479_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D56DD1-6E2A-1014-9B16-9B4239F2A392","group_id_src":"V-235755","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235755r961479"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:132","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000400","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Password manager and protection/Enable saving passwords to the password manager\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PasswordManagerEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Password manager and protection/Enable saving passwords to the password manager\" to \"disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000043","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Enable Microsoft Edge to save user passwords.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, users can save their passwords in Microsoft Edge. The next time the user visits the site, Microsoft Edge will enter the password automatically.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable Microsoft Edge Password Manager)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The Password Manager must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002007"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235756","title":"SRG-APP-000400"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235756","rule_id_src":"SV-235756r961521_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D5725E-6E2A-1014-8853-A5EF745CD73E","group_id_src":"V-235756","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235756r961521"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.edge:questionnaire:7701","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-APP-000456","comments":null,"check_content":"Cross-reference the build information displayed with the Microsoft Edge site to identify, at minimum, the oldest supported build available. \n\nIf the installed version of Edge is not supported by Microsoft, this is a finding.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Install a supported version of Edge.","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000045","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Security flaws with software applications are discovered daily. Vendors are constantly updating and patching their products to address newly discovered security vulnerabilities. Organizations (including any contractor to the organization) are required to promptly install security-relevant software updates (e.g., patches, service packs, and hot fixes). Flaws discovered during security assessments, continuous monitoring, incident response activities, or information system error handling must also be addressed expeditiously. \n\nOrganization-defined time periods for updating security-relevant software may vary based on a variety of factors including, for example, the security category of the information system or the criticality of the update (i.e., severity of the vulnerability related to the discovered flaw). \n\nThis requirement will apply to software patch management solutions that are used to install patches across the enclave and also to applications themselves that are not part of that patch management solution. For example, many browsers today provide the capability to install their own patch software. Patch criticality, as well as system criticality will vary. Therefore, the tactical situations regarding the patch management process will also vary. This means that the time period used must be a configurable parameter. Time frames for application of security-relevant software updates may be dependent upon the Information Assurance Vulnerability Management (IAVM) process.\n\nThe application will be configured to check for and install security-relevant software updates within an identified time period from the availability of the update. The specific time period will be defined by an authoritative source (e.g., IAVM, CTOs, DTMs, and STIGs).","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-235758, SV-235758r1117151, SRG-APP-000456)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The version of Microsoft Edge running on the system must be a supported version.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002605"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235758","title":"SRG-APP-000456"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235758","rule_id_src":"SV-235758r1117151_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D57690-6E2A-1014-8510-B487F774292C","group_id_src":"V-235758","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235758r1117151"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:135","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable site isolation for every site\" must be set to \"enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"SitePerProcess\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable site isolation for every site\" to \"enabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000047","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The \"SitePerProcess\" policy can be used to prevent users from opting out of the default behavior of isolating all sites. The \"IsolateOrigins\" policy can be used to isolate additional, finer-grained origins.\n\nEnabling this policy prevents users from opting out of the default behavior where each site runs in its own process.\n\nIf this policy is not disabled or configured, a user can opt out of site isolation (e.g., by using \"Disable site isolation\" entry in edge://flags.) Disabling the policy or not configuring the policy does not turn off Site Isolation.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Enable the setting 'Enable site isolation for every site')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Site isolation for every site must be enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235760","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235760","rule_id_src":"SV-235760r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D57A41-6E2A-1014-BCAC-A6603E64DD72","group_id_src":"V-235760","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235760r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:136","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000142","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/HTTP authentication/Supported authentication schemes\" must be set to  \"ntlm,negotiate\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"AuthSchemes\" is not set to \"REG_SZ = ntlm,negotiate\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/HTTP authentication/Supported authentication schemes\" to \"ntlm,negotiate\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000048","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting specifies which HTTP authentication schemes are supported.\n\nThe policy can be configured by using these values: \"basic\", \"digest\", \"ntlm\", and \"negotiate\". Separate multiple values with commas.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, all four schemes are used.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Enable the setting 'Supported authentication schemes')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Supported authentication schemes must be configured.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000382"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235761","title":"SRG-APP-000142"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235761","rule_id_src":"SV-235761r1043177_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D57DD2-6E2A-1014-9AD4-DD7F41687277","group_id_src":"V-235761","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235761r1043177"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:138","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"SmartScreenEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.\n\nIf this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000050","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting configures Microsoft Defender SmartScreen, which provides warning messages to help protect  users from potential phishing scams and malicious software. By default, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned on.\n\nIf this setting is enabled, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned on.\n\nIf this setting is disabled, Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned off.\n\nIf this setting is not configured, users can choose whether to use Microsoft Defender SmartScreen.\n\nThis policy is available only on Windows instances that are joined to a Microsoft Active Directory domain, Windows 10 Pro or Enterprise instances that enrolled for device management, or macOS instances that are that are managed via MDM or joined to a domain via MCX.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be enabled.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235763","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235763","rule_id_src":"SV-235763r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D5817A-6E2A-1014-8613-F9E612CFAD93","group_id_src":"V-235763","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235763r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:139","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen to block potentially unwanted apps\" must be set to \"Enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for SmartScreenPuaEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.\n\nIf this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/SmartScreen settings/Configure Microsoft Defender SmartScreen to block potentially unwanted apps\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000051","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting configures blocking for potentially unwanted apps with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen. Potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen provides warning messages to help protect users from adware, coin miners, bundleware, and other low-reputation apps that are hosted by websites. Potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned off by default.\n\nIf this setting is enabled, potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned on.\n\nIf this setting is disabled, potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen is turned off.\n\nIf this setting is not configured, users can choose whether to use potentially unwanted app blocking with Microsoft Defender SmartScreen.\n\nThis policy is available only on Windows instances that are joined to a Microsoft Active Directory domain, Windows 10 Pro or Enterprise instances that enrolled for device management, or macOS instances that are managed via MDM or joined to a domain via MCX.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be configured to block potentially unwanted apps.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Microsoft Defender SmartScreen must be configured to block potentially unwanted apps.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235764","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235764","rule_id_src":"SV-235764r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D5853F-6E2A-1014-B51F-DB3B3571EE64","group_id_src":"V-235764","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235764r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:140","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Ask where to save downloaded files\" must be set to \"enabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"PromptForDownloadLocation\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","severity":"low","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Ask where to save downloaded files\" to \"enabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000052","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting provides positive feedback before a download starts, limiting the possibility of inadvertent downloads without notifying the user.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Prompt for download location)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The download location prompt must be configured.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235765","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235765","rule_id_src":"SV-235765r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D589F4-6E2A-1014-8FD2-B06E48999DB6","group_id_src":"V-235765","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235765r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:141","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000148","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Block tracking of users' web-browsing activity\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Balanced\" or \"Strict\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"TrackingPrevention\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\" or \"REG_DWORD = 3\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Block tracking of users' web-browsing activity\" to \"Balanced\" or \"Strict\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000054","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The setting allows websites to be blocked from tracking users' web-browsing activity.\n\nIf this policy is disabled or is not configured, users can set their own level of tracking prevention.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- TrackingPreventionOff (0) = Off (no tracking prevention)\n- TrackingPreventionBasic (1) = Basic (blocks harmful trackers; content and ads will be personalized)\n- TrackingPreventionBalanced (2) = Balanced (blocks harmful trackers and trackers from sites user has not visited; content and ads will be less personalized)\n- TrackingPreventionStrict (3) = Strict (blocks harmful trackers and majority of trackers from all sites; content and ads will have minimal personalization; some parts of sites might not work)","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Tracking of browsing activity must be disabled.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Tracking of browsing activity must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000388"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235766","title":"SRG-APP-000148"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235766","rule_id_src":"SV-235766r1051115_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D58E9B-6E2A-1014-99A7-A338422EBF2B","group_id_src":"V-235766","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235766r1051115"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:142","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000149","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow websites to query for available payment methods\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for PaymentMethodQueryEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow websites to query for available payment methods\" to \"disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000055","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting determines whether websites can check if the user has payment methods saved.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, websites that use \"PaymentRequest.canMakePayment\" or \"PaymentRequest.hasEnrolledInstrument\" API will be informed that no payment methods are available.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or is not set, websites can check to determine if the user has payment methods saved.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable the setting 'Allow websites to query for available payment methods')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"A website's ability to query for payment methods must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235767","title":"SRG-APP-000149"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235767","rule_id_src":"SV-235767r960972_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D59292-6E2A-1014-BA0B-FCEFC02BA4D6","group_id_src":"V-235767","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235767r960972"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:143","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000151","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for AlternateErrorPagesEnabled is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000056","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting allows Microsoft Edge to issue a connection to a web service to generate URL and search suggestions for connectivity issues such as DNS errors.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, a web service is used to generate URL and search suggestions for network errors.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, no calls to the web service are made and a standard error page is shown.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, Microsoft Edge respects the user preference that is set under Services at edge://settings/privacy. Specifically, there is a \"Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" toggle, which the user can switch on or off. \n\nNote that if this policy has been enabled (AlternateErrorPagesEnabled), the \"Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found setting\" is turned on, but the user cannot change the setting by using the toggle. \n\nIf this policy is disabled, the \"Suggest similar pages when a webpage can't be found\" setting is turned off, and the user cannot change the setting by using the toggle.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Suggestions of similar web pages in the event of a navigation error must be disabled.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Suggestions of similar web pages in the event of a navigation error must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381","CCI-000767"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235768","title":"SRG-APP-000151"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235768","rule_id_src":"SV-235768r1015298_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D59649-6E2A-1014-BC27-F416BF630FC3","group_id_src":"V-235768","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235768r1015298"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:144","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000152","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow user feedback\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for UserFeedbackAllowed is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow user feedback\" to \"disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000057","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Microsoft Edge uses the Edge Feedback feature (enabled by default) to allow users to send feedback, suggestions, or customer surveys and to report any issues with the browser. By default, users cannot disable (turn off) the Edge Feedback feature.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can invoke Edge Feedback.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, users cannot invoke Edge Feedback.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable the setting 'Allow user feedback')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"User feedback must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235769","title":"SRG-APP-000152"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235769","rule_id_src":"SV-235769r960981_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D599D9-6E2A-1014-B52A-E8A2C561219E","group_id_src":"V-235769","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235769r960981"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:145","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000153","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable the Collections feature\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"EdgeCollectionsEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable the Collections feature\" to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000058","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting allows users to access the Collections feature, where they can collect, organize, share, and export content more efficiently and with Office integration.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, users can access and use the Collections feature in Microsoft Edge.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, users cannot access and use Collections in Microsoft Edge.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (The collections feature must be disabled.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The collections feature must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235770","title":"SRG-APP-000153"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235770","rule_id_src":"SV-235770r960984_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D59D53-6E2A-1014-908E-847DFAC43F05","group_id_src":"V-235770","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235770r960984"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:146","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure the Share experience\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"Don't allow using the Share experience\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ConfigureShare\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure the Share experience\" to \"Don't allow using the Share experience\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000059","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"If this policy is set to \"ShareAllowed\" (the default), users will be able to access the Windows 10 Share experience from the Settings and More menu in Microsoft Edge to share with other apps on the system.\n\nIf this policy is set to \"ShareDisallowed\", users will not be able to access the Windows 10 Share experience. If the Share button is on the toolbar, it will also be hidden.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n- ShareAllowed (0) = Allow using the Share experience.\n- ShareDisallowed (1) = Do not allow using the Share experience.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Enable the setting 'Enable site isolation for every site')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The Share Experience feature must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235771","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235771","rule_id_src":"SV-235771r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D5A0C9-6E2A-1014-9DCB-A18C7000EE04","group_id_src":"V-235771","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235771r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:147","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable guest mode\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"BrowserGuestModeEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Enable guest mode\" to \"disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000060","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Enabling Guest mode allows the use of guest profiles in Microsoft Edge. In a guest profile, the browser does not import browsing data from existing profiles, and it deletes browsing data when all guest profiles are closed.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, Microsoft Edge lets users browse in guest profiles.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, Microsoft Edge does not let users browse in guest profiles.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable Browser Guest Mode)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Guest mode must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235772","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235772","rule_id_src":"SV-235772r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D5A447-6E2A-1014-BFC7-B49DEA62CD45","group_id_src":"V-235772","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235772r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:148","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000156","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Notify a user that a browser restart is recommended or required for pending updates\" must be set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Required\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"RelaunchNotification\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 2\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Notify a user that a browser restart is recommended or required for pending updates\" web-browsing activity to \"Required\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000061","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Users must be required to restart the browser to finish installation of pending updates and prevent users from continually using an old/vulnerable browser version.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Relaunch notification must be required.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Relaunch notification must be required.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235773","title":"SRG-APP-000156"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235773","rule_id_src":"SV-235773r960993_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D5A79F-6E2A-1014-84E6-F59C2FAF29B9","group_id_src":"V-235773","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235773r960993"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:149","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000157","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Use built-in DNS client\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"BuiltInDnsClientEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Use built-in DNS client\" to \"disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000062","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting controls whether to use the built-in DNS client.\n\nThis does not affect which DNS servers are used; it only controls the software stack that is used to communicate with them. For example, if the operating system is configured to use an enterprise DNS server, that same server would be used by the built-in DNS client. However, it is however possible that the built-in DNS client will address servers in different ways by using more modern DNS-related protocols such as DNS-over-TLS.\n\nIf this policy is enabled, the built-in DNS client is used if it is available.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, the client is never used.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Built in DNS client is disabled)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The built-in DNS client must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001941","CCI-001942"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-235774","title":"SRG-APP-000157"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-235774","rule_id_src":"SV-235774r1015299_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D5AC3D-6E2A-1014-9BC0-DD66F9383109","group_id_src":"V-235774","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-235774r1015299"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:150","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow QUIC protocol\" must be set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"QuicAllowed\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow QUIC protocol\" to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000063","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"QUIC is used by more than half of all connections from the Edge web browser to Google's servers, and this activity is undesirable in the DoD.\n\nIf you enable this policy or don't configure it, the QUIC protocol is allowed.\n\nIf you disable this policy, the QUIC protocol is blocked.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (QUIC protocol is disabled)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Use of the QUIC protocol must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-246736","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-246736","rule_id_src":"SV-246736r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D5B046-6E2A-1014-AE3E-BF4B6D4BA26F","group_id_src":"V-246736","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-246736r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.edge:questionnaire:10901","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"If this machine is on SIPRNet, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThis requirement for \"AutoplayAllowlist\" is not required; this is optional.\n\nThe policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay on specific sites\" may be set to \"allow\" for allowlisted domains.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nAutoplayAllowlist may be set as follows:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AutoplayAllowlist\\1 = mydomain.com\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\AutoplayAllowlist\\2 = myagency.mil\n\nIf configured, the list of domains for which autoplay is allowed may be allowlisted.","severity":"low","fix_text":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Allow media autoplay on specific sites\" may be set to \"allow\" for allowlisted domains.","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000064","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Define a list of sites, based on URL patterns, that are allowed to autoplay media.\n\nIf this policy is not configured, the global default value from the AutoplayAllowed policy (if set) or the user's personal configuration is used for all sites.\n\nEDGE-00-000024 disables the AutoplayAllowed policy. ","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT III, V-251694, SV-251694r960963, SRG-APP-000141)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The list of domains media autoplay allows must be allowlisted if used.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-251694","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-251694","rule_id_src":"SV-251694r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D67B96-6E2A-1014-9490-D1698AAE6423","group_id_src":"V-251694","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-251694r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:260465","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Visual search enabled\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"VisualSearchEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Visual search enabled\" to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000065","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Visual Search allows for quick exploration of more related content about entities in an image.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, Visual Search will be enabled via image hover, context menu, and search in Sidebar.\n\nIf this policy is disabled, Visual Search will be disabled and more information about images will not be available via hover, context menu, and search in Sidebar.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Visual Search is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\VisualSearchEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Visual Search must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-260465","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-260465","rule_id_src":"SV-260465r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D685E7-6E2A-1014-9F66-C2D5019B7B11","group_id_src":"V-260465","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-260465r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:260466","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Show Hubs Sidebar\" is set to \"Disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"HubsSidebarEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Show Hubs Sidebar\" to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000066","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The Sidebar is a launcher bar on the right side of Microsoft Edge's screen.\n\nIf this policy is enabled or not configured, the Sidebar will be shown. If this policy is disabled, the Sidebar will never be shown.\n\nDisabling Sidebar will disable Copilot.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Copilot is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\HubsSidebarEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Copilot must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-260466","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-260466","rule_id_src":"SV-260466r960963_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D68ECC-6E2A-1014-BFF0-D3AEBDDA59E7","group_id_src":"V-260466","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-260466r960963"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:260467","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Configure cookies\" is set to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Keep cookies for the duration of the session, except ones listed in 'SaveCookiesOnExit'\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for âDefaultCookiesSettingâ is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 4\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Content settings/Configure cookies\" to \"Enabled\" with the option value set to \"Keep cookies for the duration of the session, except ones listed in 'SaveCookiesOnExit'\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000067","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Cookies must only be allowed per session and only for approved URLs as permanently stored cookies can be used for malicious intent. \n\nApproved URLs may be allowlisted via the \"CookiesAllowedForUrls\" or \"SaveCookiesOnExit\" policy settings, but these are not requirements.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Session only-based cookies is enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\DefaultCookiesSetting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Session only-based cookies must be enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-260467","title":"SRG-APP-000080"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-260467","rule_id_src":"SV-260467r960864_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D69384-6E2A-1014-ABDD-A0A4CF905D1B","group_id_src":"V-260467","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-260467r960864"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:266981","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Configure the default paste format of URLs copied from Microsoft Edge and determine if additional formats will be available to users\" must be set to \"enabled\" with the option value set to \"The plain URL without any extra information, such as the pageÂ´s title. This is the recommended option when this policy is configured. For more information, see the description.\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ConfigureFriendlyURLFormat\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft EdgeConfigure the default paste format of URLs copied from Microsoft Edge, and determine if additional formats will be available to users\" to \"enabled\" and select \"The plain URL without any extra information, such as the pageÂ´s title. This is the recommended option when this policy is configured. For more information, see the description.\"","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000068","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"If FriendlyURLs are enabled, Microsoft Edge will compute additional representations of the URL and place them on the clipboard.\n\nThis policy configures what format will be pasted when the user pastes in external applications, or inside Microsoft Edge without the \"Paste As\" context menu item.\n\nIf configured, this policy makes a choice on behalf of the user. The options in edge://settings/shareCopyPaste will be grayed out, and the options in the \"Paste As\" context menu will not be available.\n\nNot configured = The user will be able to choose their preferred paste format. By default, this is set to the friendly URL format. The \"Paste As\" menu will be available in Microsoft Edge.\n\n1 = No additional formats will be stored on the clipboard. There will be no \"Paste as\" context menu item in Microsoft Edge and the only format available to paste will be the plain text URL format. Effectively, the friendly URL feature will be disabled.\n\n3 = The user will get a friendly URL whenever they paste into surfaces that accept rich text. The plain URL will still be available for non-rich surfaces. There will be no \"Paste As\" menu in Microsoft Edge.\n\n4 = (Not currently used)\n\nThe richer formats may not be well-supported in some paste destinations and/or websites. In these scenarios, the plain URL option is recommended when configuring this policy.\n\nThe recommended policy is available in Microsoft Edge 105 or later.\n\nPolicy options mapping:\n\nPlainText (1) = The plain URL without any extra information, such as the page's title. This is the recommended option when this policy is configured. For more information, see the description.\n\nTitledHyperlink (3) = Titled Hyperlink: A hyperlink that points to the copied URL, but whose visible text is the title of the destination page. This is the Friendly URL format.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (FriendlyURLs is enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ConfigureFriendlyURLFormat'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"FriendlyURLs must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-266981","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-266981","rule_id_src":"SV-266981r1169858_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D6981F-6E2A-1014-8D67-F21B16509B20","group_id_src":"V-266981","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-266981r1169858"},{"reference_identifier":"5280","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.edge:def:279940","href":"U_MS_Edge_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV14-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","comments":null,"check_content":"The policy value for \"Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Microsoft Edge/Control access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance in Microsoft Edge for Business\" must be set to \"disabled\".\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\nHKLM\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\n\nIf the value for \"ComposeInlineEnabled\" is not set to \"REG_DWORD = 0\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Set the policy value for \"Control access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance in Microsoft Edge for Business\" to \"disabled\".","rule_version":"EDGE-00-000069","stig_uuid":"D1D19EF6-6E2A-1014-AEFA-F84E893AE075","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy controls whether users can use writing support features in Microsoft Edge for Business, such as Rewrite, which utilizes Microsoft 365 Copilot Chat.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:22\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Edge\\ComposeInlineEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Access to Microsoft 365 Copilot writing assistance must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-279940","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-279940","rule_id_src":"SV-279940r1156561_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"D1D6A17E-6E2A-1014-8F0A-EC115B7ABF5C","group_id_src":"V-279940","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-279940r1156561"}],"size":60,"version":"2"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","stig_id":"MS_Windows_Server_2022_STIG","classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","stig_name":"Microsoft Windows Server 2022 Security Technical Implementation Guide","display_name":"Microsoft Windows Server 2022","uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","release_info":"Release: 7 Benchmark Date: 05 Jan 2026","rules":[{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:101","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify each user with administrative privileges has been assigned a unique administrative account separate from their standard user account. \n\nIf users with administrative privileges do not have separate accounts for administrative functions and standard user functions, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Ensure each user with administrative privileges has a separate account for user duties and one for privileged duties.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000010","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Using a privileged account to perform routine functions makes the computer vulnerable to malicious software inadvertently introduced during a session that has been granted full privileges.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254238, SV-254238r991589, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 users with Administrative privileges must have separate accounts for administrative duties and normal operational tasks.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254238","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254238","rule_id_src":"SV-254238r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A41CD50-6E2B-1014-9A2A-CCE2E61CFFC2","group_id_src":"V-254238","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254238r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254239","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","comments":null,"check_content":"If there are no enabled local Administrator accounts, this is Not Applicable.\n\nReview the password last set date for the enabled local Administrator account.\n\nOn the stand alone or domain-joined server:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-LocalUser | Where-Object {$_.SID -like \"*500\"} | ForEach-Object ($_.PasswordLastSet){\"$($_.Name) password is: $([int]((Get-Date) - $_.PasswordLastSet).TotalDays) days old\"}\".\n\nIf the \"PasswordLastSet\" date is greater than \"60\" days old for the local Administrator account for administering the computer, this is a finding.\n\nVerify LAPS is configured and operational.\n\nIf the system is a stand alone member server, the LAPS portion of this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; LAPS &gt;&gt; Password Settings &gt;&gt; Set to enabled. Password Complexity, large letters + small letters + numbers + special, Password Length 14, Password Age 60. If not configured as shown, this is a finding.\n\nVerify LAPS Operational logs &gt;&gt; Event Viewer &gt;&gt; Applications and Services Logs &gt;&gt; Microsoft &gt;&gt; Windows &gt;&gt; LAPS &gt;&gt; Operational. Verify LAPS policy process is completing. If it is not, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Change the enabled local Administrator account password at least every 60 days. For domain-joined systems, Windows LAPS must be used to change the built-in Administrator account password.\n\nMore information is available at:\nhttps://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/windows-it-pro-blog/by-popular-demand-windows-laps-available-now/ba-p/3788747\nhttps://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-server/identity/laps/laps-overview#windows-laps-supported-platforms-and-azure-ad-laps-preview-status","rule_version":"WN22-00-000020","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The longer a password is in use, the greater the opportunity for someone to gain unauthorized knowledge of the password. The built-in Administrator account is not generally used and its password may not be changed as frequently as necessary. Changing the password for the built-in Administrator account on a regular basis will limit its exposure.\n\nFor domain-joined systems, Windows LAPS must be used to change the built-in Administrator account password.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :         false (LAPS Compliance: Password Age - 60)\nTest            :         false (LAPS Compliance: Password Length - 14)\nTest            :         false (LAPS Compliance: Password Complexity - large letters + small letters + numbers + specials)\nTest            :         false (Verify LAPS policy process is completing)\nTest            :       true (The system is a Windows Standalone Server)\nTest            :     true (Password Age Check: Verify local Administrator account password age is less than 60 day old (if enabled))\nTest            :   false (Enabled local administrator accounts are not found on the system.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 passwords for the built-in Administrator account must be changed at least every 60 days.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000199"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254239","title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254239","rule_id_src":"SV-254239r1153440_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A41D425-6E2B-1014-BC44-8D54C5B488B2","group_id_src":"V-254239","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254239r1153440"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:501","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"Determine whether organization policy, at a minimum, prohibits administrative accounts from using applications that access the internet, such as web browsers, or with potential internet sources, such as email, except as necessary for local service administration.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.\n\nThe organization may use technical means such as whitelisting to prevent the use of browsers and mail applications to enforce this requirement.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Establish a policy, at minimum, to prohibit administrative accounts from using applications that access the internet, such as web browsers, or with potential internet sources, such as email. Ensure the policy is enforced.\n\nThe organization may use technical means such as whitelisting to prevent the use of browsers and mail applications to enforce this requirement.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000030","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Using applications that access the internet or have potential internet sources using administrative privileges exposes a system to compromise. If a flaw in an application is exploited while running as a privileged user, the entire system could be compromised. Web browsers and email are common attack vectors for introducing malicious code and must not be run with an administrative account.\n\nSince administrative accounts may generally change or work around technical restrictions for running a web browser or other applications, it is essential that policy require administrative accounts to not access the internet or use applications such as email.\n\nThe policy must define specific exceptions for local service administration. These exceptions may include HTTP(S)-based tools that are used for the administration of the local system, services, or attached devices.\n\nWhitelisting can be used to enforce the policy to ensure compliance.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227, SRG-OS-000205-GPOS-00083","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-254240, SV-254240r991589, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 administrative accounts must not be used with applications that access the internet, such as web browsers, or with potential internet sources, such as email.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366","CCI-001312"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254240","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254240","rule_id_src":"SV-254240r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A41D8D4-6E2B-1014-B8D4-A6B698481EAB","group_id_src":"V-254240","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254240r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:701","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If no accounts are members of the Backup Operators group, this is NA.\n\nVerify users with accounts in the Backup Operators group have a separate user account for backup functions and for performing normal user tasks.\n\nIf users with accounts in the Backup Operators group do not have separate accounts for backup functions and standard user functions, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Ensure each member of the Backup Operators group has separate accounts for backup functions and standard user functions.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000040","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Backup Operators are able to read and write to any file in the system, regardless of the rights assigned to it. Backup and restore rights permit users to circumvent the file access restrictions present on NTFS disk drives for backup and restore purposes. Members of the Backup Operators group must have separate logon accounts for performing backup duties.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254241, SV-254241r991589, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 members of the Backup Operators group must have separate accounts for backup duties and normal operational tasks.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254241","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254241","rule_id_src":"SV-254241r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A41DCEB-6E2B-1014-8940-BBCD9B849AB6","group_id_src":"V-254241","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254241r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254242","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000078-GPOS-00046","comments":null,"check_content":"Determine if manually managed application/service accounts exist. If none exist, this is NA.\n\nVerify the organization has a policy to ensure passwords for manually managed application/service accounts are at least 14 characters in length.\n\nIf such a policy does not exist or has not been implemented, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Establish a policy that requires application/service account passwords that are manually managed to be at least 14 characters in length. Ensure the policy is enforced.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000050","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Application/service account passwords must be of sufficient length to prevent being easily cracked. Application/service accounts that are manually managed must have passwords at least 14 characters in length.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Verify Password Length Setting is required to be 14 or more characters.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 manually managed application account passwords must be at least 14 characters in length.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000205"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254242","title":"SRG-OS-000078-GPOS-00046"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254242","rule_id_src":"SV-254242r1051087_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A41E0CF-6E2B-1014-B997-A7AA929C958F","group_id_src":"V-254242","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254242r1051087"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:1101","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"Determine if manually managed application/service accounts exist. If none exist, this is NA.\n\nIf passwords for manually managed application/service accounts are not changed at least annually or when an administrator with knowledge of the password leaves the organization, this is a finding.\n\nIdentify manually managed application/service accounts.\n\nTo determine the date a password was last changed:\n\nDomain controllers:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-AdUser -Identity [application account name] -Properties PasswordLastSet | FT Name, PasswordLastSet\", where [application account name] is the name of the manually managed application/service account.\n\nIf the \"PasswordLastSet\" date is more than one year old, this is a finding.\n\nMember servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems:\n\nOpen \"Command Prompt\".\n\nEnter 'Net User [application account name] | Find /i \"Password Last Set\"', where [application account name] is the name of the manually managed application/service account.\n\nIf the \"Password Last Set\" date is more than one year old, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Change passwords for manually managed application/service accounts at least annually or when an administrator with knowledge of the password leaves the organization.\n\nIt is recommended that system-managed service accounts be used whenever possible.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000060","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Setting application account passwords to expire may cause applications to stop functioning. However, not changing them on a regular basis exposes them to attack. If managed service accounts are used, this alleviates the need to manually change application account passwords.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254243, SV-254243r991589, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 manually managed application account passwords must be changed at least annually or when a system administrator with knowledge of the password leaves the organization.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254243","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254243","rule_id_src":"SV-254243r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A41E4A0-6E2B-1014-A7F1-840154F91D10","group_id_src":"V-254243","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254243r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:1301","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000104-GPOS-00051","comments":null,"check_content":"Determine whether any shared accounts exist. If no shared accounts exist, this is NA.\n\nShared accounts, such as required by an application, may be approved by the organization. This must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO). Documentation must include the reason for the account, who has access to the account, and how the risk of using the shared account is mitigated to include monitoring account activity.\n\nIf unapproved shared accounts exist, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Remove unapproved shared accounts from the system.\n\nDocument required shared accounts with the ISSO. Documentation must include the reason for the account, who has access to the account, and how the risk of using the shared account is mitigated to include monitoring account activity.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000070","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Shared accounts (accounts where two or more people log on with the same user identification) do not provide adequate identification and authentication. There is no way to provide for nonrepudiation or individual accountability for system access and resource usage.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254244, SV-254244r958482, SRG-OS-000104-GPOS-00051)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 shared user accounts must not be permitted.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000764"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254244","title":"SRG-OS-000104-GPOS-00051"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254244","rule_id_src":"SV-254244r958482_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A41EC0A-6E2B-1014-B238-D06DD6D2AF25","group_id_src":"V-254244","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254244r958482"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:1501","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the operating system employs a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs.\n\nIf an application allowlisting program is not in use on the system, this is a finding.\n\nConfiguration of allowlisting applications will vary by the program.\n\nAppLocker is an allowlisting application built in to Windows Server. A deny-by-default implementation is initiated by enabling any AppLocker rules within a category, only allowing what is specified by defined rules.\n\nIf AppLocker is used, perform the following to view the configuration of AppLocker:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nIf the AppLocker PowerShell module has not been imported previously, execute the following first:\n\nImport-Module AppLocker\n\nExecute the following command, substituting [c:\\temp\\file.xml] with a location and file name appropriate for the system:\n\nGet-AppLockerPolicy -Effective -XML &gt; c:\\temp\\file.xml\n\nThis will produce an xml file with the effective settings that can be viewed in a browser or opened in a program such as Excel for review.\n\nImplementation guidance for AppLocker is available at the following link:\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/security/threat-protection/windows-defender-application-control/applocker/applocker-policies-deployment-guide","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure an application allowlisting program to employ a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs.\n\nConfiguration of allowlisting applications will vary by the program. AppLocker is an allowlisting application built in to Windows Server.\n\nIf AppLocker is used, it is configured through group policy in Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Application Control Policies &gt;&gt; AppLocker.\n\nImplementation guidance for AppLocker is available at the following link:\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/security/threat-protection/windows-defender-application-control/applocker/applocker-policies-deployment-guide","rule_version":"WN22-00-000080","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Using an allowlist provides a configuration management method to allow the execution of only authorized software. Using only authorized software decreases risk by limiting the number of potential vulnerabilities.\n\nThe organization must identify authorized software programs and only permit execution of authorized software. The process used to identify software programs that are authorized to execute on organizational information systems is commonly referred to as allowlisting.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254245, SV-254245r958808, SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must employ a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001774"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254245","title":"SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254245","rule_id_src":"SV-254245r958808_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A41F155-6E2B-1014-9911-DF349E3A498E","group_id_src":"V-254245","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254245r958808"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254246","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nVerify the system has a TPM and it is ready for use.\n\nRun \"tpm.msc\".\n\nReview the sections in the center pane.\n\n\"Status\" must indicate it has been configured with a message such as \"The TPM is ready for use\" or \"The TPM is on and ownership has been taken\".\n\nTPM Manufacturer Information - Specific Version = 2.0 or 1.2\n\nIf a TPM is not found or is not ready for use, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Ensure domain-joined systems have a TPM that is configured for use. (Versions 2.0 or 1.2 support Credential Guard.)\n\nThe TPM must be enabled in the firmware.\n\nRun \"tpm.msc\" for configuration options in Windows.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000090","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Credential Guard uses virtualization-based security to protect data that could be used in credential theft attacks if compromised. A number of system requirements must be met in order for Credential Guard to be configured and enabled properly. Without a TPM enabled and ready for use, Credential Guard keys are stored in a less secure method using software.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 domain-joined systems must have a Trusted Platform Module (TPM) enabled and ready for use.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254246","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254246","rule_id_src":"SV-254246r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A41FCD3-6E2B-1014-8269-C9D0D642216D","group_id_src":"V-254246","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254246r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254247","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"Open \"Command Prompt\".\n\nEnter \"winver.exe\".\n\nIf the \"About Windows\" dialog box does not display \"Microsoft Windows Server Version 21H1 (Build 20348.xxx)\" or greater, this is a finding.\n\nPreview versions must not be used in a production environment.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Update the system to a Version 21H2 (Build 20348.xxx) or greater.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000100","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Systems at unsupported servicing levels will not receive security updates for new vulnerabilities, which leave them subject to exploitation. Systems must be maintained at a servicing level supported by the vendor with new security updates.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :     true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 20348)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be maintained at a supported servicing level.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254247","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254247","rule_id_src":"SV-254247r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42063A-6E2B-1014-9FE9-A2A012A4630B","group_id_src":"V-254247","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254247r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:2101","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify an antivirus solution is installed on the system. The antivirus solution may be bundled with an approved host-based security solution.\n\nIf there is no antivirus solution installed on the system, this is a finding.\n\nVerify if Microsoft Defender antivirus is in use or enabled:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"get-service | where {$_.DisplayName -Like \"*Defender*\"} | Select Status,DisplayName\"\n\nVerify if third-party antivirus is in use or enabled:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"get-service | where {$_.DisplayName -Like \"*mcafee*\"} | Select Status,DisplayName\n\nEnter \"get-service | where {$_.DisplayName -Like \"*symantec*\"} | Select Status,DisplayName","severity":"medium","fix_text":"If no antivirus software is in use, install Microsoft Defender or third-party antivirus.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Install-WindowsFeature -Name Windows-Defender\".\n\nFor third-party antivirus, install per antivirus instructions and disable Windows Defender.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Uninstall-WindowsFeature -Name Windows-Defender\".","rule_version":"WN22-00-000110","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Malicious software can establish a base on individual desktops and servers. Employing an automated mechanism to detect this type of software will aid in elimination of the software from the operating system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254248, SV-254248r991589, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must use an antivirus program.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254248","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254248","rule_id_src":"SV-254248r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A420AEB-6E2B-1014-A144-9370C0F3E66F","group_id_src":"V-254248","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254248r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:2301","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"Determine whether there is a HIDS or HIPS on each server. \n\nIf the HIPS component of ESS is installed and active on the host and the alerts of blocked activity are being logged and monitored, this meets the requirement. \n\nA HIDS device is not required on a system that has the role as the Network Intrusion Device (NID). However, this exception needs to be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nIf a HIDS is not installed on the system, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Install a HIDS or HIPS on each server.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000120","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"A properly configured Host-based Intrusion Detection System (HIDS) or Host-based Intrusion Prevention System (HIPS) provides another level of defense against unauthorized access to critical servers. With proper configuration and logging enabled, such a system can stop and/or alert for many attempts to gain unauthorized access to resources.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254249, SV-254249r991589, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have a host-based intrusion detection or prevention system.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254249","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254249","rule_id_src":"SV-254249r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A420EBF-6E2B-1014-9C50-F72DCCF978CB","group_id_src":"V-254249","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254249r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254250","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","comments":null,"check_content":"Open \"Computer Management\".\n\nSelect \"Disk Management\" under \"Storage\".\n\nFor each local volume, if the file system does not indicate \"NTFS\", this is a finding.\n\n\"ReFS\" (resilient file system) is also acceptable and is not a finding.\nCSV ( Cluster Shared Volumes) is not a finding.\n\nThis does not apply to system partitions such the Recovery and EFI System Partition.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Format volumes to use NTFS, ReFS, or CSVFS.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000130","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The ability to set access permissions and auditing is critical to maintaining the security and proper access controls of a system. To support this, volumes must be formatted using a file system that supports NTFS attributes.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (local volumes are formatted using NTFS, ReFS or CSVFS)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 local volumes must use a format that supports NTFS attributes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254250","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254250","rule_id_src":"SV-254250r1137691_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A421286-6E2B-1014-87C3-B63E1E616C42","group_id_src":"V-254250","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254250r1137691"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254251","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00122","comments":null,"check_content":"The default permissions are adequate when the Security Option \"Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" is set to \"Disabled\" (WN22-SO-000240).\n\nReview the permissions for the system drive's root directory (usually C:\\). Nonprivileged groups such as Users or Authenticated Users must not have greater than \"Read &amp; execute\" permissions except where noted as defaults. Individual accounts must not be used to assign permissions.\n\nIf permissions are not as restrictive as the default permissions listed below, this is a finding.\n\nViewing in File Explorer:\n\nView the Properties of the system drive's root directory.\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab, and the \"Advanced\" button.\n\nDefault permissions:\nC:\\\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\n\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\n\nSYSTEM - Full control - This folder, subfolders, and files\nAdministrators - Full control - This folder, subfolders, and files\nUsers - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nUsers - Create folders/append data - This folder and subfolders\nUsers - Create files/write data - Subfolders only\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - Subfolders and files only\n\nAlternately, use icacls:\n\nOpen \"Command Prompt (Admin)\".\n\nEnter \"icacls\" followed by the directory:\n\n\"icacls c:\\\"\n\nThe following results must be displayed:\n\nc:\\\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(OI)(CI)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(OI)(CI)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(OI)(CI)(RX)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(CI)(AD)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(CI)(IO)(WD)\nCREATOR OWNER:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nSuccessfully processed 1 files; Failed processing 0 files","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Maintain the default permissions for the system drive's root directory and configure the Security Option \"Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" to \"Disabled\" (WN22-SO-000240).\n\nDefault Permissions\nC:\\\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\n\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\n\nSYSTEM - Full control - This folder, subfolders, and files\nAdministrators - Full control - This folder, subfolders, and files\nUsers - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nUsers - Create folders/append data - This folder and subfolders\nUsers - Create files/write data - Subfolders only\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - Subfolders and files only","rule_version":"WN22-00-000140","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Changing the system's file and directory permissions allows the possibility of unauthorized and anonymous modification to the operating system and installed applications.\n\nThe default permissions are adequate when the Security Option \"Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" is set to \"Disabled\" (WN22-SO-000240).\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00122, SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00123, SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00124","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users is set to 'Disabled')\nTest            :   true (Permissions must conform to minimum requirements.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 permissions for the system drive root directory (usually C:\\) must conform to minimum requirements.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002165"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254251","title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00122"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254251","rule_id_src":"SV-254251r958702_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A421677-6E2B-1014-A1D4-95BF5D24D085","group_id_src":"V-254251","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254251r958702"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254252","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00122","comments":null,"check_content":"The default permissions are adequate when the Security Option \"Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" is set to \"Disabled\" (WN22-SO-000240).\n\nReview the permissions for the program file directories (Program Files and Program Files [x86]). Nonprivileged groups such as Users or Authenticated Users must not have greater than \"Read &amp; execute\" permissions. Individual accounts must not be used to assign permissions.\n\nIf permissions are not as restrictive as the default permissions listed below, this is a finding.\n\nViewing in File Explorer:\n\nFor each folder, view the Properties.\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab, and the \"Advanced\" button.\n\nDefault permissions:\n\\Program Files and \\Program Files (x86)\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\n\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\n\nTrustedInstaller - Full control - This folder and subfolders\nSYSTEM - Modify - This folder only\nSYSTEM - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nAdministrators - Modify - This folder only\nAdministrators - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nUsers - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders and files\nCREATOR OWNER - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\n\nAlternately, use icacls:\n\nOpen a Command prompt (admin).\n\nEnter \"icacls\" followed by the directory:\n\n'icacls \"c:\\program files\"'\n'icacls \"c:\\program files (x86)\"'\n\nThe following results must be displayed for each when entered:\n\nc:\\program files (c:\\program files (x86))\nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(F)\nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(CI)(IO)(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(M)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(M)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(RX)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nCREATOR OWNER:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES:(RX)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES:(RX)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nSuccessfully processed 1 files; Failed processing 0 files","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Maintain the default permissions for the program file directories and configure the Security Option \"Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" to \"Disabled\" (WN22-SO-000240).\n\nDefault permissions:\n\\Program Files and \\Program Files (x86)\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\n\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\n\nTrustedInstaller - Full control - This folder and subfolders\nSYSTEM - Modify - This folder only\nSYSTEM - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nAdministrators - Modify - This folder only\nAdministrators - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nUsers - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nCREATOR OWNER - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files","rule_version":"WN22-00-000150","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Changing the system's file and directory permissions allows the possibility of unauthorized and anonymous modification to the operating system and installed applications.\n\nThe default permissions are adequate when the Security Option \"Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" is set to \"Disabled\" (WN22-SO-000240).\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00122, SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00123, SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00124","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users is set to 'Disabled')\nTest            :   true (Program Files directory permissions must conform to minimum requirements.)\nTest            :   true (Program Files (x86) directory permissions must conform to minimum requirements.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 permissions for program file directories must conform to minimum requirements.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002165"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254252","title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00122"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254252","rule_id_src":"SV-254252r958702_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A421A44-6E2B-1014-A7CF-ED0210A18FB8","group_id_src":"V-254252","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254252r958702"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254253","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00122","comments":null,"check_content":"The default permissions are adequate when the Security Option \"Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" is set to \"Disabled\" (WN22-SO-000240).\n\nReview the permissions for the Windows installation directory (usually C:\\Windows). Nonprivileged groups such as Users or Authenticated Users must not have greater than \"Read &amp; execute\" permissions. Individual accounts must not be used to assign permissions.\n\nIf permissions are not as restrictive as the default permissions listed below, this is a finding:\n\nViewing in File Explorer:\n\nFor each folder, view the Properties.\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab and the \"Advanced\" button.\n\nDefault permissions:\n\\Windows\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\n\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\n\nTrustedInstaller - Full control - This folder and subfolders\nSYSTEM - Modify - This folder only\nSYSTEM - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nAdministrators - Modify - This folder only\nAdministrators - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nUsers - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nCREATOR OWNER - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\n\nAlternately, use icacls:\n\nOpen a Command prompt (admin).\n\nEnter \"icacls\" followed by the directory:\n\n\"icacls c:\\windows\"\n\nThe following results must be displayed for each when entered:\n\nc:\\windows\nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(F)\nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(CI)(IO)(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(M)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(M)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(RX)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nCREATOR OWNER:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES:(RX)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES:(RX)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nSuccessfully processed 1 files; Failed processing 0 files","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Maintain the default file ACLs and configure the Security Option \"Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" to \"Disabled\" (WN22-SO-000240).\n\nDefault permissions:\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\n\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\n\nTrustedInstaller - Full control - This folder and subfolders\nSYSTEM - Modify - This folder only\nSYSTEM - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nAdministrators - Modify - This folder only\nAdministrators - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nUsers - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nCREATOR OWNER - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files","rule_version":"WN22-00-000160","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Changing the system's file and directory permissions allows the possibility of unauthorized and anonymous modification to the operating system and installed applications.\n\nThe default permissions are adequate when the Security Option \"Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" is set to \"Disabled\" (WN22-SO-000240).\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00122, SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00123, SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00124","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users is set to 'Disabled')\nTest            :   true (Permissions must conform to minimum requirements.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 permissions for the Windows installation directory must conform to minimum requirements.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002165"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254253","title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00122"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254253","rule_id_src":"SV-254253r958702_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A421E1A-6E2B-1014-9D08-D6F7B0423C28","group_id_src":"V-254253","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254253r958702"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254254","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Review the registry permissions for the keys of the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE hive noted below.\n\nIf any nonprivileged groups such as Everyone, Users, or Authenticated Users have greater than Read permission, this is a finding.\n\nIf permissions are not as restrictive as the default permissions listed below, this is a finding:\n\nRun \"Regedit\".\n\nRight-click on the registry areas noted below.\n\nSelect \"Permissions\" and \"Advanced\".\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SECURITY\n\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Special - This key and subkeys\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\n\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nUsers - Read - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read - This key and subkeys\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\n\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nAuthenticated Users - Read - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - This key and Subkeys\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read - This key and subkeys\nServer Operators - Read - This Key and subkeys (Domain controllers only)\n\nOther examples under the noted keys may also be sampled. There may be some instances where nonprivileged groups have greater than Read permission.\n\nMicrosoft has given Read permission to the SOFTWARE and SYSTEM registry keys in Windows Server 2022 to the following SID. This is currently not a finding.\nS-1-15-3-1024-1065365936-1281604716-3511738428-1654721687-432734479-3232135806-4053264122-3456934681\n\nIf the defaults have not been changed, these are not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Maintain the default permissions for the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE registry hive.\n\nThe default permissions of the higher-level keys are noted below.\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SECURITY\n\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Special - This key and subkeys\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\n\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nUsers - Read - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read - This key and subkeys\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\n\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nAuthenticated Users - Read - This key and subkeys\nAdministrators - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nSYSTEM - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nCREATOR OWNER - Full Control - This key and subkeys\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read - This key and subkeys\nServer Operators - Read - This Key and subkeys (Domain controllers only)\n\nMicrosoft has also given Read permission to the SOFTWARE and SYSTEM registry keys in Windows Server 2022 to the following SID:\nS-1-15-3-1024-1065365936-1281604716-3511738428-1654721687-432734479-3232135806-4053264122-3456934681","rule_version":"WN22-00-000170","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The registry is integral to the function, security, and stability of the Windows system. Changing the system's registry permissions allows the possibility of unauthorized and anonymous modification to the operating system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :     false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       false (The system is a Windows Domain Controller)\nTest            :       false (Default Domain Controller permissions for the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM registry key must be maintained.)\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The system is a Windows Domain Controller) (negated)\nTest            :       true (Default Non-Domain Controller permissions for the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM registry key must be maintained.)\nTest            :   true (Default permissions for the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SECURITY registry key must be maintained.)\nTest            :   true (Default Non-Domain Controller permissions for the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE registry key must be maintained.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 default permissions for the HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE registry hive must be maintained.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254254","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254254","rule_id_src":"SV-254254r1153443_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A422212-6E2B-1014-9CD2-E96F44A3052B","group_id_src":"V-254254","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254254r1153443"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:3501","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","comments":null,"check_content":"Open \"Printers &amp; scanners\" in \"Settings\".\n\nIf there are no printers configured, this is NA. (Exclude Microsoft Print to PDF and Microsoft XPS Document Writer, which do not support sharing.)\n\nFor each printer:\n\nSelect the printer and \"Manage\". \n\nSelect \"Printer Properties\". \n\nSelect the \"Sharing\" tab. \n\nIf \"Share this printer\" is checked, select the \"Security\" tab.\n\nIf any standard user accounts or groups have permissions other than \"Print\", this is a finding.\n\nThe default is for the \"Everyone\" group to be given \"Print\" permission.\n\n\"All APPLICATION PACKAGES\" and \"CREATOR OWNER\" are not standard user accounts.","severity":"low","fix_text":"Configure the permissions on shared printers to restrict standard users to only have Print permissions.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000180","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Windows shares are a means by which files, folders, printers, and other resources can be published for network users to access. Improper configuration can permit access to devices and data beyond a user's need.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT III, V-254255, SV-254255r1137691, SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 nonadministrative accounts or groups must only have print permissions on printer shares.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254255","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254255","rule_id_src":"SV-254255r1137691_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42259E-6E2B-1014-A040-9175B074F897","group_id_src":"V-254255","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254255r1137691"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:3701","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000118-GPOS-00060","comments":null,"check_content":"Open \"Windows PowerShell\".\n\nDomain Controllers:\n\nEnter \"Search-ADAccount -AccountInactive -UsersOnly -TimeSpan 35.00:00:00\"\n\nThis will return accounts that have not been logged on to for 35 days, along with various attributes such as the Enabled status and LastLogonDate.\n\nMember servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems:\n\nCopy or enter the lines below to the PowerShell window and enter. (Entering twice may be required. Do not include the quotes at the beginning and end of the query.)\n\n\"([ADSI]('WinNT://{0}' -f $env:COMPUTERNAME)).Children | Where { $_.SchemaClassName -eq 'user' } | ForEach {\n $user = ([ADSI]$_.Path)\n $lastLogin = $user.Properties.LastLogin.Value\n $enabled = ($user.Properties.UserFlags.Value -band 0x2) -ne 0x2\n if ($lastLogin -eq $null) {\n $lastLogin = 'Never'\n }\n Write-Host $user.Name $lastLogin $enabled \n}\"\n\nThis will return a list of local accounts with the account name, last logon, and if the account is enabled (True/False).\nFor example: User1 10/31/2015 5:49:56 AM True\n\nReview the list of accounts returned by the above queries to determine the finding validity for each account reported.\n\nExclude the following accounts:\n\n- Built-in administrator account (Renamed, SID ending in 500)\n- Built-in guest account (Renamed, Disabled, SID ending in 501)\n- Application accounts\n\nIf any enabled accounts have not been logged on to within the past 35 days, this is a finding.\n\nInactive accounts that have been reviewed and deemed to be required must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Regularly review accounts to determine if they are still active. Remove or disable accounts that have not been used in the last 35 days.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000190","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Outdated or unused accounts provide penetration points that may go undetected. Inactive accounts must be deleted if no longer necessary or, if still required, disabled until needed.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254256, SV-254256r1051088, SRG-OS-000118-GPOS-00060)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 outdated or unused accounts must be removed or disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-003627","CCI-000795"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254256","title":"SRG-OS-000118-GPOS-00060"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254256","rule_id_src":"SV-254256r1051088_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42292A-6E2B-1014-AA02-B23093E38FE5","group_id_src":"V-254256","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254256r1051088"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254257","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000104-GPOS-00051","comments":null,"check_content":"Review the password required status for enabled user accounts.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nDomain Controllers:\n\nEnter \"Get-Aduser -Filter * -Properties Passwordnotrequired |FT Name, Passwordnotrequired, Enabled\".\n\nExclude disabled accounts (e.g., DefaultAccount, Guest) and Trusted Domain Objects (TDOs).\n\nIf \"Passwordnotrequired\" is \"True\" or blank for any enabled user account, this is a finding.\n\nMember servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems:\n\nEnter 'Get-CimInstance -Class Win32_Useraccount -Filter \"PasswordRequired=False and LocalAccount=True\" | FT Name, PasswordRequired, Disabled, LocalAccount'.\n\nExclude disabled accounts (e.g., DefaultAccount, Guest).\n\nIf any enabled user accounts are returned with a \"PasswordRequired\" status of \"False\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure all enabled accounts to require passwords.\n\nThe password required flag can be set by entering the following on a command line: \"Net user [username] /passwordreq:yes\", substituting [username] with the name of the user account.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000200","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The lack of password protection enables anyone to gain access to the information system, which opens a backdoor opportunity for intruders to compromise the system as well as other resources. Accounts on a system must require passwords.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Windows Server - Accounts must require passwords.)\nTest            :     true (The system is a Windows Standalone Server or a Windows Domain Member Server)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Windows Domain Controller - Accounts must require passwords.)\nTest            :     false (The system is a Windows Domain Controller)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 accounts must require passwords.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000764"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254257","title":"SRG-OS-000104-GPOS-00051"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254257","rule_id_src":"SV-254257r958482_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A422CC7-6E2B-1014-BB4C-89865D8FFB91","group_id_src":"V-254257","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254257r958482"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254258","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","comments":null,"check_content":"Review the password never expires status for enabled user accounts.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nDomain Controllers:\n\nEnter \"Search-ADAccount -PasswordNeverExpires -UsersOnly | FT Name, PasswordNeverExpires, Enabled\".\n\nExclude application accounts, disabled accounts (e.g., DefaultAccount, Guest) and the krbtgt account.\n\nIf any enabled user accounts are returned with a \"PasswordNeverExpires\" status of \"True\", this is a finding.\n\nMember servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems:\n\nEnter 'Get-CimInstance -Class Win32_Useraccount -Filter \"PasswordExpires=False and LocalAccount=True\" | FT Name, PasswordExpires, Disabled, LocalAccount'.\n\nExclude application accounts and disabled accounts (e.g., DefaultAccount, Guest).\n\nIf any enabled user accounts are returned with a \"PasswordExpires\" status of \"False\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure all enabled user account passwords to expire.\n\nUncheck \"Password never expires\" for all enabled user accounts in Active Directory Users and Computers for domain accounts and Users in Computer Management for member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems. Document any exceptions with the  information system security officer (ISSO).","rule_version":"WN22-00-000210","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Passwords that do not expire or are reused increase the exposure of a password with greater probability of being discovered or cracked.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Windows Server - Local User Account Passwords from Enabled Users must be configured to expire.)\nResult Analysis :          Existence requirement is 'none_exists' and 1 collected item exists, so result is false\nTest            :     true (The system is a Windows Standalone Server or a Windows Domain Member Server)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Windows Domain Controller - Active Directory User Account Passwords for Enabled Users must be configured to expire.)\nTest            :     false (The system is a Windows Domain Controller)\nResult Analysis :          domainrole = '2' failed test of 'equals' compared to '5' \n                : domainrole = '2' failed test of 'equals' compared to '4' \n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 passwords must be configured to expire.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000199"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254258","title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254258","rule_id_src":"SV-254258r1051089_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42305A-6E2B-1014-BBAF-85C0B5523006","group_id_src":"V-254258","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254258r1051089"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:4301","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000363-GPOS-00150","comments":null,"check_content":"Determine whether the system is monitored for unauthorized changes to system files (e.g., *.exe, *.bat, *.com, *.cmd, and *.dll) against a baseline on a weekly basis.\n\nIf system files are not monitored for unauthorized changes, this is a finding.\n\nAn approved and properly configured solution will contain both a list of baselines that includes all system file locations and a file comparison task that is scheduled to run at least weekly.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Monitor the system for unauthorized changes to system files (e.g., *.exe, *.bat, *.com, *.cmd, and *.dll) against a baseline on a weekly basis. This can be done with the use of various monitoring tools.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000220","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Monitoring system files for changes against a baseline on a regular basis may help detect the possible introduction of malicious code on a system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254259, SV-254259r958794, SRG-OS-000363-GPOS-00150)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 system files must be monitored for unauthorized changes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001744"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254259","title":"SRG-OS-000363-GPOS-00150"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254259","rule_id_src":"SV-254259r958794_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4233D5-6E2B-1014-9DF1-A814C07DB2E4","group_id_src":"V-254259","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254259r958794"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:4501","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","comments":null,"check_content":"If only system-created shares such as \"ADMIN$\", \"C$\", and \"IPC$\" exist on the system, this is NA. (System-created shares will display a message that it has been shared for administrative purposes when \"Properties\" is selected.)\n\nRun \"Computer Management\".\n\nNavigate to System Tools &gt;&gt; Shared Folders &gt;&gt; Shares.\n\nRight-click any nonsystem-created shares.\n\nSelect \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Share Permissions\" tab.\n\nIf the file shares have not been configured to restrict permissions to the specific groups or accounts that require access, this is a finding.\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nIf the permissions have not been configured to restrict permissions to the specific groups or accounts that require access, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"If a nonsystem-created share is required on a system, configure the share and NTFS permissions to limit access to the specific groups or accounts that require it.\n\nRemove any unnecessary nonsystem-created shares.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000230","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Shares on a system provide network access. To prevent exposing sensitive information, where shares are necessary, permissions must be reconfigured to give the minimum access to accounts that require it.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254260, SV-254260r1137695, SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 nonsystem-created file shares must limit access to groups that require it.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001090"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254260","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254260","rule_id_src":"SV-254260r1137695_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42374E-6E2B-1014-8C5E-A27A0C180C17","group_id_src":"V-254260","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254260r1137695"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254261","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"Search all drives for *.p12 and *.pfx files.\n\nIf any files with these extensions exist, this is a finding.\n\nThis does not apply to server-based applications that have a requirement for .p12 certificate files or Adobe PreFlight certificate files. Some applications create files with extensions of .p12 that are not certificate installation files. Removal of noncertificate installation files from systems is not required. These must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Remove any certificate installation files (*.p12 and *.pfx) found on a system.\n\nNote: This does not apply to server-based applications that have a requirement for .p12 certificate files or Adobe PreFlight certificate files.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000240","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Use of software certificates and their accompanying installation files for end users to access resources is less secure than the use of hardware-based certificates.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Software certificate installation files must be removed. .p12 files)\nTest            :   true (Software certificate installation files must be removed. .pfx  files)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have software certificate installation files removed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254261","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254261","rule_id_src":"SV-254261r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A423AA4-6E2B-1014-8329-E8D71A6C1BC1","group_id_src":"V-254261","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254261r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:4901","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000185-GPOS-00079","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify systems that require additional protections due to factors such as inadequate physical protection or sensitivity of the data employ encryption to protect the confidentiality and integrity of all information at rest.\n\nIf they do not, this is a finding.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure systems that require additional protections due to factors such as inadequate physical protection or sensitivity of the data to employ encryption to protect the confidentiality and integrity of all information at rest.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000250","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This requirement addresses protection of user-generated data as well as operating system-specific configuration data. Organizations may choose to employ different mechanisms to achieve confidentiality and integrity protections, as appropriate, in accordance with the security category and/or classification of the information.\n\nSelection of a cryptographic mechanism is based on the need to protect the integrity of organizational information. The strength of the mechanism is commensurate with the security category and/or classification of the information. Organizations have the flexibility to either encrypt all information on storage devices (i.e., full disk encryption) or encrypt specific data structures (e.g., files, records, or fields).\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000185-GPOS-00079, SRG-OS-000404-GPOS-00183, SRG-OS-000405-GPOS-00184","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-254262, SV-254262r958552, SRG-OS-000185-GPOS-00079)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 systems requiring data at rest protections must employ cryptographic mechanisms to prevent unauthorized disclosure and modification of the information at rest.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001199","CCI-002475","CCI-002476"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254262","title":"SRG-OS-000185-GPOS-00079"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254262","rule_id_src":"SV-254262r958552_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A423E47-6E2B-1014-9382-B59FAED1F01D","group_id_src":"V-254262","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254262r958552"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:5101","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000425-GPOS-00189","comments":null,"check_content":"If the data owner has a strict requirement for ensuring data integrity and confidentiality is maintained at every step of the data transfer and handling process, verify protection methods such as TLS, encrypted VPNs, or IPsec have been implemented.\n\nIf protection methods have not been implemented, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure protection methods such as TLS, encrypted VPNs, or IPsec when the data owner has a strict requirement for ensuring data integrity and confidentiality is maintained at every step of the data transfer and handling process.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000260","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Information can be either unintentionally or maliciously disclosed or modified during preparation for transmission, for example, during aggregation, at protocol transformation points, and during packing/unpacking. These unauthorized disclosures or modifications compromise the confidentiality or integrity of the information.\n\nEnsuring the confidentiality of transmitted information requires the operating system to take measures in preparing information for transmission. This can be accomplished via access control and encryption.\n\nUse of this requirement will be limited to situations where the data owner has a strict requirement for ensuring data integrity and confidentiality is maintained at every step of the data transfer and handling process. When transmitting data, operating systems need to support transmission protection mechanisms such as TLS, encrypted VPNs, or IPsec.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000425-GPOS-00189, SRG-OS-000426-GPOS-00190","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254263, SV-254263r958912, SRG-OS-000425-GPOS-00189)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must implement protection methods such as TLS, encrypted VPNs, or IPsec if the data owner has a strict requirement for ensuring data integrity and confidentiality is maintained at every step of the data transfer and handling process.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002420","CCI-002422"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254263","title":"SRG-OS-000425-GPOS-00189"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254263","rule_id_src":"SV-254263r958912_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42420D-6E2B-1014-9378-C9D17E2BCAF0","group_id_src":"V-254263","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254263r958912"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:5301","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"Required roles and features will vary based on the function of the individual system.\n\nRoles and features specifically required to be disabled per the STIG are identified in separate requirements.\n\nIf the organization has not documented the roles and features required for the system(s), this is a finding.\n\nThe PowerShell command \"Get-WindowsFeature\" will list all roles and features with an \"Install State\".","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Document the roles and features required for the system to operate. Uninstall any that are not required.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000270","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Unnecessary roles and features increase the attack surface of a system. Limiting roles and features of a system to only those necessary reduces this potential. The standard installation option (previously called Server Core) further reduces this when selected at installation.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254264, SV-254264r958478, SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have the roles and features required by the system documented.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254264","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254264","rule_id_src":"SV-254264r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4246F0-6E2B-1014-9300-FB1FA30EC097","group_id_src":"V-254264","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254264r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:5501","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"Determine if a host-based firewall is installed and enabled on the system.\n\nIf a host-based firewall is not installed and enabled on the system, this is a finding.\n\nThe configuration requirements will be determined by the applicable firewall STIG.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Install and enable a host-based firewall on the system.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000280","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack, allowing or blocking inbound and outbound connections based on a set of rules.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00232","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254265, SV-254265r991589, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have a host-based firewall installed and enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366","CCI-002080"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254265","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254265","rule_id_src":"SV-254265r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A424BCF-6E2B-1014-9ED9-E37C761173C2","group_id_src":"V-254265","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254265r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:5701","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000191-GPOS-00080","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify DOD-approved ESS software is installed and properly operating. Ask the site information system security manager (ISSM) for documentation of the ESS software installation and configuration.\n\nIf the ISSM is not able to provide a documented configuration for an installed ESS or if the ESS software is not properly maintained or used, this is a finding.\n\nNote: Example of documentation can be a copy of the site's configuration control board (CCB)-approved software baseline with version of software noted or a memo from the ISSM stating current ESS software and version.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Install a DOD-approved ESS software and ensure it is operating continuously.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000290","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Without the use of automated mechanisms to scan for security flaws on a continuous and/or periodic basis, the operating system or other system components may remain vulnerable to the exploits presented by undetected software flaws. The operating system may have an integrated solution incorporating continuous scanning using ESS and periodic scanning using other tools.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254266, SV-254266r1000154, SRG-OS-000191-GPOS-00080)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must employ automated mechanisms to determine the state of system components with regard to flaw remediation using the following frequency: continuously, where Endpoint Security Solution (ESS) is used; 30 days, for any additional internal network scans not covered by ESS; and annually, for external scans by Computer Network Defense Service Provider (CNDSP).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254266","title":"SRG-OS-000191-GPOS-00080"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254266","rule_id_src":"SV-254266r1000154_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A424FA8-6E2B-1014-81ED-F121D67F1D12","group_id_src":"V-254266","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254266r1000154"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:5901","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000002-GPOS-00002","comments":null,"check_content":"Review temporary user accounts for expiration dates.\n\nDetermine if temporary user accounts are used and identify any that exist. If none exist, this is NA.\n\nDomain Controllers:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Search-ADAccount -AccountExpiring | FT Name, AccountExpirationDate\".\n\nIf \"AccountExpirationDate\" has not been defined within 72 hours for any temporary user account, this is a finding.\n\nMember servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems:\n\nOpen \"Command Prompt\".\n\nRun \"Net user [username]\", where [username] is the name of the temporary user account.\n\nIf \"Account expires\" has not been defined within 72 hours for any temporary user account, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure temporary user accounts to automatically expire within 72 hours.\n\nDomain accounts can be configured with an account expiration date, under \"Account\" properties.\n\nLocal accounts can be configured to expire with the command \"Net user [username] /expires:[mm/dd/yyyy]\", where [username] is the name of the temporary user account.\n\nDelete any temporary user accounts that are no longer necessary.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000300","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"If temporary user accounts remain active when no longer needed or for an excessive period, these accounts may be used to gain unauthorized access. To mitigate this risk, automated termination of all temporary accounts must be set upon account creation.\n\nTemporary accounts are established as part of normal account activation procedures when there is a need for short-term accounts without the demand for immediacy in account activation.\n\nIf temporary accounts are used, the operating system must be configured to automatically terminate these types of accounts after a DoD-defined time period of 72 hours.\n\nTo address access requirements, many operating systems may be integrated with enterprise-level authentication/access mechanisms that meet or exceed access control policy requirements.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254267, SV-254267r958364, SRG-OS-000002-GPOS-00002)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must automatically remove or disable temporary user accounts after 72 hours.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000016"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254267","title":"SRG-OS-000002-GPOS-00002"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254267","rule_id_src":"SV-254267r958364_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A425363-6E2B-1014-9308-B3AE01FD1BFC","group_id_src":"V-254267","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254267r958364"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:6101","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000123-GPOS-00064","comments":null,"check_content":"Determine if emergency administrator accounts are used and identify any that exist. If none exist, this is NA.\n\nIf emergency administrator accounts cannot be configured with an expiration date due to an ongoing crisis, the accounts must be disabled or removed when the crisis is resolved.\n\nIf emergency administrator accounts have not been configured with an expiration date or have not been disabled or removed following the resolution of a crisis, this is a finding.\n\nDomain Controllers:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Search-ADAccount -AccountExpiring | FT Name, AccountExpirationDate\".\n\nIf \"AccountExpirationDate\" has been defined and is not within 72 hours for an emergency administrator account, this is a finding.\n\nMember servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems:\n\nOpen \"Command Prompt\".\n\nRun \"Net user [username]\", where [username] is the name of the emergency account.\n\nIf \"Account expires\" has been defined and is not within 72 hours for an emergency administrator account, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Remove emergency administrator accounts after a crisis has been resolved or configure the accounts to automatically expire within 72 hours.\n\nDomain accounts can be configured with an account expiration date, under \"Account\" properties.\n\nLocal accounts can be configured to expire with the command \"Net user [username] /expires:[mm/dd/yyyy]\", where [username] is the name of the temporary user account.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000310","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Emergency administrator accounts are privileged accounts established in response to crisis situations where the need for rapid account activation is required. Therefore, emergency account activation may bypass normal account authorization processes. If these accounts are automatically disabled, system maintenance during emergencies may not be possible, thus adversely affecting system availability.\n\nEmergency administrator accounts are different from infrequently used accounts (i.e., local logon accounts used by system administrators when network or normal logon/access is not available). Infrequently used accounts are not subject to automatic termination dates. Emergency accounts are accounts created in response to crisis situations, usually for use by maintenance personnel. The automatic expiration or disabling time period may be extended as needed until the crisis is resolved; however, it must not be extended indefinitely. A permanent account must be established for privileged users who need long-term maintenance accounts.\n\nTo address access requirements, many operating systems can be integrated with enterprise-level authentication/access mechanisms that meet or exceed access control policy requirements.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254268, SV-254268r958508, SRG-OS-000123-GPOS-00064)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must automatically remove or disable emergency accounts after the crisis is resolved or within 72 hours.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001682"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254268","title":"SRG-OS-000123-GPOS-00064"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254268","rule_id_src":"SV-254268r958508_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42573D-6E2B-1014-8624-9AFEBBABC0ED","group_id_src":"V-254268","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254268r958508"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254269","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"Open \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-WindowsFeature | Where Name -eq Fax\".\n\nIf \"Installed State\" is \"Installed\", this is a finding.\n\nAn Installed State of \"Available\" or \"Removed\" is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Uninstall the \"Fax Server\" role.\n\nStart \"Server Manager\".\n\nSelect the server with the role.\n\nScroll down to \"ROLES AND FEATURES\" in the right pane.\n\nSelect \"Remove Roles and Features\" from the drop-down \"TASKS\" list.\n\nSelect the appropriate server on the \"Server Selection\" page and click \"Next\".\n\nDeselect \"Fax Server\" on the \"Roles\" page.\n\nClick \"Next\" and \"Remove\" as prompted.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000320","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Unnecessary services increase the attack surface of a system. Some of these services may not support required levels of authentication or encryption or may provide unauthorized access to the system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The Fax server role is not installed.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must not have the Fax Server role installed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254269","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254269","rule_id_src":"SV-254269r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A425AB7-6E2B-1014-B939-9FCBF58D1D0F","group_id_src":"V-254269","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254269r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254270","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","comments":null,"check_content":"If the server has the role of an FTP server, this is NA.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-WindowsFeature | Where Name -eq Web-Ftp-Service\".\n\nIf \"Installed State\" is \"Installed\", this is a finding.\n\nAn Installed State of \"Available\" or \"Removed\" is not a finding.\n\nIf the system has the role of an FTP server, this must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Uninstall the \"FTP Server\" role.\n\nStart \"Server Manager\".\n\nSelect the server with the role.\n\nScroll down to \"ROLES AND FEATURES\" in the right pane.\n\nSelect \"Remove Roles and Features\" from the drop-down \"TASKS\" list.\n\nSelect the appropriate server on the \"Server Selection\" page and click \"Next\".\n\nDeselect \"FTP Server\" under \"Web Server (IIS)\" on the \"Roles\" page.\n\nClick \"Next\" and \"Remove\" as prompted.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000330","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Unnecessary services increase the attack surface of a system. Some of these services may not support required levels of authentication or encryption.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Check to make sure the FTP server role is not present.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must not have the Microsoft FTP service installed unless required by the organization.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000382"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254270","title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254270","rule_id_src":"SV-254270r958480_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A425E2D-6E2B-1014-BBA8-8ED9BF74328A","group_id_src":"V-254270","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254270r958480"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254271","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"Open \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-WindowsFeature | Where Name -eq PNRP\".\n\nIf \"Installed State\" is \"Installed\", this is a finding.\n\nAn Installed State of \"Available\" or \"Removed\" is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Uninstall the \"Peer Name Resolution Protocol\" feature.\n\nStart \"Server Manager\".\n\nSelect the server with the feature.\n\nScroll down to \"ROLES AND FEATURES\" in the right pane.\n\nSelect \"Remove Roles and Features\" from the drop-down \"TASKS\" list.\n\nSelect the appropriate server on the \"Server Selection\" page and click \"Next\".\n\nDeselect \"Peer Name Resolution Protocol\" on the \"Features\" page.\n\nClick \"Next\" and \"Remove\" as prompted.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000340","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Unnecessary services increase the attack surface of a system. Some of these services may not support required levels of authentication or encryption or may provide unauthorized access to the system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The Peer Name Resolution Protocol server feature is disabled or not present)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must not have the Peer Name Resolution Protocol installed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254271","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254271","rule_id_src":"SV-254271r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A426192-6E2B-1014-9E84-C8F24D29829E","group_id_src":"V-254271","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254271r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254272","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"Open \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-WindowsFeature | Where Name -eq Simple-TCPIP\".\n\nIf \"Installed State\" is \"Installed\", this is a finding.\n\nAn Installed State of \"Available\" or \"Removed\" is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Uninstall the \"Simple TCP/IP Services\" feature.\n\nStart \"Server Manager\".\n\nSelect the server with the feature.\n\nScroll down to \"ROLES AND FEATURES\" in the right pane.\n\nSelect \"Remove Roles and Features\" from the drop-down \"TASKS\" list.\n\nSelect the appropriate server on the \"Server Selection\" page and click \"Next\".\n\nDeselect \"Simple TCP/IP Services\" on the \"Features\" page.\n\nClick \"Next\" and \"Remove\" as prompted.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000350","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Unnecessary services increase the attack surface of a system. Some of these services may not support required levels of authentication or encryption or may provide unauthorized access to the system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Check to make sure the Simple TCP/IP Services server feature is not present.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must not have Simple TCP/IP Services installed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254272","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254272","rule_id_src":"SV-254272r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4264E8-6E2B-1014-BFE9-A3168A9DBF75","group_id_src":"V-254272","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254272r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254273","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","comments":null,"check_content":"Open \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-WindowsFeature | Where Name -eq Telnet-Client\".\n\nIf \"Installed State\" is \"Installed\", this is a finding.\n\nAn Installed State of \"Available\" or \"Removed\" is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Uninstall the \"Telnet Client\" feature.\n\nStart \"Server Manager\".\n\nSelect the server with the feature.\n\nScroll down to \"ROLES AND FEATURES\" in the right pane.\n\nSelect \"Remove Roles and Features\" from the drop-down \"TASKS\" list.\n\nSelect the appropriate server on the \"Server Selection\" page and click \"Next\".\n\nDeselect \"Telnet Client\" on the \"Features\" page.\n\nClick \"Next\" and \"Remove\" as prompted.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000360","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Unnecessary services increase the attack surface of a system. Some of these services may not support required levels of authentication or encryption or may provide unauthorized access to the system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: errorRule Result     : Error\nCriteria        : error (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   error (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     error (The Telnet Client is not installed on the system)\nError Informatio: \"Could not execute WMI query SELECT installstate FROM win32_optionalfeature WHERE name = 'TelnetClient' on SOT-WIN2K22-01 - WMI Error Info.Info: OLE exception from \"SWbemServicesEx\":The process cannot access the file because it is being used by anotherprocess. Win32::OLE(0.1713) error 0x80070020: \"The process cannot access the filebecause it is being used by another process\"    in METHOD/PROPERTYGET \"ExecQuery\"\" from Probe_WMI57 found in Probe_WMI57 (989).\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must not have the Telnet Client installed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000382"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254273","title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254273","rule_id_src":"SV-254273r958480_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42683E-6E2B-1014-A47E-D8384EDEEC05","group_id_src":"V-254273","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254273r958480"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254274","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"Open \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-WindowsFeature | Where Name -eq TFTP-Client\".\n\nIf \"Installed State\" is \"Installed\", this is a finding.\n\nAn Installed State of \"Available\" or \"Removed\" is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Uninstall the \"TFTP Client\" feature.\n\nStart \"Server Manager\".\n\nSelect the server with the feature.\n\nScroll down to \"ROLES AND FEATURES\" in the right pane.\n\nSelect \"Remove Roles and Features\" from the drop-down \"TASKS\" list.\n\nSelect the appropriate server on the \"Server Selection\" page and click \"Next\".\n\nDeselect \"TFTP Client\" on the \"Features\" page.\n\nClick \"Next\" and \"Remove\" as prompted.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000370","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Unnecessary services increase the attack surface of a system. Some of these services may not support required levels of authentication or encryption or may provide unauthorized access to the system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: errorRule Result     : Error\nCriteria        : error (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   error (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     error (The TFTP Client is not installed on the system)\nError Informatio: \"Could not execute WMI query SELECT installstate FROM win32_optionalfeature WHERE name = 'TFTP' on SOT-WIN2K22-01 - WMI Error Info.Info: OLE exception from \"SWbemServicesEx\":The process cannot access the file because it is being used by anotherprocess. Win32::OLE(0.1713) error 0x80070020: \"The process cannot access the filebecause it is being used by another process\"    in METHOD/PROPERTYGET \"ExecQuery\"\" from Probe_WMI57 found in Probe_WMI57 (989).\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must not have the TFTP Client installed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254274","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254274","rule_id_src":"SV-254274r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A426BA1-6E2B-1014-A868-FEE8DFDA1257","group_id_src":"V-254274","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254274r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254275","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"Different methods are available to disable SMBv1 on Windows Server 2022. This is the preferred method, however if WN22-00-000390 and WN22-00-000400 are configured, this is NA.\n\nOpen \"Windows PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter \"Get-WindowsFeature -Name FS-SMB1\".\n\nIf \"Installed State\" is \"Installed\", this is a finding.\n\nAn Installed State of \"Available\" or \"Removed\" is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Uninstall the SMBv1 protocol.\n\nOpen \"Windows PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter \"Uninstall-WindowsFeature -Name FS-SMB1 -Restart\".\n(Omit the Restart parameter if an immediate restart of the system cannot be done.)\n\nAlternately:\n\nStart \"Server Manager\".\n\nSelect the server with the feature.\n\nScroll down to \"ROLES AND FEATURES\" in the right pane.\n\nSelect \"Remove Roles and Features\" from the drop-down \"TASKS\" list.\n\nSelect the appropriate server on the \"Server Selection\" page and click \"Next\".\n\nDeselect \"SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support\" on the \"Features\" page.\n\nClick \"Next\" and \"Remove\" as prompted.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000380","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"SMBv1 is a legacy protocol that uses the MD5 algorithm as part of SMB. MD5 is known to be vulnerable to a number of attacks such as collision and preimage attacks and is not FIPS compliant.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :       true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :         true ('SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support' feature is not installed)\nTest            :         true ('Configure SMBv1 Server' is set to 'Disabled')\nCriteria        :       true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :         true ('SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support' feature is not installed)\nTest            :         true ('Configure SMBv1 client driver' is set to 'Enabled' with 'Disable driver (recommended)' selected for 'Configure MrxSmb10 driver')\nTest            :     true ('SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support' feature is not installed)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must not the Server Message Block (SMB) v1 protocol installed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254275","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254275","rule_id_src":"SV-254275r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A426F04-6E2B-1014-A3DC-CCE922C0E29D","group_id_src":"V-254275","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254275r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254276","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"Different methods are available to disable SMBv1 on Windows Server 2022, if WN22-00-000380 is configured, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SMB1\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; MS Security Guide &gt;&gt; Configure SMBv1 Server to \"Disabled\".\n\nThe system must be restarted for the change to take effect.\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000390","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"SMBv1 is a legacy protocol that uses the MD5 algorithm as part of SMB. MD5 is known to be vulnerable to a number of attacks such as collision and preimage attacks as well as not being FIPS compliant.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     true ('SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support' feature is not installed)\nTest            :     true ('Configure SMBv1 Server' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have the Server Message Block (SMB) v1 protocol disabled on the SMB server.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254276","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254276","rule_id_src":"SV-254276r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A427262-6E2B-1014-8754-BF8955D5FC03","group_id_src":"V-254276","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254276r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254277","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"Different methods are available to disable SMBv1 on Windows Server 2022, if WN22-00-000380 is configured, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\mrxsmb10\\\n\nValue Name: Start\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000004 (4)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; MS Security Guide &gt;&gt; Configure SMBv1 client driver to \"Enabled\" with \"Disable driver (recommended)\" selected for \"Configure MrxSmb10 driver\".\n\nThe system must be restarted for the changes to take effect.\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000400","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"SMBv1 is a legacy protocol that uses the MD5 algorithm as part of SMB. MD5 is known to be vulnerable to a number of attacks such as collision and preimage attacks as well as not being FIPS compliant.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     true ('SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support' feature is not installed)\nTest            :     true ('Configure SMBv1 client driver' is set to 'Enabled' with 'Disable driver (recommended)' selected for 'Configure MrxSmb10 driver')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have the Server Message Block (SMB) v1 protocol disabled on the SMB client.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254277","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254277","rule_id_src":"SV-254277r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4275D7-6E2B-1014-9923-DDD9FA934D01","group_id_src":"V-254277","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254277r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254278","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"Open \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-WindowsFeature | Where Name -eq PowerShell-v2\".\n\nIf \"Installed State\" is \"Installed\", this is a finding.\n\nAn Installed State of \"Available\" or \"Removed\" is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Uninstall the \"Windows PowerShell 2.0 Engine\".\n\nStart \"Server Manager\".\n\nSelect the server with the feature.\n\nScroll down to \"ROLES AND FEATURES\" in the right pane.\n\nSelect \"Remove Roles and Features\" from the drop-down \"TASKS\" list.\n\nSelect the appropriate server on the \"Server Selection\" page and click \"Next\".\n\nDeselect \"Windows PowerShell 2.0 Engine\" under \"Windows PowerShell\" on the \"Features\" page.\n\nClick \"Next\" and \"Remove\" as prompted.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000410","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Windows PowerShell 5.x added advanced logging features that can provide additional detail when malware has been run on a system. Disabling the Windows PowerShell 2.0 mitigates against a downgrade attack that evades the Windows PowerShell 5.x script block logging feature.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Windows PowerShell 2.0 feature is not installed)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must not have Windows PowerShell 2.0 installed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254278","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254278","rule_id_src":"SV-254278r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A427932-6E2B-1014-B606-F23A5836B8F7","group_id_src":"V-254278","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254278r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254279","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If FTP is not installed on the system, this is NA.\n\nOpen \"Internet Information Services (IIS) Manager\".\n\nSelect the server.\n\nDouble-click \"FTP Authentication\".\n\nIf the \"Anonymous Authentication\" status is \"Enabled\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the FTP service to prevent anonymous logons.\n\nOpen \"Internet Information Services (IIS) Manager\".\n\nSelect the server.\n\nDouble-click \"FTP Authentication\".\n\nSelect \"Anonymous Authentication\".\n\nSelect \"Disabled\" under \"Actions\".","rule_version":"WN22-00-000420","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The FTP service allows remote users to access shared files and directories. Allowing anonymous FTP connections makes user auditing difficult.\n\nUsing accounts that have administrator privileges to log on to FTP risks that the userid and password will be captured on the network and give administrator access to an unauthorized user.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 FTP servers must be configured to prevent anonymous logons.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254279","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254279","rule_id_src":"SV-254279r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A427CA8-6E2B-1014-939A-AF43EDEB219C","group_id_src":"V-254279","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254279r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254280","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If FTP is not installed on the system, this is NA.\n\nOpen \"Internet Information Services (IIS) Manager\".\n\nSelect \"Sites\" under the server name.\n\nFor any sites with a Binding that lists FTP, right-click the site and select \"Explore\".\n\nIf the site is not defined to a specific folder for shared FTP resources, this is a finding.\n\nIf the site includes any system areas such as root of the drive, Program Files, or Windows directories, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the FTP sites to allow access only to specific FTP shared resources. Do not allow access to other areas of the system.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000430","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The FTP service allows remote users to access shared files and directories that could provide access to system resources and compromise the system, especially if the user can gain access to the root directory of the boot drive.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 FTP servers must be configured to prevent access to the system drive.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254280","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254280","rule_id_src":"SV-254280r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4282C6-6E2B-1014-9C96-F590B19A70A6","group_id_src":"V-254280","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254280r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:8701","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000355-GPOS-00143","comments":null,"check_content":"Review the Windows time service configuration.\n\nOpen an elevated \"Command Prompt\" (run as administrator).\n\nEnter \"W32tm /query /configuration\".\n\nDomain-joined systems (excluding the domain controller with the PDC emulator role):\n\nIf the value for \"Type\" under \"NTP Client\" is not \"NT5DS\", this is a finding.\n\nOther systems:\n\nIf systems are configured with a \"Type\" of \"NTP\", including standalone or nondomain-joined systems and the domain controller with the PDC Emulator role, and do not have a DOD time server defined for \"NTPServer\", this is a finding.\n\nTo determine the domain controller with the PDC Emulator role:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-ADDomain | FT PDCEmulator\".","severity":"low","fix_text":"Configure the system to synchronize time with an appropriate DOD time source.\n\nDomain-joined systems use NT5DS to synchronize time from other systems in the domain by default.\n\nIf the system needs to be configured to an NTP server, configure the system to point to an authorized time server by setting the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Windows Time Service &gt;&gt; Time Providers. Change \"Configure Windows NTP Client\" to \"Enabled\", and configure the \"NtpServer\" field to point to an appropriate DOD time server.\n\nThe US Naval Observatory operates stratum 1 time servers, identified at https://www.cnmoc.usff.navy.mil/Our-Commands/United-States-Naval-Observatory/Precise-Time-Department/Network-Time-Protocol-NTP/. Time synchronization will occur through a hierarchy of time servers down to the local level. Clients and lower-level servers will synchronize with an authorized time server in the hierarchy.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000440","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The Windows Time Service controls time synchronization settings. Time synchronization is essential for authentication and auditing purposes. If the Windows Time Service is used, it must synchronize with a secure, authorized time source. Domain-joined systems are automatically configured to synchronize with domain controllers. If an NTP server is configured, it must synchronize with a secure, authorized time source.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT III, V-254281, SV-254281r1051090, SRG-OS-000355-GPOS-00143)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The Windows Server 2022 time service must synchronize with an appropriate DOD time source.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-004923","CCI-001891"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254281","title":"SRG-OS-000355-GPOS-00143"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254281","rule_id_src":"SV-254281r1051090_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4286D2-6E2B-1014-A125-CCBD1D91190D","group_id_src":"V-254281","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254281r1051090"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254282","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"Review the effective User Rights setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nReview each User Right listed for any unresolved SIDs to determine whether they are valid, such as due to being temporarily disconnected from the domain. (Unresolved SIDs have the format that begins with \"*S-1-\".)\n\nIf any unresolved SIDs exist and are not for currently valid accounts or groups, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /export /areas USER_RIGHTS /cfg c:\\path\\UserRights.txt\n\nThe results in the file identify user right assignments by SID instead of group name. Review the SIDs for unidentified ones. A list of typical SIDs \\ Groups is below, search Microsoft for articles on well known SIDs for others. \n\nIf any unresolved SIDs exist and are not for currently valid accounts or groups, this is a finding.\n\nSID - Group\nS-1-5-11 - Authenticated Users\nS-1-5-113 - Local account\nS-1-5-114 - Local account and member of Administrators group\nS-1-5-19 - Local Service\nS-1-5-20 - Network Service\nS-1-5-32-544 - Administrators\nS-1-5-32-546 - Guests\nS-1-5-6 - Service\nS-1-5-9 - Enterprise Domain Controllers\nS-1-5-domain-512 - Domain Admins\nS-1-5-root domain-519 - Enterprise Admins\nS-1-5-80-3139157870-2983391045-3678747466-658725712-1809340420 - NT Service\\WdiServiceHost","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Remove any unresolved SIDs found in User Rights assignments and determined to not be for currently valid accounts or groups by removing the accounts or groups from the appropriate group policy.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000450","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Accounts or groups given rights on a system may show up as unresolved SIDs for various reasons including deletion of the accounts or groups. If the account or group objects are reanimated, there is a potential they may still have rights no longer intended. Valid domain accounts or groups may also show up as unresolved SIDs if a connection to the domain cannot be established.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Orphaned security identifiers (SIDs) must be removed from user rights.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have orphaned security identifiers (SIDs) removed from user rights.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254282","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254282","rule_id_src":"SV-254282r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A428B57-6E2B-1014-A6DD-D3C7FA4BABD2","group_id_src":"V-254282","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254282r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254283","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"Devices that have UEFI firmware must run in \"UEFI\" mode.\n\nVerify the system firmware is configured to run in \"UEFI\" mode, not \"Legacy BIOS\".\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", if \"BIOS Mode\" does not display \"UEFI\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure UEFI firmware to run in \"UEFI\" mode, not \"Legacy BIOS\" mode.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000460","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"UEFI provides additional security features in comparison to legacy BIOS firmware, including Secure Boot. UEFI is required to support additional security features in Windows, including Virtualization Based Security and Credential Guard. Systems with UEFI that are operating in \"Legacy BIOS\" mode will not support these security features.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Unified Extensible Firmware Interface (UEFI) firmware must exist and be configured to run in UEFI mode, not Legacy BIOS.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 systems must have Unified Extensible Firmware Interface (UEFI) firmware and be configured to run in UEFI mode, not Legacy BIOS.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254283","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254283","rule_id_src":"SV-254283r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A428F11-6E2B-1014-85B8-94082CFA7B86","group_id_src":"V-254283","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254283r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254284","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"Devices that have UEFI firmware must have Secure Boot enabled.\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", if \"Secure Boot State\" does not display \"On\", this is a finding.\n\nOn server core installations, run the following PowerShell command:\n\nConfirm-SecureBootUEFI\n\nIf a value of \"True\" is not returned, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Enable Secure Boot in the system firmware.","rule_version":"WN22-00-000470","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Secure Boot is a standard that ensures systems boot only to a trusted operating system. Secure Boot is required to support additional security features in Windows, including Virtualization Based Security and Credential Guard. If Secure Boot is turned off, these security features will not function.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Run a PowerShell command to determine if Secure Boot must be enabled.)\nResult Analysis :        'False' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'True' \n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have Secure Boot enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254284","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254284","rule_id_src":"SV-254284r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A429275-6E2B-1014-9A92-99D67577151D","group_id_src":"V-254284","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254284r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254285","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000329-GPOS-00128","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy.\n\nIf the \"Account lockout duration\" is less than \"15\" minutes (excluding \"0\"), this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"LockoutDuration\" is less than \"15\" (excluding \"0\") in the file, this is a finding.\n\nConfiguring this to \"0\", requiring an administrator to unlock the account, is more restrictive and is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy &gt;&gt; Account lockout duration to \"15\" minutes or greater.\n\nA value of \"0\" is also acceptable, requiring an administrator to unlock the account.","rule_version":"WN22-AC-000010","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The account lockout feature, when enabled, prevents brute-force password attacks on the system. This parameter specifies the period of time that an account will remain locked after the specified number of failed logon attempts.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false ('Account lockout duration' is set to '0')\nTest            :       true ('Account lockout duration' is set to '15 minutes' or greater)\nTest            :     true ('Account lockout threshold' is not set to '0')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 account lockout duration must be configured to 15 minutes or greater.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002238"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254285","title":"SRG-OS-000329-GPOS-00128"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254285","rule_id_src":"SV-254285r958736_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4295EE-6E2B-1014-8373-92FB5B15ED84","group_id_src":"V-254285","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254285r958736"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254286","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000021-GPOS-00005","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy.\n\nIf the \"Account lockout threshold\" is \"0\" or more than \"3\" attempts, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"LockoutBadCount\" equals \"0\" or is greater than \"3\" in the file, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy &gt;&gt; Account lockout threshold to \"3\" or fewer invalid logon attempts (excluding \"0\", which is unacceptable).","rule_version":"WN22-AC-000020","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The account lockout feature, when enabled, prevents brute-force password attacks on the system. The higher this value is, the less effective the account lockout feature will be in protecting the local system. The number of bad logon attempts must be reasonably small to minimize the possibility of a successful password attack while allowing for honest errors made during normal user logon.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Account lockout threshold' is set to '3' or less)\nTest            :     true ('Account lockout threshold' is not set to '0')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have the number of allowed bad logon attempts configured to three or less.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000044"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254286","title":"SRG-OS-000021-GPOS-00005"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254286","rule_id_src":"SV-254286r958388_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42996E-6E2B-1014-9F74-8497E7AEBE24","group_id_src":"V-254286","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254286r958388"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254287","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000021-GPOS-00005","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy.\n\nIf the \"Reset account lockout counter after\" value is less than \"15\" minutes, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"ResetLockoutCount\" is less than \"15\" in the file, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy &gt;&gt; Reset account lockout counter after to at least \"15\" minutes.","rule_version":"WN22-AC-000030","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The account lockout feature, when enabled, prevents brute-force password attacks on the system. This parameter specifies the period of time that must pass after failed logon attempts before the counter is reset to \"0\". The smaller this value is, the less effective the account lockout feature will be in protecting the local system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Reset account lockout counter after' is set to at least the required value)\nTest            :     true ('Account lockout threshold' is not set to '0')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have the period of time before the bad logon counter is reset configured to 15 minutes or greater.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000044"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254287","title":"SRG-OS-000021-GPOS-00005"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254287","rule_id_src":"SV-254287r958388_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A429CE1-6E2B-1014-A0B5-CFAE187809FE","group_id_src":"V-254287","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254287r958388"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254288","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000077-GPOS-00045","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for \"Enforce password history\" is less than \"24\" passwords remembered, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"PasswordHistorySize\" is less than \"24\" in the file, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; Enforce password history to \"24\" passwords remembered.","rule_version":"WN22-AC-000040","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"A system is more vulnerable to unauthorized access when system users recycle the same password several times without being required to change to a unique password on a regularly scheduled basis. This enables users to effectively negate the purpose of mandating periodic password changes. The default value is \"24\" for Windows domain systems. DOD has decided this is the appropriate value for all Windows systems.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Enforce password history' is set to '24' passwords or more)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 password history must be configured to 24 passwords remembered.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-004061"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254288","title":"SRG-OS-000077-GPOS-00045"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254288","rule_id_src":"SV-254288r1000156_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42A053-6E2B-1014-919A-A8FB1FD91D19","group_id_src":"V-254288","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254288r1000156"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254289","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for the \"Maximum password age\" is greater than \"60\" days, this is a finding.\n\nIf the value is set to \"0\" (never expires), this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"MaximumPasswordAge\" is greater than \"60\" or equal to \"0\" in the file, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; Maximum password age to \"60\" days or less (excluding \"0\", which is unacceptable).","rule_version":"WN22-AC-000050","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The longer a password is in use, the greater the opportunity for someone to gain unauthorized knowledge of the passwords. Scheduled changing of passwords hinders the ability of unauthorized system users to crack passwords and gain access to a system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Maximum Password Age is set to 60 days or less, but greater than 0.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 maximum password age must be configured to 60 days or less.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000199"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254289","title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254289","rule_id_src":"SV-254289r1051091_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42A3D1-6E2B-1014-83A0-89F876CC70B4","group_id_src":"V-254289","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254289r1051091"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254290","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000075-GPOS-00043","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for the \"Minimum password age\" is set to \"0\" days (\"Password can be changed immediately\"), this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"MinimumPasswordAge\" equals \"0\" in the file, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; Minimum password age to at least \"1\" day.","rule_version":"WN22-AC-000060","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Permitting passwords to be changed in immediate succession within the same day allows users to cycle passwords through their history database. This enables users to effectively negate the purpose of mandating periodic password changes.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Minimum Password Age' is set to at least '1' day)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 minimum password age must be configured to at least one day.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000198"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254290","title":"SRG-OS-000075-GPOS-00043"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254290","rule_id_src":"SV-254290r1051092_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42A744-6E2B-1014-B75D-B19EB5644FD6","group_id_src":"V-254290","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254290r1051092"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254291","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000078-GPOS-00046","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for the \"Minimum password length,\" is less than \"14\" characters, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"MinimumPasswordLength\" is less than \"14\" in the file, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; \"Minimum password length\" to \"14\" characters.","rule_version":"WN22-AC-000070","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Information systems not protected with strong password schemes (including passwords of minimum length) provide the opportunity for anyone to crack the password, thus gaining access to the system and compromising the device, information, or the local network.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Minimum password length' is set to at least '14' characters)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 minimum password length must be configured to 14 characters.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000205"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254291","title":"SRG-OS-000078-GPOS-00046"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254291","rule_id_src":"SV-254291r1051093_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42AAB1-6E2B-1014-B6E8-F22C1F97798E","group_id_src":"V-254291","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254291r1051093"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254292","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000069-GPOS-00037","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for \"Password must meet complexity requirements\" is not set to \"Enabled\", this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"PasswordComplexity\" equals \"0\" in the file, this is a finding.\n\nNote: If an external password filter is in use that enforces all four character types and requires this setting to be set to \"Disabled\", this would not be considered a finding. If this setting does not affect the use of an external password filter, it must be enabled for fallback purposes.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; Password must meet complexity requirements to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-AC-000080","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The use of complex passwords increases their strength against attack. The built-in Windows password complexity policy requires passwords to contain at least three of the four types of characters (numbers, uppercase and lowercase letters, and special characters) and prevents the inclusion of user names or parts of user names.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000069-GPOS-00037, SRG-OS-000070-GPOS-00038, SRG-OS-000071-GPOS-00039, SRG-OS-000266-GPOS-00101","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Password must meet complexity requirements' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have the built-in Windows password complexity policy enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000192","CCI-000193","CCI-000194","CCI-001619"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254292","title":"SRG-OS-000069-GPOS-00037"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254292","rule_id_src":"SV-254292r1051094_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42AE58-6E2B-1014-BF79-9FEA6A68FB12","group_id_src":"V-254292","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254292r1051094"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254293","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for \"Store passwords using reversible encryption\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"ClearTextPassword\" equals \"1\" in the file, this is a finding.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; Store passwords using reversible encryption to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-AC-000090","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Storing passwords using reversible encryption is essentially the same as storing clear-text versions of the passwords, which are easily compromised. For this reason, this policy must never be enabled.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Store password using reversible encryption' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 reversible password encryption must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-004062","CCI-000196"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254293","title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254293","rule_id_src":"SV-254293r1051095_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42B1F6-6E2B-1014-89DC-D27BB5EDE518","group_id_src":"V-254293","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254293r1051095"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:11301","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000342-GPOS-00133","comments":null,"check_content":"Determine if a process to back up log data to a different system or media than the system being audited has been implemented.\n\nIf it has not, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Establish and implement a process for backing up log data to another system or media other than the system being audited.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000010","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Protection of log data includes ensuring the log data is not accidentally lost or deleted. Audit information stored in one location is vulnerable to accidental or incidental deletion or alteration.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254294, SV-254294r958754, SRG-OS-000342-GPOS-00133)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 audit records must be backed up to a different system or media than the system being audited.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001851"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254294","title":"SRG-OS-000342-GPOS-00133"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254294","rule_id_src":"SV-254294r958754_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42B554-6E2B-1014-915C-EC3BC3BD782D","group_id_src":"V-254294","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254294r958754"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:11501","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000479-GPOS-00224","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the audit records, at a minimum, are offloaded for interconnected systems in real time and offloaded for standalone or nondomain-joined systems weekly. \n\nIf they are not, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the system to, at a minimum, offload audit records of interconnected systems in real time and offload standalone or nondomain-joined systems weekly.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000020","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Protection of log data includes assuring the log data is not accidentally lost or deleted. Audit information stored in one location is vulnerable to accidental or incidental deletion or alteration.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-254295, SV-254295r959008, SRG-OS-000479-GPOS-00224)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must, at a minimum, offload audit records of interconnected systems in real time and offload standalone or nondomain-joined systems weekly.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001851"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254295","title":"SRG-OS-000479-GPOS-00224"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254295","rule_id_src":"SV-254295r959008_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42B888-6E2B-1014-8E13-B99C810B1E53","group_id_src":"V-254295","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254295r959008"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254296","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","comments":null,"check_content":"Navigate to the Application event log file.\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\System32\\winevt\\Logs\" folder. However, the logs may have been moved to another folder.\n\nIf the permissions for the \"Application.evtx\" file are not as restrictive as the default permissions listed below, this is a finding:\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the permissions on the Application event log file (Application.evtx) to prevent access by nonprivileged accounts. The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement:\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\System32\\winevt\\Logs\" folder.\n\nIf the location of the logs has been changed, when adding Eventlog to the permissions, it must be entered as \"NT Service\\Eventlog\".","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000030","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. The Application event log may be susceptible to tampering if proper permissions are not applied.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027, SRG-OS-000058-GPOS-00028, SRG-OS-000059-GPOS-00029","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :     false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The Application event log must have at least default permissions. Strict Path)\nTest            :       false (The Application event log registry specified location must have the %SystemRoot% environment variable.) (negated)\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The Application event log must have at least default permissions. Built Path)\nTest            :       true (The Application event log registry specified location must have the %SystemRoot% environment variable.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 permissions for the Application event log must prevent access by nonprivileged accounts.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254296","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254296","rule_id_src":"SV-254296r958434_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42BBFB-6E2B-1014-88B7-89E2C1AC0F76","group_id_src":"V-254296","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254296r958434"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254297","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","comments":null,"check_content":"Navigate to the Security event log file.\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\System32\\winevt\\Logs\" folder. However, the logs may have been moved to another folder.\n\nIf the permissions for the \"Security.evtx\" file are not as restrictive as the default permissions listed below, this is a finding:\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the permissions on the Security event log file (Security.evtx) to prevent access by nonprivileged accounts. The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement:\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\System32\\winevt\\Logs\" folder.\n\nIf the location of the logs has been changed, when adding Eventlog to the permissions, it must be entered as \"NT Service\\Eventlog\".","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000040","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. The Security event log may disclose sensitive information or be susceptible to tampering if proper permissions are not applied.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027, SRG-OS-000058-GPOS-00028, SRG-OS-000059-GPOS-00029","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :     false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The Security event log must have at least default permissions. Strict Path)\nTest            :       false (The Security event log registry specified location must have the %SystemRoot% environment variable.) (negated)\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The Security event log must have at least default permissions. Built Path)\nTest            :       true (The Security event log registry specified location must have the %SystemRoot% environment variable.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 permissions for the Security event log must prevent access by nonprivileged accounts.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254297","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254297","rule_id_src":"SV-254297r958434_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42BF8C-6E2B-1014-8722-85DA6BE7DE99","group_id_src":"V-254297","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254297r958434"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254298","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","comments":null,"check_content":"Navigate to the System event log file.\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\System32\\winevt\\Logs\" folder. However, the logs may have been moved to another folder.\n\nIf the permissions for the \"System.evtx\" file are not as restrictive as the default permissions listed below, this is a finding:\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the permissions on the System event log file (System.evtx) to prevent access by nonprivileged accounts. The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement:\n\nEventlog - Full Control\nSYSTEM - Full Control\nAdministrators - Full Control\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\System32\\winevt\\Logs\" folder.\n\nIf the location of the logs has been changed, when adding Eventlog to the permissions, it must be entered as \"NT Service\\Eventlog\".","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000050","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. The System event log may be susceptible to tampering if proper permissions are not applied.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027, SRG-OS-000058-GPOS-00028, SRG-OS-000059-GPOS-00029","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :     false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The System event log must have at least default permissions. Strict Path)\nTest            :       false (The System event log registry specified location must have the %SystemRoot% environment variable.) (negated)\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The System event log must have at least default permissions. Built Path)\nTest            :       true (The System event log registry specified location must have the %SystemRoot% environment variable.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 permissions for the System event log must prevent access by nonprivileged accounts.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254298","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254298","rule_id_src":"SV-254298r958434_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42C333-6E2B-1014-BECC-B2F015E8AF7C","group_id_src":"V-254298","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254298r958434"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254299","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000257-GPOS-00098","comments":null,"check_content":"This is not applicable for Windows Core Edition.\n\nNavigate to \"%SystemRoot%\\System32\".\n\nView the permissions on \"Eventvwr.exe\".\n\nIf any groups or accounts other than TrustedInstaller have \"Full control\" or \"Modify\" permissions, this is a finding.\n\nThe default permissions below satisfy this requirement:\n\nTrustedInstaller - Full Control\nAdministrators, SYSTEM, Users, ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES, ALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; Execute","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the permissions on the \"Eventvwr.exe\" file to prevent modification by any groups or accounts other than TrustedInstaller. The default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement:\n\nTrustedInstaller - Full Control\nAdministrators, SYSTEM, Users, ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES, ALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; Execute\n\nThe default location is the \"%SystemRoot%\\System32\" folder.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000060","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Protecting audit information also includes identifying and protecting the tools used to view and manipulate log data. Therefore, protecting audit tools is necessary to prevent unauthorized operation on audit information.\n\nOperating systems providing tools to interface with audit information will leverage user permissions and roles identifying the user accessing the tools and the corresponding rights the user enjoys to make access decisions regarding the modification or deletion of audit tools.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000257-GPOS-00098, SRG-OS-000258-GPOS-00099","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Eventvwr.exe: Only Read and Execute rights for users other than TrustedInstaller)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Event Viewer must be protected from unauthorized modification and deletion.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001494","CCI-001495"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254299","title":"SRG-OS-000257-GPOS-00098"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254299","rule_id_src":"SV-254299r991558_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42C6C2-6E2B-1014-853B-8F55AFDEA49C","group_id_src":"V-254299","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254299r991558"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254300","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214","comments":null,"check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nAccount Logon &gt;&gt; Credential Validation - Success","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Account Logon &gt;&gt; Audit Credential Validation with \"Success\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000070","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nCredential Validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Credential Validation' is set to 'Success')\nTest            :     true ('Audit Credential Validation' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit Account Logon - Credential Validation successes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254300","title":"SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254300","rule_id_src":"SV-254300r991578_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42CA41-6E2B-1014-9718-EC4532975DA4","group_id_src":"V-254300","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254300r991578"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254301","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214","comments":null,"check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nAccount Logon &gt;&gt; Credential Validation - Failure","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Account Logon &gt;&gt; Audit Credential Validation with \"Failure\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000080","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nCredential Validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Credential Validation' is set to 'Failure')\nTest            :     true ('Audit Credential Validation' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit Account Logon - Credential Validation failures.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254301","title":"SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254301","rule_id_src":"SV-254301r991578_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42CDB7-6E2B-1014-A9B3-929B4AB2C646","group_id_src":"V-254301","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254301r991578"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254302","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","comments":null,"check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nAccount Management &gt;&gt; Other Account Management Events - Success","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Account Management &gt;&gt; Audit Other Account Management Events with \"Success\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000090","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nOther Account Management Events records events such as the access of a password hash or the Password Policy Checking API being called.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000064-GPOS-00033, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000466-GPOS-00210","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Audit - Other Account Management Events - 'Success only' or 'Success and Failure')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit Account Management - Other Account Management Events successes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254302","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254302","rule_id_src":"SV-254302r958732_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42D617-6E2B-1014-B23F-FFDD3D65A966","group_id_src":"V-254302","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254302r958732"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254303","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","comments":null,"check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nAccount Management &gt;&gt; Security Group Management - Success","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Account Management &gt;&gt;  Audit Security Group Management with \"Success\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000100","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSecurity Group Management records events such as creating, deleting, or changing security groups, including changes in group members.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004, SRG-OS-000239-GPOS-00089, SRG-OS-000240-GPOS-00090, SRG-OS-000241-GPOS-00091, SRG-OS-000303-GPOS-00120, SRG-OS-000476-GPOS-00221","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Audit Security Group Management' is set to 'Success' or 'Success and Failure')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit Account Management - Security Group Management successes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000018","CCI-000172","CCI-001403","CCI-001404","CCI-001405","CCI-002130"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254303","title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254303","rule_id_src":"SV-254303r958368_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A42E453-6E2B-1014-8CB7-C351684A745D","group_id_src":"V-254303","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254303r958368"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254304","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","comments":null,"check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nAccount Management &gt;&gt; User Account Management - Success","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Account Management &gt;&gt; Audit User Account Management with \"Success\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000110","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nUser Account Management records events such as creating, changing, deleting, renaming, disabling, or enabling user accounts.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004, SRG-OS-000239-GPOS-00089, SRG-OS-000240-GPOS-00090, SRG-OS-000241-GPOS-00091, SRG-OS-000303-GPOS-00120, SRG-OS-000476-GPOS-00221","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     fals