id":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Group Membership records information related to the group membership of a user's logon token.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings must be set to Enabled)\nTest            :   true (Logon/Logoff - Group Membership successes.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit Logon/Logoff - Group Membership successes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254310","title":"SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254310","rule_id_src":"SV-254310r991578_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4311DF-6E2B-1014-9671-8915AA8C34DD","group_id_src":"V-254310","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254310r991578"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254311","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000472-GPOS-00217","comments":null,"check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nLogon/Logoff &gt;&gt; Logoff - Success","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Logon/Logoff &gt;&gt; Audit Logoff with \"Success\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000180","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nLogoff records user logoffs. If this is an interactive logoff, it is recorded on the local system. If it is to a network share, it is recorded on the system accessed.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     true (Audit - Logoff - Success only)\nTest            :     false (Audit - Logoff - Success and Failure)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit logoff successes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254311","title":"SRG-OS-000472-GPOS-00217"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254311","rule_id_src":"SV-254311r991581_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A431593-6E2B-1014-962F-88D25F33233B","group_id_src":"V-254311","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254311r991581"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254312","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000032-GPOS-00013","comments":null,"check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nLogon/Logoff &gt;&gt; Logon - Success","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Logon/Logoff &gt;&gt; Audit Logon with \"Success\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000190","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nLogon records user logons. If this is an interactive logon, it is recorded on the local system. If it is to a network share, it is recorded on the system accessed.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000032-GPOS-00013, SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214, SRG-OS-000472-GPOS-00217, SRG-OS-000473-GPOS-00218, SRG-OS-000475-GPOS-00220","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Logon' is set to 'Success')\nTest            :     true ('Audit Logon' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit logon successes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000067","CCI-000172"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254312","title":"SRG-OS-000032-GPOS-00013"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254312","rule_id_src":"SV-254312r958406_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43193C-6E2B-1014-94E8-8236B8B57956","group_id_src":"V-254312","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254312r958406"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254313","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000032-GPOS-00013","comments":null,"check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nLogon/Logoff &gt;&gt; Logon - Failure","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Logon/Logoff &gt;&gt; Audit Logon with \"Failure\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000200","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nLogon records user logons. If this is an interactive logon, it is recorded on the local system. If it is to a network share, it is recorded on the system accessed.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000032-GPOS-00013, SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214, SRG-OS-000472-GPOS-00217, SRG-OS-000473-GPOS-00218, SRG-OS-000475-GPOS-00220","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Logon' is set to 'Failure')\nTest            :     true ('Audit Logon' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit logon failures.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000067","CCI-000172"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254313","title":"SRG-OS-000032-GPOS-00013"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254313","rule_id_src":"SV-254313r958406_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A431CEF-6E2B-1014-B553-A5D6B8F0663F","group_id_src":"V-254313","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254313r958406"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254314","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214","comments":null,"check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nLogon/Logoff &gt;&gt; Special Logon - Success","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Logon/Logoff &gt;&gt; Audit Special Logon with \"Success\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000210","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSpecial Logon records special logons that have administrative privileges and can be used to elevate processes.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214, SRG-OS-000472-GPOS-00217, SRG-OS-000473-GPOS-00218, SRG-OS-000475-GPOS-00220","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     true (Audit - Special Logon - Success only)\nTest            :     false (Audit - Special Logon - Success and Failure)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit Logon/Logoff - Special Logon successes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254314","title":"SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254314","rule_id_src":"SV-254314r991578_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4320A8-6E2B-1014-BAFC-E45BCAD76098","group_id_src":"V-254314","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254314r991578"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254315","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214","comments":null,"check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nObject Access &gt;&gt; Other Object Access Events - Success","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Object Access &gt;&gt; Audit Other Object Access Events with \"Success\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000220","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAuditing for other object access records events related to the management of task scheduler jobs and COM+ objects.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Other Object Access Events' is set to 'Success')\nTest            :     true ('Audit Other Object Access Events' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\n","docum