ll child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Audit - System Integrity - Success only)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit System - System Integrity successes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254331","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254331","rule_id_src":"SV-254331r958732_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A436593-6E2B-1014-9ACC-D2ED4BE74448","group_id_src":"V-254331","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254331r958732"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254332","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","comments":null,"check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nSystem &gt;&gt; System Integrity - Failure","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Audit System Integrity with \"Failure\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000390","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSystem Integrity records events related to violations of integrity to the security subsystem.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00216, SRG-OS-000477-GPOS-00222","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false (Audit - System Integrity - Failure only)\nTest            :     true (Audit - System Integrity - Success and Failure)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit System - System Integrity failures.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254332","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254332","rule_id_src":"SV-254332r958732_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A436E85-6E2B-1014-814C-957CE5F6638A","group_id_src":"V-254332","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254332r958732"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254333","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the registry value below. \n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Personalization\\\n\nValue Name: NoLockScreenSlideshow\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Control Panel &gt;&gt; Personalization &gt;&gt; Prevent enabling lock screen slide show to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000010","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Slide shows that are displayed on the lock screen could display sensitive information to unauthorized personnel. Turning off this feature will limit access to the information to a logged-on user.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Verifies 'Prevent enabling lock screen slide show' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent the display of slide shows on the lock screen.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254333","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254333","rule_id_src":"SV-254333r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43737D-6E2B-1014-94B3-B844793729DF","group_id_src":"V-254333","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254333r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254334","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\Wdigest\\\n\nValue Name:  UseLogonCredential\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; MS Security Guide . Set \"WDigest Authentication (disabling may require KB2871997)\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \" SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000020","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"When the WDigest Authentication protocol is enabled, plain-text passwords are stored in the Local Security Authority Subsystem Service (LSASS), exposing them to theft. WDigest is disabled by default in Windows Server 2022. This setting ensures this is enforced.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (WDigest Authentication is disabled)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have WDigest Authentication disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254334","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254334","rule_id_src":"SV-254334r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43775C-6E2B-1014-B576-E5E65D0E8F09","group_id_src":"V-254334","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254334r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254335","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip6\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisableIPSourceRouting\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)","severity":"low","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; MSS (Legacy) &gt;&gt; MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting IPv6) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing) to \"Enabled\" with \"Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\" selected.\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000030","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Configuring the system to disable IPv6 source routing protects against spoofing.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting IPv6) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing)' is set to 'Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Internet Protocol version 6 (IPv6) source routing must be configured to the highest protection level to prevent IP source routing.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254335","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254335","rule_id_src":"SV-254335r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A437B11-6E2B-1014-B338-F23B44E1AD30","group_id_src":"V-254335","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254335r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254336","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisableIPSourceRouting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)","severity":"low","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; MSS (Legacy) &gt;&gt; MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing) to \"Enabled\" with \"Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\" selected.\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000040","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Configuring the system to disable IP source routing protects against spoofing.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing)' is set to 'Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 source routing must be configured to the highest protection level to prevent Internet Protocol (IP) source routing.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254336","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254336","rule_id_src":"SV-254336r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A438056-6E2B-1014-8705-CCC12F12F21E","group_id_src":"V-254336","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254336r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254337","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: EnableICMPRedirect\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"low","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; MSS (Legacy) &gt;&gt; MSS: (EnableICMPRedirect) Allow ICMP redirects to override OSPF generated routes to \"Disabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000050","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Allowing ICMP redirect of routes can lead to traffic not being routed properly. When disabled, this forces ICMP to be routed via the shortest path first.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('MSS: (EnableICMPRedirect) Allow ICMP redirects to override OSPF generated routes' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to prevent Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) redirects from overriding Open Shortest Path First (OSPF)-generated routes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254337","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254337","rule_id_src":"SV-254337r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4384CF-6E2B-1014-9CD4-8978B0079EFC","group_id_src":"V-254337","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254337r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254338","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netbt\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  NoNameReleaseOnDemand\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","severity":"low","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; MSS (Legacy) &gt;&gt; MSS: (NoNameReleaseOnDemand) Allow the computer to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers to \"Enabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000060","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Configuring the system to ignore name release requests, except from WINS servers, prevents a denial of service (DoS) attack. The DoS consists of sending a NetBIOS name release request to the server for each entry in the server's cache, causing a response delay in the normal operation of the server's WINS resolution capability.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('MSS: (NoNameReleaseOnDemand) Allow computer to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002385"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254338","title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254338","rule_id_src":"SV-254338r958902_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A438882-6E2B-1014-BE76-C63C184E446E","group_id_src":"V-254338","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254338r958902"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254339","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\LanmanWorkstation\\\n\nValue Name: AllowInsecureGuestAuth\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Network &gt;&gt; Lanman Workstation &gt;&gt; Enable insecure guest logons to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000070","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Insecure guest logons allow unauthenticated access to shared folders. Shared resources on a system must require authentication to establish proper access.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Enable insecure guest logons' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 insecure logons to an SMB server must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254339","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254339","rule_id_src":"SV-254339r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A438C0E-6E2B-1014-AC54-B170BA8EF384","group_id_src":"V-254339","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254339r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254340","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems. For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\NetworkProvider\\HardenedPaths\\\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\NETLOGON\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\SYSVOL\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nAdditional entries would not be a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Network &gt;&gt; Network Provider &gt;&gt; Hardened UNC Paths\" to \"Enabled\" with at least the following configured in \"Hardened UNC Paths\" (click the \"Show\" button to display):\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\SYSVOL\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\NETLOGON\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000080","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Additional security requirements are applied to UNC paths specified in hardened UNC paths before allowing access to them. This aids in preventing tampering with or spoofing of connections to these paths.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 hardened Universal Naming Convention (UNC) paths must be defined to require mutual authentication and integrity for at least the \\\\*\\SYSVOL and \\\\*\\NETLOGON shares.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254340","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254340","rule_id_src":"SV-254340r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A438FA1-6E2B-1014-B69A-D74E359690AB","group_id_src":"V-254340","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254340r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254341","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Audit\\\n\nValue Name: ProcessCreationIncludeCmdLine_Enabled\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Audit Process Creation &gt;&gt; Include command line in process creation events to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000090","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling \"Include command line data for process creation events\" will record the command line information with the process creation events in the log. This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Include command line in process creation events' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 command line data must be included in process creation events.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000135"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254341","title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254341","rule_id_src":"SV-254341r958422_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A439335-6E2B-1014-B797-F808D7773A77","group_id_src":"V-254341","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254341r958422"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254342","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CredentialsDelegation\\\n\nValue Name: AllowProtectedCreds\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Credentials Delegation &gt;&gt; Remote host allows delegation of nonexportable credentials to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000100","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"An exportable version of credentials is provided to remote hosts when using credential delegation which exposes them to theft on the remote host. Restricted Admin mode or Remote Credential Guard allow delegation of nonexportable credentials providing additional protection of the credentials. Enabling this configures the host to support Restricted Admin mode or Remote Credential Guard.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Remote host allows delegation of non-exportable credentials' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to enable Remote host allows delegation of nonexportable credentials.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254342","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254342","rule_id_src":"SV-254342r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4396A2-6E2B-1014-82E3-F0F08B03204A","group_id_src":"V-254342","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254342r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254343","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter the following:\n\n\"Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_DeviceGuard -Namespace root\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\"\n\nIf \"RequiredSecurityProperties\" does not include a value of \"2\" indicating \"Secure Boot\" (e.g., \"{1, 2}\"), this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" is configured, \"3\" will also be displayed in the results (e.g., \"{1, 2, 3}\").\n\nIf \"VirtualizationBasedSecurityStatus\" is not a value of \"2\" indicating \"Running\", this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", verify the following:\n\nIf \"Device Guard Virtualization based security\" does not display \"Running\", this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Device Guard Required Security Properties\" does not display \"Base Virtualization Support, Secure Boot\", this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" is configured, \"DMA Protection\" will also be displayed (e.g., \"Base Virtualization Support, Secure Boot, DMA Protection\").\n\nThe policy settings referenced in the Fix section will configure the following registry values; however, due to hardware requirements, the registry values alone do not ensure proper function.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\\\n\nValue Name: EnableVirtualizationBasedSecurity\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nValue Name: RequirePlatformSecurityFeatures\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) (Secure Boot only) or 0x00000003 (3) (Secure Boot and DMA Protection)\n\nA Microsoft TechNet article on Credential Guard, including system requirement details, can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/keep-secure/credential-guard","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Device Guard &gt;&gt; Turn On Virtualization Based Security to \"Enabled\" with \"Secure Boot\" or \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" selected.\n\nA Microsoft TechNet article on Credential Guard, including system requirement details, can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/keep-secure/credential-guard","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000110","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Virtualization Based Security (VBS) provides the platform for the additional security features Credential Guard and virtualization-based protection of code integrity. Secure Boot is the minimum security level, with DMA protection providing additional memory protection. DMA Protection requires a CPU that supports input/output memory management unit (IOMMU).","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 virtualization-based security must be enabled with the platform security level configured to Secure Boot or Secure Boot with DMA Protection.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254343","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254343","rule_id_src":"SV-254343r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A439A46-6E2B-1014-AD2B-EC0CD4AAF0EA","group_id_src":"V-254343","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254343r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254344","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"The default behavior is for Early Launch Antimalware - Boot-Start Driver Initialization policy to enforce \"Good, unknown and bad but critical\" (preventing \"bad\").\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0x00000007 (7)\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Policies\\EarlyLaunch\\\n\nValue Name: DriverLoadPolicy\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1), 0x00000003 (3), or 0x00000008 (8) (or if the Value Name does not exist)\n\nPossible values for this setting are:\n8 - Good only\n1 - Good and unknown\n3 - Good, unknown and bad but critical\n7 - All (which includes \"bad\" and would be a finding)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Early Launch Antimalware - Boot-Start Driver Initialization policy to enforce \"Good, unknown and bad but critical\" (preventing \"bad\").\n\nIf this needs to be corrected or a more secure setting is desired, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Early Launch Antimalware &gt;&gt; Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy to \"Not Configured\" or \"Enabled\" with any option other than \"All\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000130","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Compromised boot drivers can introduce malware prior to protection mechanisms that load after initialization. The Early Launch Antimalware driver can limit allowed drivers based on classifications determined by the malware protection application. At a minimum, drivers determined to be bad must not be allowed.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy' is not set to 'Enabled' with 'All' selected)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Early Launch Antimalware, Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy must prevent boot drivers identified as bad.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254344","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254344","rule_id_src":"SV-254344r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A439DBC-6E2B-1014-A4FB-BBD9B01D0C8B","group_id_src":"V-254344","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254344r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254345","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"This is not applicable for Domain Controllers.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Group Policy\\{35378EAC-683F-11D2-A89A-00C04FBBCFA2}\\\n\nValue Name: NoGPOListChanges\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Group Policy &gt;&gt; Configure registry policy processing to \"Enabled\" with the option \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000140","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Registry entries for group policy settings can potentially be changed from the required configuration. This could occur as part of troubleshooting or by a malicious process on a compromised system. Enabling this setting and then selecting the \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\" option ensures the policies will be reprocessed even if none have been changed. This way, any unauthorized changes are forced to match the domain-based group policy settings again.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (NoGPOistChanges is set to 0.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 group policy objects must be reprocessed even if they have not changed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254345","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254345","rule_id_src":"SV-254345r1135378_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43A13D-6E2B-1014-8802-CE8B9B6D6ADA","group_id_src":"V-254345","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254345r1135378"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254346","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\\\n\nValue Name: DisableWebPnPDownload\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Internet Communication Management &gt;&gt; Internet Communication settings &gt;&gt; Turn off downloading of print drivers over HTTP to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000150","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and will prevent uncontrolled updates to the system. \n\nThis setting prevents the computer from downloading print driver packages over HTTP.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Turn off downloading of print drivers over HTTP' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 downloading print driver packages over HTTP must be turned off.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254346","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254346","rule_id_src":"SV-254346r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43A4A8-6E2B-1014-B43C-8461BEBE9C9A","group_id_src":"V-254346","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254346r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254347","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\\\n\nValue Name: DisableHTTPPrinting\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Internet Communication Management &gt;&gt; Internet Communication settings &gt;&gt; Turn off printing over HTTP to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000160","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and will prevent uncontrolled updates to the system.\n\nThis setting prevents the client computer from printing over HTTP, which allows the computer to print to printers on the intranet as well as the internet.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Turn off printing over HTTP' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 printing over HTTP must be turned off.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254347","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254347","rule_id_src":"SV-254347r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43A80E-6E2B-1014-918F-B73417F976C9","group_id_src":"V-254347","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254347r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254348","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the registry value below. If it does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: DontDisplayNetworkSelectionUI\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Logon &gt;&gt; Do not display network selection UI to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000170","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Enabling interaction with the network selection UI allows users to change connections to available networks without signing in to Windows.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Verifies 'Do not display network selection UI' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 network selection user interface (UI) must not be displayed on the logon screen.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254348","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254348","rule_id_src":"SV-254348r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43AB6E-6E2B-1014-ADC4-DD89271C1D88","group_id_src":"V-254348","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254348r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254349","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Power\\PowerSettings\\0e796bdb-100d-47d6-a2d5-f7d2daa51f51\\\n\nValue Name: DCSettingIndex\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Power Management &gt;&gt; Sleep Settings &gt;&gt; Require a password when a computer wakes (on battery) to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000180","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"A system that does not require authentication when resuming from sleep may provide access to unauthorized users. Authentication must always be required when accessing a system. This setting ensures users are prompted for a password when the system wakes from sleep (on battery).","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Require a password when a computer wakes (on battery)' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 users must be prompted to authenticate when the system wakes from sleep (on battery).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254349","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254349","rule_id_src":"SV-254349r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43AEE0-6E2B-1014-AE0A-B30FE148D4DA","group_id_src":"V-254349","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254349r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254350","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Power\\PowerSettings\\0e796bdb-100d-47d6-a2d5-f7d2daa51f51\\\n\nValue Name: ACSettingIndex\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Power Management &gt;&gt; Sleep Settings &gt;&gt; Require a password when a computer wakes (plugged in) to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000190","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"A system that does not require authentication when resuming from sleep may provide access to unauthorized users. Authentication must always be required when accessing a system. This setting ensures users are prompted for a password when the system wakes from sleep (plugged in).","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Require a password when a computer wakes (plugged in)' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 users must be prompted to authenticate when the system wakes from sleep (plugged in).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254350","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254350","rule_id_src":"SV-254350r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43B248-6E2B-1014-9A34-A77699D0C3B1","group_id_src":"V-254350","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254350r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254351","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppCompat\\\n\nValue Name: DisableInventory\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"low","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Application Compatibility &gt;&gt; Turn off Inventory Collector to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000200","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and will prevent uncontrolled updates to the system.\n\nThis setting will prevent the Program Inventory from collecting data about a system and sending the information to Microsoft.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Turn off Inventory Collector' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Application Compatibility Program Inventory must be prevented from collecting data and sending the information to Microsoft.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254351","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254351","rule_id_src":"SV-254351r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43B5A1-6E2B-1014-8BB7-CDD0DF77A020","group_id_src":"V-254351","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254351r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254352","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoAutoplayfornonVolume\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; AutoPlay Policies &gt;&gt; Disallow Autoplay for nonvolume devices to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000210","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Allowing AutoPlay to execute may introduce malicious code to a system. AutoPlay begins reading from a drive as soon as media is inserted into the drive. As a result, the setup file of programs or music on audio media may start. This setting will disable AutoPlay for nonvolume devices, such as Media Transfer Protocol (MTP) devices.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Disallow Autoplay for non-volume devices' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Autoplay must be turned off for nonvolume devices.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001764"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254352","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254352","rule_id_src":"SV-254352r958804_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43B90D-6E2B-1014-9E5A-F4327DA8648A","group_id_src":"V-254352","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254352r958804"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254353","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoAutorun\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; AutoPlay Policies &gt;&gt; Set the default behavior for AutoRun to \"Enabled\" with \"Do not execute any autorun commands\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000220","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Allowing AutoRun commands to execute may introduce malicious code to a system. Configuring this setting prevents AutoRun commands from executing.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Default behavior for AutoRun' is set to 'Enabled' with 'Do not execute any autorun commands' selected)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 default AutoRun behavior must be configured to prevent AutoRun commands.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001764"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254353","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254353","rule_id_src":"SV-254353r958804_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43BC51-6E2B-1014-9557-CC6F437DFD1D","group_id_src":"V-254353","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254353r958804"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254354","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoDriveTypeAutoRun\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x000000ff (255)","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; AutoPlay Policies &gt;&gt; Turn off AutoPlay to \"Enabled\" with \"All Drives\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000230","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Allowing AutoPlay to execute may introduce malicious code to a system. AutoPlay begins reading from a drive as soon media is inserted into the drive. As a result, the setup file of programs or music on audio media may start. By default, AutoPlay is disabled on removable drives, such as the floppy disk drive (but not the CD-ROM drive) and on network drives. Enabling this policy disables AutoPlay on all drives.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Turn off AutoPlay' is set to 'Enabled:All Drives')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 AutoPlay must be disabled for all drives.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001764"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254354","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254354","rule_id_src":"SV-254354r958804_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43BFB0-6E2B-1014-B662-DE54390E14E5","group_id_src":"V-254354","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254354r958804"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254355","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\CredUI\\\n\nValue Name: EnumerateAdministrators\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Credential User Interface &gt;&gt; Enumerate administrator accounts on elevation to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000240","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Enumeration of administrator accounts when elevating can provide part of the logon information to an unauthorized user. This setting configures the system to always require users to type in a username and password to elevate a running application.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Enumerate administrator accounts on elevation' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 administrator accounts must not be enumerated during elevation.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254355","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254355","rule_id_src":"SV-254355r958518_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43C3EE-6E2B-1014-892D-A0418FB38995","group_id_src":"V-254355","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254355r958518"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254356","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DataCollection\\\n\nValue Name: AllowTelemetry\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1), 0x00000003 (3)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Data Collection and Preview Build &gt;&gt; Allow Diagnostic Data to \"Enabled\" with \"Send required diagnostic data\" selected or \"Send optional diagnostic data\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000250","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Limiting this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise. The \"send required diagnostic data\" option for Allow Diagnostic Data configures the lowest amount of data, effectively none outside of the Malicious Software Removal Tool (MSRT), Defender, and Diagnostic Data client settings. \"Optional Diagnostic Data\" sends basic diagnostic and usage data and may be required to support some Microsoft services.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Allow Diagnostic Data' is set to 'Enabled' with 'Send Required Diagnostic Data' or 'Send Optional Diagnostic Data' selected in 'Options:')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Diagnostic Data must be configured to send \"required diagnostic data\" or \"optional diagnostic data\".","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254356","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254356","rule_id_src":"SV-254356r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43C7A0-6E2B-1014-9737-AD1FFF0EBC54","group_id_src":"V-254356","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254356r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254357","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeliveryOptimization\\\n\nValue Name: DODownloadMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) - No peering (HTTP Only)\n0x00000001 (1) - Peers on same NAT only (LAN)\n0x00000002 (2) - Local Network / Private group peering (Group)\n0x00000063 (99) - Simple download mode, no peering (Simple)\n\nA value of 0x00000003 (3), Internet, is a finding.","severity":"low","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Delivery Optimization &gt;&gt; Download Mode to \"Enabled\" with any option except \"Internet\" selected.\n\nAcceptable selections include:\n\nHTTP only (0)\nLAN (1)\nGroup (2)\nInternet (3)\nSimple (99)","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000260","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Windows Update can obtain updates from additional sources instead of Microsoft. In addition to Microsoft, updates can be obtained from and sent to PCs on the local network as well as on the internet. This is part of the Windows Update trusted process; however, to minimize outside exposure, obtaining updates from or sending to systems on the internet must be prevented.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('DownloadMode' is set to 'Enabled' with 'HTTP only, LAN, Group, Simple or Bypass' selected.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Windows Update must not obtain updates from other PCs on the internet.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254357","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254357","rule_id_src":"SV-254357r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43CB3F-6E2B-1014-A148-FE9CF4C64978","group_id_src":"V-254357","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254357r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254358","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","comments":null,"check_content":"If the system is configured to write events directly to an audit server, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\Application\\\n\nValue Name: MaxSize\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00008000 (32768) (or greater)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Event Log Service &gt;&gt; Application &gt;&gt; Specify the maximum log file size (KB) to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"32768\" or greater.","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000270","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly. This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The Application event log size is configured to 32768 KB or greater)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Application event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001849"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254358","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254358","rule_id_src":"SV-254358r958752_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43CEA2-6E2B-1014-903A-B5F3911C37C7","group_id_src":"V-254358","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254358r958752"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254359","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","comments":null,"check_content":"If the system is configured to write events directly to an audit server, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\Security\\\n\nValue Name: MaxSize\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00030000 (196608) (or greater)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Event Log Service &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Specify the maximum log file size (KB) to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"196608\" or greater.","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000280","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly. This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The Security event log size is configured to 196608 KB or greater)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Security event log size must be configured to 196608 KB or greater.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001849"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254359","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254359","rule_id_src":"SV-254359r958752_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43D1F8-6E2B-1014-9EE8-C5BD25CD56DE","group_id_src":"V-254359","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254359r958752"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254360","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","comments":null,"check_content":"If the system is configured to write events directly to an audit server, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\System\\\n\nValue Name: MaxSize\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00008000 (32768) (or greater)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Event Log Service &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Specify the maximum log file size (KB) to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"32768\" or greater.","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000290","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly. This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The System event log size is configured to 32768 KB or greater)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 System event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001849"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254360","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254360","rule_id_src":"SV-254360r958752_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43D73D-6E2B-1014-9782-8C62DAABC93D","group_id_src":"V-254360","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254360r958752"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254361","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems; for other systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSmartScreen\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; File Explorer &gt;&gt; Configure Windows Defender SmartScreen to \"Enabled\" with either option \"Warn\" or \"Warn and prevent bypass\" selected.\n\nWindows Server 2022 includes duplicate policies for this setting. It can also be configured under Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Defender SmartScreen &gt;&gt; Explorer.","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000300","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Microsoft Defender antivirus SmartScreen helps protect systems from programs downloaded from the internet that may be malicious. Enabling SmartScreen can block potentially malicious programs or warn users.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Configure Windows SmartScreen' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Microsoft Defender antivirus SmartScreen must be enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254361","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254361","rule_id_src":"SV-254361r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43DAD2-6E2B-1014-9A37-DF0BEC295F03","group_id_src":"V-254361","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254361r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254362","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","comments":null,"check_content":"The default behavior is for Data Execution Prevention to be turned on for File Explorer.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoDataExecutionPrevention\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"The default behavior is for data execution prevention to be turned on for File Explorer.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; File Explorer &gt;&gt; Turn off Data Execution Prevention for Explorer to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000310","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Data Execution Prevention provides additional protection by performing checks on memory to help prevent malicious code from running. This setting will prevent Data Execution Prevention from being turned off for File Explorer.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Turn off Data Execution Prevention for Explorer' is set to 'Disabled' or 'Not Configured')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Explorer Data Execution Prevention must be enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002824"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254362","title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254362","rule_id_src":"SV-254362r958928_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43DE3A-6E2B-1014-BD3C-C2B2D6604841","group_id_src":"V-254362","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254362r958928"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254363","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"The default behavior is for File Explorer heap termination on corruption to be enabled.\n\nIf the registry Value Name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoHeapTerminationOnCorruption\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","severity":"low","fix_text":"The default behavior is for File Explorer heap termination on corruption to be disabled.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; File Explorer &gt;&gt; Turn off heap termination on corruption to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000320","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Legacy plug-in applications may continue to function when a File Explorer session has become corrupt. Disabling this feature will prevent this.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Turn off heap termination on corruption' is set to 'Not Configured' or 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Turning off File Explorer heap termination on corruption must be disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254363","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254363","rule_id_src":"SV-254363r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43E190-6E2B-1014-80B4-C9DFA2783C91","group_id_src":"V-254363","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254363r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254364","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"The default behavior is for shell protected mode to be turned on for File Explorer.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: PreXPSP2ShellProtocolBehavior\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"The default behavior is for shell protected mode to be turned on for File Explorer.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; File Explorer &gt;&gt; Turn off shell protocol protected mode to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000330","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The shell protocol will limit the set of folders that applications can open when run in protected mode. Restricting files an application can open to a limited set of folders increases the security of Windows.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Turn off shell protocol protected mode' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 File Explorer shell protocol must run in protected mode.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254364","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254364","rule_id_src":"SV-254364r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43E4F9-6E2B-1014-A6E3-B362BDF95805","group_id_src":"V-254364","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254364r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254365","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: DisablePasswordSaving\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Remote Desktop Services &gt;&gt; Remote Desktop Connection Client &gt;&gt; Do not allow passwords to be saved to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000340","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Saving passwords in the Remote Desktop Client could allow an unauthorized user to establish a remote desktop session to another system. The system must be configured to prevent users from saving passwords in the Remote Desktop Client.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156, SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Do not allow passwords to be saved' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must not save passwords in the Remote Desktop Client.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002038"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254365","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254365","rule_id_src":"SV-254365r1051096_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43E83D-6E2B-1014-BFFE-EEE40E00E39F","group_id_src":"V-254365","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254365r1051096"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254366","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fDisableCdm\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Remote Desktop Services &gt;&gt; Remote Desktop Session Host &gt;&gt; Device and Resource Redirection &gt;&gt; Do not allow drive redirection to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000350","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Preventing users from sharing the local drives on their client computers with Remote Session Hosts that they access helps reduce possible exposure of sensitive data.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Do not allow drive redirection' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must prevent drive redirection.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001090"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254366","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254366","rule_id_src":"SV-254366r1137695_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43EB87-6E2B-1014-B96B-DD90FB999CC8","group_id_src":"V-254366","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254366r1137695"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254367","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fPromptForPassword\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Remote Desktop Services &gt;&gt; Remote Desktop Session Host &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Always prompt for password upon connection to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000360","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting controls the ability of users to supply passwords automatically as part of their remote desktop connection. Disabling this setting would allow anyone to use the stored credentials in a connection item to connect to the terminal server.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156, SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Always prompt for password upon connection' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must always prompt a client for passwords upon connection.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002038"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254367","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254367","rule_id_src":"SV-254367r1051097_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43EEE1-6E2B-1014-87DB-98B14515C2BA","group_id_src":"V-254367","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254367r1051097"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254368","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fEncryptRPCTraffic\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Remote Desktop Services &gt;&gt; Remote Desktop Session Host &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Require secure RPC communication to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000370","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Allowing unsecure RPC communication exposes the system to man-in-the-middle attacks and data disclosure attacks. A man-in-the-middle attack occurs when an intruder captures packets between a client and server and modifies them before allowing the packets to be exchanged. Usually the attacker will modify the information in the packets in an attempt to cause either the client or server to reveal sensitive information.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014, SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Require secure RPC communication' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must require secure Remote Procedure Call (RPC) communications.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000068","CCI-001453"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254368","title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254368","rule_id_src":"SV-254368r958408_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43F26A-6E2B-1014-9195-9ED20D819472","group_id_src":"V-254368","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254368r958408"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254369","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: MinEncryptionLevel\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000003 (3)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Remote Desktop Services &gt;&gt; Remote Desktop Session Host &gt;&gt; Security &gt;&gt; Set client connection encryption level to \"Enabled\" with \"High Level\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000380","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Remote connections must be encrypted to prevent interception of data or sensitive information. Selecting \"High Level\" will ensure encryption of Remote Desktop Services sessions in both directions.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014, SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Set client connection encryption level' is set to 'Enabled' and 'High Level')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must be configured with the client connection encryption set to High Level.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000068","CCI-001453"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254369","title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254369","rule_id_src":"SV-254369r958408_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43F612-6E2B-1014-A5B9-D66883B013D4","group_id_src":"V-254369","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254369r958408"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254370","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: DisableEnclosureDownload\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; RSS Feeds &gt;&gt; Prevent downloading of enclosures to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000390","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Attachments from RSS feeds may not be secure. This setting will prevent attachments from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Prevent downloading of enclosures' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent attachments from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254370","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254370","rule_id_src":"SV-254370r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43F9AF-6E2B-1014-A401-BB8EC431CD0B","group_id_src":"V-254370","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254370r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254371","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"The default behavior is for the Windows RSS platform to not use Basic authentication over HTTP connections.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasicAuthInClear\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"The default behavior is for the Windows RSS platform to not use Basic authentication over HTTP connections.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; RSS Feeds &gt;&gt; Turn on Basic feed authentication over HTTP to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000400","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain-text passwords that could be used to compromise a system. Disabling Basic authentication will reduce this potential.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Turn on Basic feed authentication over HTTP' is set to 'Not Configured' or 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must disable Basic authentication for RSS feeds over HTTP.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254371","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254371","rule_id_src":"SV-254371r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A43FD3E-6E2B-1014-8CFE-89057BAD2DA5","group_id_src":"V-254371","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254371r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254372","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Windows Search\\\n\nValue Name: AllowIndexingEncryptedStoresOrItems\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Search &gt;&gt; Allow indexing of encrypted files to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000410","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Indexing of encrypted files may expose sensitive data. This setting prevents encrypted files from being indexed.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Allow indexing of encrypted files' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent Indexing of encrypted files.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254372","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254372","rule_id_src":"SV-254372r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4400EF-6E2B-1014-AABD-C1A834929C0B","group_id_src":"V-254372","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254372r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254373","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: EnableUserControl\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Installer &gt;&gt; Allow user control over installs to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000420","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Installation options for applications are typically controlled by administrators. This setting prevents users from changing installation options that may bypass security features.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Allow user control over installs' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent users from changing installation options.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-003980","CCI-001812"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254373","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254373","rule_id_src":"SV-254373r1051098_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A440479-6E2B-1014-BACE-FC77E5AA684C","group_id_src":"V-254373","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254373r1051098"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254374","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: AlwaysInstallElevated\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Installer &gt;&gt; Always install with elevated privileges to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000430","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Standard user accounts must not be granted elevated privileges. Enabling Windows Installer to elevate privileges when installing applications can allow malicious persons and applications to gain full control of a system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Always install with elevated privileges' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must disable the Windows Installer Always install with elevated privileges option.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-003980","CCI-001812"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254374","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254374","rule_id_src":"SV-254374r1051099_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A44081C-6E2B-1014-B461-D110564E81E9","group_id_src":"V-254374","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254374r1051099"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254375","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"The default behavior is for Internet Explorer to warn users and select whether to allow or refuse installation when a web-based program attempts to install software on the system.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: SafeForScripting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Internet Explorer to warn users and select whether to allow or refuse installation when a web-based program attempts to install software on the system.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Installer &gt;&gt; Prevent Internet Explorer security prompt for Windows Installer scripts to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000440","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Web-based programs may attempt to install malicious software on a system. Ensuring users are notified if a web-based program attempts to install software allows them to refuse the installation.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Prevent Internet Explorer security prompt for Windows Installer scripts' is set to 'Not Configured' or 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 users must be notified if a web-based program attempts to install software.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254375","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254375","rule_id_src":"SV-254375r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A440BBE-6E2B-1014-9944-A44307DDF263","group_id_src":"V-254375","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254375r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254376","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00229","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the registry value below. If it does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: DisableAutomaticRestartSignOn\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Logon Options &gt;&gt; Sign-in and lock last interactive user automatically after a restart to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000450","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Windows can be configured to automatically sign the user back in after a Windows Update restart. Some protections are in place to help ensure this is done in a secure fashion; however, disabling this will prevent the caching of credentials for this purpose and also ensure the user is aware of the restart.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Verifies 'Sign-in last interactive user automatically after a system-initiated restart' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must disable automatically signing in the last interactive user after a system-initiated restart.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254376","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00229"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254376","rule_id_src":"SV-254376r991591_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A440F60-6E2B-1014-88FA-E0EBD1B57EE6","group_id_src":"V-254376","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254376r991591"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254377","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\ScriptBlockLogging\\\n\nValue Name: EnableScriptBlockLogging\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows PowerShell &gt;&gt; Turn on PowerShell Script Block Logging to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000460","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling PowerShell script block logging will record detailed information from the processing of PowerShell commands and scripts. This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Turn on PowerShell Script Block Logging' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 PowerShell script block logging must be enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000135"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254377","title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254377","rule_id_src":"SV-254377r958422_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A44147A-6E2B-1014-A52B-CC8E4A590B0A","group_id_src":"V-254377","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254377r958422"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254378","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasic\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Remote Management (WinRM) &gt;&gt; WinRM Client &gt;&gt; Allow Basic authentication to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000470","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain-text passwords that could be used to compromise a system. Disabling Basic authentication will reduce this potential.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Allow Basic authentication' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Basic authentication.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000877"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254378","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254378","rule_id_src":"SV-254378r958510_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4417FE-6E2B-1014-BB4D-C3349720B7A8","group_id_src":"V-254378","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254378r958510"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254379","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\\\n\nValue Name: AllowUnencryptedTraffic\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Remote Management (WinRM) &gt;&gt; WinRM Client &gt;&gt; Allow unencrypted traffic to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000480","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Unencrypted remote access to a system can allow sensitive information to be compromised. Windows remote management connections must be encrypted to prevent this.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173, SRG-OS-000394-GPOS-00174","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Allow unencrypted traffic' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not allow unencrypted traffic.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002890","CCI-003123"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254379","title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254379","rule_id_src":"SV-254379r958848_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A441B9F-6E2B-1014-B2B7-F01CDF90E513","group_id_src":"V-254379","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254379r958848"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254380","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\\\n\nValue Name: AllowDigest\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Remote Management (WinRM) &gt;&gt; WinRM Client &gt;&gt; Disallow Digest authentication to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000490","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Digest authentication is not as strong as other options and may be subject to man-in-the-middle attacks. Disallowing Digest authentication will reduce this potential.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Disallow Digest authentication' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Digest authentication.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000877"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254380","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254380","rule_id_src":"SV-254380r958510_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A441F17-6E2B-1014-B13D-DE73E309CF2A","group_id_src":"V-254380","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254380r958510"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254381","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasic\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Remote Management (WinRM) &gt;&gt; WinRM Service &gt;&gt; Allow Basic authentication to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000500","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain-text passwords that could be used to compromise a system. Disabling Basic authentication will reduce this potential.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Allow Basic authentication' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not use Basic authentication.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000877"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254381","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254381","rule_id_src":"SV-254381r958510_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4423EC-6E2B-1014-90CF-E9A73321C2E2","group_id_src":"V-254381","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254381r958510"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254382","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\\\n\nValue Name: AllowUnencryptedTraffic\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Remote Management (WinRM) &gt;&gt; WinRM Service &gt;&gt; Allow unencrypted traffic to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000510","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Unencrypted remote access to a system can allow sensitive information to be compromised. Windows remote management connections must be encrypted to prevent this.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173, SRG-OS-000394-GPOS-00174","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Allow unencrypted traffic' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not allow unencrypted traffic.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002890","CCI-003123"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254382","title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254382","rule_id_src":"SV-254382r958848_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A442AD5-6E2B-1014-8459-AAC86A7DAF36","group_id_src":"V-254382","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254382r958848"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254383","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\\\n\nValue Name: DisableRunAs\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows Remote Management (WinRM) &gt;&gt; WinRM Service &gt;&gt; Disallow WinRM from storing RunAs credentials to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000520","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Storage of administrative credentials could allow unauthorized access. Disallowing the storage of RunAs credentials for Windows Remote Management will prevent them from being used with plug-ins.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156, SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Disallow WinRM from storing RunAs credentials' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not store RunAs credentials.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002038"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254383","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254383","rule_id_src":"SV-254383r1051100_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A442F08-6E2B-1014-87EA-CCA096D45F09","group_id_src":"V-254383","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254383r1051100"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254384","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000041-GPOS-00019","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\Transcription\\\n\nValue Name: EnableTranscripting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Windows PowerShell &gt;&gt; \"Turn on PowerShell Transcription\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nSpecify the Transcript output directory to point to a Central Log Server or another secure location to prevent user access.","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000530","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling PowerShell Transcription will record detailed information from the processing of PowerShell commands and scripts. This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (PowerShell Transcription is enabled on Windows 11)\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\Transcription\\EnableTranscripting'.  Existence requirement is 'all_exist' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have PowerShell Transcription enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000134"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254384","title":"SRG-OS-000041-GPOS-00019"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254384","rule_id_src":"SV-254384r958420_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A44389F-6E2B-1014-A3DB-C99362F861C6","group_id_src":"V-254384","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254384r958420"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:29301","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. A separate version applies to other systems.\n\nReview the Administrators group. Only the appropriate administrator groups or accounts responsible for administration of the system may be members of the group.\n\nStandard user accounts must not be members of the local administrator group.\n\nIf prohibited accounts are members of the local administrators group, this is a finding.\n\nIf the built-in Administrator account or other required administrative accounts are found on the system, this is not a finding.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the Administrators group to include only administrator groups or accounts that are responsible for the system.\n\nRemove any standard user accounts.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000010","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"An account that does not have Administrator duties must not have Administrator rights. Such rights would allow the account to bypass or modify required security restrictions on that machine and make it vulnerable to attack.\n\nSystem administrators must log on to systems using only accounts with the minimum level of authority necessary. \n\nStandard user accounts must not be members of the built-in Administrators group.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must only allow administrators responsible for the domain controller to have Administrator rights on the system.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254385","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254385","rule_id_src":"SV-254385r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A444328-6E2B-1014-988C-87FC8BD9C3A2","group_id_src":"V-254385","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254385r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254386","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nVerify the following is configured in the Default Domain Policy:\n\nOpen \"Group Policy Management\".\n\nNavigate to \"Group Policy Objects\" in the Domain being reviewed (Forest &gt;&gt; Domains &gt;&gt; Domain). \n\nRight-click on the \"Default Domain Policy\".\n\nSelect \"Edit\".\n\nNavigate to Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Policies &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Kerberos Policy.\n\nIf the \"Enforce user logon restrictions\" is not set to \"Enabled\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value in the Default Domain Policy for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Policies &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Kerberos Policy &gt;&gt; Enforce user logon restrictions to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000020","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether the Kerberos Key Distribution Center (KDC) validates every request for a session ticket against the user rights policy of the target computer. The policy is enabled by default, which is the most secure setting for validating that access to target resources is not circumvented.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057, SRG-OS-000113-GPOS-00058","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Kerberos user logon restrictions must be enforced.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001941","CCI-001942"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254386","title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254386","rule_id_src":"SV-254386r1051101_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4492F0-6E2B-1014-AB9F-EBA6D2497A28","group_id_src":"V-254386","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254386r1051101"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254387","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nVerify the following is configured in the Default Domain Policy:\n\nOpen \"Group Policy Management\".\n\nNavigate to \"Group Policy Objects\" in the Domain being reviewed (Forest &gt;&gt; Domains &gt;&gt; Domain). \n\nRight-click on the \"Default Domain Policy\".\n\nSelect \"Edit\".\n\nNavigate to Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Policies &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Kerberos Policy.\n\nIf the value for \"Maximum lifetime for service ticket\" is \"0\" or greater than \"600\" minutes, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value in the Default Domain Policy for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Policies &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Kerberos Policy &gt;&gt; Maximum lifetime for service ticket to a maximum of \"600\" minutes, but not \"0\", which equates to \"Ticket doesn't expire\".","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000030","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting determines the maximum amount of time (in minutes) that a granted session ticket can be used to access a particular service. Session tickets are used only to authenticate new connections with servers. Ongoing operations are not interrupted if the session ticket used to authenticate the connection expires during the connection.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057, SRG-OS-000113-GPOS-00058","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Kerberos service ticket maximum lifetime must be limited to 600 minutes or less.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001941","CCI-001942"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254387","title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254387","rule_id_src":"SV-254387r1051102_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A449A45-6E2B-1014-BEDF-FFE616F0D3D6","group_id_src":"V-254387","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254387r1051102"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254388","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nVerify the following is configured in the Default Domain Policy:\n\nOpen \"Group Policy Management\".\n\nNavigate to \"Group Policy Objects\" in the Domain being reviewed (Forest &gt;&gt; Domains &gt;&gt; Domain).\n\nRight-click on the \"Default Domain Policy\".\n\nSelect \"Edit\".\n\nNavigate to Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Policies &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Kerberos Policy.\n\nIf the value for \"Maximum lifetime for user ticket\" is \"0\" or greater than \"10\" hours, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value in the Default Domain Policy for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Policies &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Kerberos Policy &gt;&gt; Maximum lifetime for user ticket to a maximum of \"10\" hours but not \"0\", which equates to \"Ticket doesn't expire\".","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000040","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"In Kerberos, there are two types of tickets: Ticket Granting Tickets (TGTs) and Service Tickets. Kerberos tickets have a limited lifetime so the time an attacker has to implement an attack is limited. This policy controls how long TGTs can be renewed. With Kerberos, the user's initial authentication to the domain controller results in a TGT, which is then used to request Service Tickets to resources. Upon startup, each computer gets a TGT before requesting a service ticket to the domain controller and any other computers it needs to access. For services that start up under a specified user account, users must always get a TGT first and then get Service Tickets to all computers and services accessed.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057, SRG-OS-000113-GPOS-00058","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Kerberos user ticket lifetime must be limited to 10 hours or less.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001941","CCI-001942"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254388","title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254388","rule_id_src":"SV-254388r1051103_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A44A161-6E2B-1014-BFE0-E7A6CF26A77C","group_id_src":"V-254388","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254388r1051103"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254389","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nVerify the following is configured in the Default Domain Policy:\n\nOpen \"Group Policy Management\".\n\nNavigate to \"Group Policy Objects\" in the Domain being reviewed (Forest &gt;&gt; Domains &gt;&gt; Domain).\n \nRight-click on the \"Default Domain Policy\".\n\nSelect \"Edit\".\n\nNavigate to Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Policies &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Kerberos Policy.\n\nIf the \"Maximum lifetime for user ticket renewal\" is greater than \"7\" days, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value in the Default Domain Policy for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Policies &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Kerberos Policy &gt;&gt; Maximum lifetime for user ticket renewal to a maximum of \"7\" days or less.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000050","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting determines the period of time (in days) during which a user's Ticket Granting Ticket (TGT) may be renewed. This security configuration limits the amount of time an attacker has to crack the TGT and gain access.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057, SRG-OS-000113-GPOS-00058","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Kerberos policy user ticket renewal maximum lifetime must be limited to seven days or less.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001941","CCI-001942"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254389","title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254389","rule_id_src":"SV-254389r1051104_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A44A780-6E2B-1014-AC0B-C53608E7592D","group_id_src":"V-254389","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254389r1051104"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254390","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nVerify the following is configured in the Default Domain Policy:\n\nOpen \"Group Policy Management\".\n\nNavigate to \"Group Policy Objects\" in the Domain being reviewed (Forest &gt;&gt; Domains &gt;&gt; Domain).\n \nRight-click on the \"Default Domain Policy\".\n\nSelect \"Edit\".\n\nNavigate to Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Policies &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Kerberos Policy.\n\nIf the \"Maximum tolerance for computer clock synchronization\" is greater than \"5\" minutes, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value in the Default Domain Policy for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Kerberos Policy &gt;&gt; Maximum tolerance for computer clock synchronization to a maximum of \"5\" minutes or less.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000060","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting determines the maximum time difference (in minutes) that Kerberos will tolerate between the time on a client's clock and the time on a server's clock while still considering the two clocks synchronous. To prevent replay attacks, Kerberos uses timestamps as part of its protocol definition. For timestamps to work properly, the clocks of the client and the server need to be in sync as much as possible.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057, SRG-OS-000113-GPOS-00058","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 computer clock synchronization tolerance must be limited to five minutes or less.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001941","CCI-001942"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254390","title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254390","rule_id_src":"SV-254390r1051105_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A44AC10-6E2B-1014-BBB5-ECF0737291E5","group_id_src":"V-254390","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254390r1051105"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254391","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nRun \"Regedit\".\n\nNavigate to \"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\NTDS\\Parameters\".\n\nNote the directory locations in the values for:\n\nDatabase log files path\nDSA Database file\n\nBy default, they will be \\Windows\\NTDS.\n\nIf the locations are different, the following will need to be run for each.\n\nOpen \"Command Prompt (Admin)\".\n\nNavigate to the NTDS directory (\\Windows\\NTDS by default).\n\nRun \"icacls *.*\".\n\nIf the permissions on each file are not as restrictive as the following, this is a finding:\n\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(I)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(I)(F)\n\n(I) - permission inherited from parent container\n(F) - full access","severity":"high","fix_text":"Maintain the permissions on NTDS database and log files as follows:\n\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(I)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(I)(F)\n\n(I) - permission inherited from parent container\n(F) - full access","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000070","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Improper access permissions for directory data-related files could allow unauthorized users to read, modify, or delete directory data or audit trails.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125, SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 permissions on the Active Directory data files must only allow System and Administrators access.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001314","CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254391","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254391","rule_id_src":"SV-254391r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A44B5D3-6E2B-1014-AB29-CA2DAED91159","group_id_src":"V-254391","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254391r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254392","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nOpen a command prompt.\n\nRun \"net share\".\n\nMake note of the directory location of the SYSVOL share.\n\nBy default, this will be \\Windows\\SYSVOL\\sysvol. For this requirement, permissions will be verified at the first SYSVOL directory level.\n\nIf any standard user accounts or groups have greater than \"Read &amp; execute\" permissions, this is a finding. \n\nThe default permissions noted below meet this requirement:\n\nOpen \"Command Prompt\".\n\nRun \"icacls c:\\Windows\\SYSVOL\".\n\nThe following results must be displayed:\n\nNT AUTHORITY\\Authenticated Users:(RX)\nNT AUTHORITY\\Authenticated Users:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nBUILTIN\\Server Operators:(RX)\nBUILTIN\\Server Operators:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(M,WDAC,WO)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nCREATOR OWNER:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\n\n(RX) - Read &amp; execute \n\nRun \"icacls /help\" to view definitions of other permission codes.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Maintain the permissions on the SYSVOL directory. Do not allow greater than \"Read &amp; execute\" permissions for standard user accounts or groups. The defaults below meet this requirement:\n\nC:\\Windows\\SYSVOL\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\n\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\n\nAuthenticated Users - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolder, and files\nServer Operators - Read &amp; execute- This folder, subfolder, and files\nAdministrators - Special - This folder only (Special = Basic Permissions: all selected except Full control)\nCREATOR OWNER - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nAdministrators - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nSYSTEM - Full control - This folder, subfolders, and files","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000080","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Improper access permissions for directory data files could allow unauthorized users to read, modify, or delete directory data.\n\nThe SYSVOL directory contains public files (to the domain) such as policies and logon scripts. Data in shared subdirectories are replicated to all domain controllers in a domain.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory SYSVOL directory must have the proper access control permissions.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254392","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254392","rule_id_src":"SV-254392r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A453B0B-6E2B-1014-B0A7-95E3A3526C50","group_id_src":"V-254392","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254392r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:30901","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the permissions on Group Policy objects.\n\nOpen \"Group Policy Management\" (available from various menus or run \"gpmc.msc\").\n\nNavigate to \"Group Policy Objects\" in the domain being reviewed (Forest &gt;&gt; Domains &gt;&gt; Domain).\n\nFor each Group Policy object:\n\nSelect the Group Policy object item in the left pane.\n\nSelect the \"Delegation\" tab in the right pane.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\".\n\nSelect each Group or user name.\n\nView the permissions.\n\nIf any standard user accounts or groups have \"Allow\" permissions greater than \"Read\" and \"Apply group policy\", this is a finding.\n\nOther access permissions that allow the objects to be updated are considered findings unless specifically documented by the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe default permissions noted below satisfy this requirement. \n\nThe permissions shown are at the summary level. More detailed permissions can be viewed by selecting the next \"Advanced\" button, the desired Permission entry, and the \"Edit\" button.\n\nAuthenticated Users - Read, Apply group policy, Special permissions\n\nThe special permissions for Authenticated Users are for Read-type Properties. If detailed permissions include any Create, Delete, Modify, or Write Permissions or Properties, this is a finding.\n\nThe special permissions for the following default groups are not the focus of this requirement and may include a wide range of permissions and properties:\n\nCREATOR OWNER - Special permissions\nSYSTEM - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Delete all child objects, Special permissions\nDomain Admins - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Delete all child objects, Special permissions\nEnterprise Admins - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Delete all child objects, Special permissions\nENTERPRISE DOMAIN CONTROLLERS - Read, Special permissions\n\n","severity":"high","fix_text":"Maintain the permissions on Group Policy objects to not allow greater than \"Read\" and \"Apply group policy\" for standard user accounts or groups. The default permissions below meet this requirement:\n\nAuthenticated Users - Read, Apply group policy, Special permissions\n\nThe special permissions for Authenticated Users are for Read-type Properties.\n\nCREATOR OWNER - Special permissions\nSYSTEM - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Delete all child objects, Special permissions\nDomain Admins - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Delete all child objects, Special permissions\nEnterprise Admins - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Delete all child objects, Special permissions\nENTERPRISE DOMAIN CONTROLLERS - Read, Special permissions\n\nDocument any other access permissions that allow the objects to be updated with the ISSO.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000090","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"When directory service database objects do not have appropriate access control permissions, it may be possible for malicious users to create, read, update, or delete the objects and degrade or destroy the integrity of the data. When the directory service is used for identification, authentication, or authorization functions, a compromise of the database objects could lead to a compromise of all systems relying on the directory service.\n\nFor Active Directory (AD), the Group Policy objects require special attention. In a distributed administration model (i.e., help desk), Group Policy objects are more likely to have access permissions changed from the secure defaults. If inappropriate access permissions are defined for Group Policy objects, this could allow an intruder to change the security policy applied to all domain client computers (workstations and servers).","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Group Policy objects must have proper access control permissions.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254393","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254393","rule_id_src":"SV-254393r1081073_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A454280-6E2B-1014-9710-D4129145367F","group_id_src":"V-254393","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254393r1081073"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:31101","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the permissions on the Domain Controllers OU.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nSelect \"Advanced Features\" in the \"View\" menu if not previously selected.\n\nSelect the \"Domain Controllers\" OU (folder in folder icon).\n\nRight-click and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nIf the permissions on the Domain Controllers OU do not restrict changes to System, Domain Admins, Enterprise Admins and Administrators, this is a finding.\n\nThe default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nDomains supporting Microsoft Exchange will have additional Exchange related permissions on the Domain Controllers OU. These may include some change related permissions and are not a finding.\n\nThe permissions shown are at the summary level. More detailed permissions can be viewed by selecting the \"Advanced\" button, the desired Permission entry, and the \"View\" or \"Edit\" button.\n\nExcept where noted otherwise, the special permissions may include a wide range of permissions and properties and are acceptable for this requirement.\n\nCREATOR OWNER - Special permissions\n\nSELF - Special permissions\n\nAuthenticated Users - Read, Special permissions\n\nThe special permissions for Authenticated Users are Read types.\n\nIf detailed permissions include any Create, Delete, Modify, or Write Permissions or Properties, this is a finding.\n\nSYSTEM - Full Control\n\nDomain Admins - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Generate resultant set of policy (logging), Generate resultant set of policy (planning), Special permissions\n\nEnterprise Admins - Full Control\n\nKey Admins - Special permissions\n\nEnterprise Key Admins - Special permissions\n\nAdministrators - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Generate resultant set of policy (logging), Generate resultant set of policy (planning), Special permissions\n\nPre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access - Special permissions\n\nThe Special permissions for Pre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access are Read types.\n\nIf detailed permissions include any Create, Delete, Modify, or Write Permissions or Properties, this is a finding.\n\nENTERPRISE DOMAIN CONTROLLERS - Read, Special permissions","severity":"high","fix_text":"Limit the permissions on the Domain Controllers OU to restrict changes to System, Domain Admins, Enterprise Admins and Administrators.\n\nThe default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nDomains supporting Microsoft Exchange will have additional Exchange related permissions on the Domain Controllers OU. These may include some change related permissions.\n\nCREATOR OWNER - Special permissions\n\nSELF - Special permissions\n\nAuthenticated Users - Read, Special permissions\n\nThe special permissions for Authenticated Users are Read types.\n\nSYSTEM - Full Control\n\nDomain Admins - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Generate resultant set of policy (logging), Generate resultant set of policy (planning), Special permissions\n\nEnterprise Admins - Full Control\n\nKey Admins - Special permissions\n\nEnterprise Key Admins - Special permissions\n\nAdministrators - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Generate resultant set of policy (logging), Generate resultant set of policy (planning), Special permissions\n\nPre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access - Special permissions\n\nThe special permissions for Pre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access are Read types.\n\nENTERPRISE DOMAIN CONTROLLERS - Read, Special permissions","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000100","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"When Active Directory objects do not have appropriate access control permissions, it may be possible for malicious users to create, read, update, or delete the objects and degrade or destroy the integrity of the data. When the directory service is used for identification, authentication, or authorization functions, a compromise of the database objects could lead to a compromise of all systems that rely on the directory service.\n\nThe Domain Controllers OU object requires special attention as the Domain Controllers are central to the configuration and management of the domain. Inappropriate access permissions defined for the Domain Controllers OU could allow an intruder or unauthorized personnel to make changes that could lead to the compromise of the domain.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Domain Controllers Organizational Unit (OU) object must have the proper access control permissions.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254394","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254394","rule_id_src":"SV-254394r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45543C-6E2B-1014-A7DC-B7EF6A099496","group_id_src":"V-254394","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254394r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:31301","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the permissions on domain-defined OUs.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nFor each OU that is defined (folder in folder icon) excluding the Domain Controllers OU:\n\nRight-click the OU and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nIf the Allow type permissions on the OU are not at least as restrictive as those below, this is a finding.\n\nThe permissions shown are at the summary level. More detailed permissions can be viewed by selecting the \"Advanced\" button, the desired Permission entry, and the \"Edit\" or \"View\" button.\n\nExcept where noted otherwise, the special permissions may include a wide range of permissions and properties and are acceptable for this requirement.\n\nCREATOR OWNER - Special permissions\n\nSelf - Special permissions\n\nAuthenticated Users - Read, Special permissions\n\nThe Special permissions for Authenticated Users are Read type. If detailed permissions include any Create, Delete, Modify, or Write Permissions or Properties, this is a finding.\n\nSYSTEM - Full Control\n\nDomain Admins - Full Control\n\nEnterprise Admins - Full Control\n\nKey Admins - Special permissions\n\nEnterprise Key Admins - Special permissions\n\nAdministrators - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Generate resultant set of policy (logging), Generate resultant set of policy (planning), Special permissions\n\nPre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access - Special permissions\n\nThe Special permissions for Pre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access are for Read types. If detailed permissions include any Create, Delete, Modify, or Write Permissions or Properties, this is a finding.\n\nENTERPRISE DOMAIN CONTROLLERS - Read, Special permissions\n\nIf an Information System Security Officer (ISSO)-approved distributed administration model (help desk or other user support staff) is implemented, permissions above Read may be allowed for groups documented by the ISSO.\n\nIf any OU with improper permissions includes identification or authentication data (e.g., accounts, passwords, or password hash data) used by systems to determine access control, the severity is CAT I (e.g., OUs that include user accounts, including service/application accounts).\n\nIf an OU with improper permissions does not include identification and authentication data used by systems to determine access control, the severity is CAT II (e.g., Workstation, Printer OUs).","severity":"high","fix_text":"Maintain the Allow type permissions on domain-defined OUs to be at least as restrictive as the defaults below.\n\nDocument any additional permissions above Read with the ISSO if an approved distributed administration model (help desk or other user support staff) is implemented.\n\nCREATOR OWNER - Special permissions\n\nSelf - Special permissions\n\nAuthenticated Users - Read, Special permissions\n\nThe special permissions for Authenticated Users are Read type.\n\nSYSTEM - Full Control\n\nDomain Admins - Full Control\n\nEnterprise Admins - Full Control\n\nKey Admins - Special permissions\n\nEnterprise Key Admins - Special permissions\n\nAdministrators - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Generate resultant set of policy (logging), Generate resultant set of policy (planning), Special permissions\n\nPre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access - Special permissions\n\nThe special permissions for Pre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access are for Read types.\n\nENTERPRISE DOMAIN CONTROLLERS - Read, Special permissions","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000110","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"When directory service database objects do not have appropriate access control permissions, it may be possible for malicious users to create, read, update, or delete the objects and degrade or destroy the integrity of the data. When the directory service is used for identification, authentication, or authorization functions, a compromise of the database objects could lead to a compromise of all systems that rely on the directory service.\n\nFor Active Directory, the OU objects require special attention. In a distributed administration model (i.e., help desk), OU objects are more likely to have access permissions changed from the secure defaults. If inappropriate access permissions are defined for OU objects, it could allow an intruder to add or delete users in the OU. This could result in unauthorized access to data or a denial of service (DoS) to authorized users.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 organization created Active Directory Organizational Unit (OU) objects must have proper access control permissions.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254395","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254395","rule_id_src":"SV-254395r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A455A7A-6E2B-1014-AF4E-E296DC952BF9","group_id_src":"V-254395","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254395r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254396","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nRun \"Regedit\".\n\nNavigate to \"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\NTDS\\Parameters\".\n\nNote the directory locations in the values for \"DSA Database file\".\n\nOpen \"Command Prompt\".\n\nEnter \"net share\".\n\nNote the logical drive(s) or file system partition for any organization-created data shares.\n\nIgnore system shares (e.g., NETLOGON, SYSVOL, and administrative shares ending in $). User shares that are hidden (ending with $) must not be ignored.\n\nIf user shares are located on the same logical partition as the directory server data files, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Move shares used to store files owned by users to a different logical partition than the directory server data files.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000120","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"When directory service data files, especially for directories used for identification, authentication, or authorization, reside on the same logical partition as user-owned files, the directory service data may be more vulnerable to unauthorized access or other availability compromises. Directory service and user-owned data files sharing a partition may be configured with less restrictive permissions in order to allow access to the user data. \n\nThe directory service may be vulnerable to a denial of service attack when user-owned files on a common partition are expanded to an extent preventing the directory service from acquiring more space for directory or audit data.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 data files owned by users must be on a different logical partition from the directory server data files.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001090"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254396","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254396","rule_id_src":"SV-254396r1137695_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A455EDF-6E2B-1014-99A7-B9846795DAB2","group_id_src":"V-254396","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254396r1137695"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:31701","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers, it is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the installed roles the domain controller is supporting.\n\nStart \"Server Manager\".\n\nSelect \"AD DS\" in the left pane and the server name under \"Servers\" to the right.\n\nSelect \"Add (or Remove) Roles and Features\" from \"Tasks\" in the \"Roles and Features\" section. (Cancel before any changes are made.)\n\nDetermine if any additional server roles are installed. A basic domain controller setup will include the following:\n\n- Active Directory Domain Services\n- DNS Server\n- File and Storage Services\n\nIf any roles not requiring installation on a domain controller are installed, this is a finding. \n\nA Domain Name System (DNS) server integrated with the directory server (e.g., AD-integrated DNS) is an acceptable application. However, the DNS server must comply with the DNS STIG security requirements.\n\nRun \"Programs and Features\".\n\nReview installed applications.\n\nIf any applications are installed that are not required for the domain controller, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Remove additional roles or applications such as web, database, and email from the domain controller.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000130","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Executing application servers on the same host machine with a directory server may substantially weaken the security of the directory server. Web or database server applications usually require the addition of many programs and accounts, increasing the attack surface of the computer. \n\nSome applications require the addition of privileged accounts, providing potential sources of compromise. Some applications (such as Microsoft Exchange) may require the use of network ports or services conflicting with the directory server. In this case, nonstandard ports might be selected, and this could interfere with intrusion detection or prevention services.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 domain controllers must run on a machine dedicated to that function.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254397","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254397","rule_id_src":"SV-254397r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4562EA-6E2B-1014-8DFF-DCA00A44420E","group_id_src":"V-254397","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254397r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:31901","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the organization network diagram(s) or documentation to determine the level of classification for the network(s) over which replication data is transmitted.\n\nDetermine the classification level of the Windows domain controller.\n\nIf the classification level of the Windows domain controller is higher than the level of the networks, review the organization network diagram(s) and directory implementation documentation to determine if NSA-approved encryption is used to protect the replication network traffic.\n\nIf the classification level of the Windows domain controller is higher than the level of the network traversed and NSA-approved encryption is not used, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure NSA-approved (Type 1) cryptography to protect the directory data in transit for directory service implementations at a classified confidentiality level that transfer replication data through a network cleared to a lower level than the data.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000140","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Directory data that is not appropriately encrypted is subject to compromise. Commercial-grade encryption does not provide adequate protection when the classification level of directory data in transit is higher than the level of the network.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must use separate, NSA-approved (Type 1) cryptography to protect the directory data in transit for directory service implementations at a classified confidentiality level when replication data traverses a network cleared to a lower level than the data.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002450"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254398","title":"SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254398","rule_id_src":"SV-254398r987791_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4571D6-6E2B-1014-B67A-D2CAC2501A8C","group_id_src":"V-254398","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254398r987791"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:32101","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nOpen \"Command Prompt\" (not elevated).\n\nRun \"ldp.exe\".\n\nFrom the \"Connection menu\", select \"Bind\".\n\nClear the User, Password, and Domain fields.\n\nSelect \"Simple bind\" for the Bind type and click \"OK\".\n\nConfirmation of anonymous access will be displayed at the end:\n\nres = ldap_simple_bind_s\nAuthenticated as: 'NT AUTHORITY\\ANONYMOUS LOGON'\n\nFrom the \"Browse\" menu, select \"Search\".\n\nIn the Search dialog, enter the DN of the domain naming context (generally something like \"dc=disaost,dc=mil\") in the Base DN field.\n\nClear the Attributes field and select \"Run\".\n\nError messages must display related to Bind and user not authenticated.\n\nIf attribute data is displayed, anonymous access is enabled to the domain naming context and this is a finding.\n\nThe following network controls allow the finding severity to be downgraded to a CAT II since these measures lower the risk associated with anonymous access.\n\nNetwork hardware ports at the site are subject to 802.1x authentication or MAC address restrictions. \n\nPremise firewall or host restrictions prevent access to ports 389, 636, 3268, and 3269 from client hosts not explicitly identified by domain (.mil) or IP address.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure directory data (outside the root DSE) of a nonpublic directory to prevent anonymous access.\n\nFor AD, there are multiple configuration items that could enable anonymous access.\n\nChanging the access permissions on the domain naming context object (from the secure defaults) could enable anonymous access. If the check procedures indicate this is the cause, the process that was used to change the permissions must be reversed. This could have been through the Windows Support Tools ADSI Edit console (adsiedit.msc).\n\nThe dsHeuristics option is used. This is addressed in check V-8555 in the AD Forest STIG.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000150","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"To the extent that anonymous access to directory data (outside the root DSE) is permitted, read access control of the data is effectively disabled. If other means of controlling access (such as network restrictions) are compromised, there may be nothing else to protect the confidentiality of sensitive directory data.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 directory data (outside the root DSE) of a nonpublic directory must be configured to prevent anonymous access.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254399","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254399","rule_id_src":"SV-254399r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A457859-6E2B-1014-8D6F-CB646F0688E0","group_id_src":"V-254399","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254399r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254400","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000163-GPOS-00072","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nOpen an elevated \"Command Prompt\" (run as administrator).\n\nEnter \"ntdsutil\".\n\nAt the \"ntdsutil:\" prompt, enter \"LDAP policies\".\n\nAt the \"ldap policy:\" prompt, enter \"connections\".\n\nAt the \"server connections:\" prompt, enter \"connect to server [host-name]\"\n(where [host-name] is the computer name of the domain controller).\n\nAt the \"server connections:\" prompt, enter \"q\".\n\nAt the \"ldap policy:\" prompt, enter \"show values\". \n\nIf the value for MaxConnIdleTime is greater than \"300\" (5 minutes) or is not specified, this is a finding.\n\nEnter \"q\" at the \"ldap policy:\" and \"ntdsutil:\" prompts to exit.\n\nAlternately, Dsquery can be used to display MaxConnIdleTime:\n\nOpen \"Command Prompt (Admin)\".\nEnter the following command (on a single line).\n\ndsquery * \"cn=Default Query Policy,cn=Query-Policies,cn=Directory Service, cn=Windows NT,cn=Services,cn=Configuration,dc=[forest-name]\" -attr LDAPAdminLimits \n\nThe quotes are required and dc=[forest-name] is the fully qualified LDAP name of the domain being reviewed (e.g., dc=disaost,dc=mil).\n\nIf the results do not specify a \"MaxConnIdleTime\" or it has a value greater than \"300\" (5 minutes), this is a finding.","severity":"low","fix_text":"Configure the directory service to terminate LDAP-based network connections to the directory server after 5 minutes of inactivity.\n\nOpen an elevated \"Command prompt\" (run as administrator).\n\nEnter \"ntdsutil\".\n\nAt the \"ntdsutil:\" prompt, enter \"LDAP policies\".\n\nAt the \"ldap policy:\" prompt, enter \"connections\".\n\nAt the \"server connections:\" prompt, enter \"connect to server [host-name]\" (where [host-name] is the computer name of the domain controller).\n\nAt the \"server connections:\" prompt, enter \"q\".\n\nAt the \"ldap policy:\" prompt, enter \"Set MaxConnIdleTime to 300\".\n\nEnter \"Commit Changes\" to save.\n\nEnter \"Show values\" to verify changes.\n\nEnter \"q\" at the \"ldap policy:\" and \"ntdsutil:\" prompts to exit.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000160","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The failure to terminate inactive network connections increases the risk of a successful attack on the directory server. The longer an established session is in progress, the more time an attacker has to hijack the session, implement a means to passively intercept data, or compromise any protections on client access. For example, if an attacker gains control of a client computer, an existing (already authenticated) session with the directory server could allow access to the directory. The lack of confidentiality protection in LDAP-based sessions increases exposure to this vulnerability.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000163-GPOS-00072, SRG-OS-000279-GPOS-00109","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 directory service must be configured to terminate LDAP-based network connections to the directory server after five minutes of inactivity.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001133","CCI-002361"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254400","title":"SRG-OS-000163-GPOS-00072"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254400","rule_id_src":"SV-254400r970703_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A457D65-6E2B-1014-B490-E2BAF32021DE","group_id_src":"V-254400","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254400r970703"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:32501","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the auditing configuration for all Group Policy objects.\n\nOpen \"Group Policy Management\" (available from various menus or run \"gpmc.msc\").\n\nNavigate to \"Group Policy Objects\" in the domain being reviewed (Forest &gt;&gt; Domains &gt;&gt; Domain).\n\nFor each Group Policy object:\n\nSelect the Group Policy object item in the left pane.\n\nSelect the \"Delegation\" tab in the right pane.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\".\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" again and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nIf the audit settings for any Group Policy object are not at least as inclusive as those below, this is a finding:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nApplies to - This object and all descendant objects or Descendant groupPolicyContainer objects\n\nThe three Success types listed below are defaults inherited from the Parent Object. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special (Permissions: Write all properties, Modify permissions; Properties: all \"Write\" type selected)\nInherited from - Parent Object\nApplies to - Descendant groupPolicyContainer objects\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - blank (Permissions: none selected; Properties: one instance - Write gPLink, one instance - Write gPOptions)\nInherited from - Parent Object\nApplies to - Descendant Organization Unit Objects","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the audit settings for Group Policy objects to include the following:\n\nThis can be done at the Policy level in Active Directory to apply to all group policies.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nSelect \"Advanced Features\" from the \"View\" Menu.\n\nNavigate to [Domain] &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Policies in the left panel.\n\nRight-click \"Policies\", select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\".\n\nSelect the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nApplies to - This object and all descendant objects or Descendant groupPolicyContainer objects\n\nThe three Success types listed below are defaults inherited from the Parent Object. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special (Permissions: Write all properties, Modify permissions; Properties: all \"Write\" type selected)\nInherited from - Parent Object\nApplies to - Descendant groupPolicyContainer objects\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - blank (Permissions: none selected; Properties: one instance - Write gPLink, one instance - Write gPOptions)\nInherited from - Parent Object\nApplies to - Descendant Organization Unit Objects","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000170","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"When inappropriate audit settings are configured for directory service database objects, it may be possible for a user or process to update the data without generating any tracking data. The impact of missing audit data is related to the type of object. A failure to capture audit data for objects used by identification, authentication, or authorization functions could degrade or eliminate the ability to track changes to access policy for systems or data. \n\nFor Active Directory (AD), there are a number of critical object types in the domain naming context of the AD database for which auditing is essential. This includes Group Policy objects. Because changes to these objects can significantly impact access controls or the availability of systems, the absence of auditing data makes it impossible to identify the source of changes that impact the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data and systems throughout an AD domain. The lack of proper auditing can result in insufficient forensic evidence needed to investigate an incident and prosecute the intruder.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Group Policy objects must be configured with proper audit settings.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254401","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254401","rule_id_src":"SV-254401r958732_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4582D3-6E2B-1014-A3A0-E1E2B0377F18","group_id_src":"V-254401","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254401r958732"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:32701","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the auditing configuration for the Domain object.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the domain name and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nIf the audit settings on the Domain object are not at least as inclusive as those below, this is a finding:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - Special\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Domain Users\nAccess - All extended rights\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Administrators\nAccess - All extended rights\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n(Access - Special = Permissions: Write all properties, Modify permissions, Modify owner)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Open \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the domain name and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nConfigure the audit settings for Domain object to include the following:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - Special\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Domain Users\nAccess - All extended rights\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Administrators\nAccess - All extended rights\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n(Access - Special = Permissions: Write all properties, Modify permissions, Modify owner.)","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000180","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"When inappropriate audit settings are configured for directory service database objects, it may be possible for a user or process to update the data without generating any tracking data. The impact of missing audit data is related to the type of object. A failure to capture audit data for objects used by identification, authentication, or authorization functions could degrade or eliminate the ability to track changes to access policy for systems or data. \n\nFor Active Directory (AD), there are a number of critical object types in the domain naming context of the AD database for which auditing is essential. This includes the Domain object. Because changes to these objects can significantly impact access controls or the availability of systems, the absence of auditing data makes it impossible to identify the source of changes that impact the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data and systems throughout an AD domain. The lack of proper auditing can result in insufficient forensic evidence needed to investigate an incident and prosecute the intruder.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Domain object must be configured with proper audit settings.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254402","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254402","rule_id_src":"SV-254402r958732_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4587E5-6E2B-1014-AFCB-84DE7CE0D2D5","group_id_src":"V-254402","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254402r958732"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:32901","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the auditing configuration for Infrastructure object.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the \"Infrastructure\" object in the right pane and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nIf the audit settings on the Infrastructure object are not at least as inclusive as those below, this is a finding:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\n(Access - Special = Permissions: Write all properties, All extended rights, Change infrastructure master)\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - (CN of domain)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Open \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the \"Infrastructure\" object in the right pane and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nConfigure the audit settings for Infrastructure object to include the following:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\n(Access - Special = Permissions: Write all properties, All extended rights, Change infrastructure master)\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - (CN of domain)","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000190","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"When inappropriate audit settings are configured for directory service database objects, it may be possible for a user or process to update the data without generating any tracking data. The impact of missing audit data is related to the type of object. A failure to capture audit data for objects used by identification, authentication, or authorization functions could degrade or eliminate the ability to track changes to access policy for systems or data. \n\nFor Active Directory (AD), there are a number of critical object types in the domain naming context of the AD database for which auditing is essential. This includes the Infrastructure object. Because changes to these objects can significantly impact access controls or the availability of systems, the absence of auditing data makes it impossible to identify the source of changes that impact the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data and systems throughout an AD domain. The lack of proper auditing can result in insufficient forensic evidence needed to investigate an incident and prosecute the intruder.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Infrastructure object must be configured with proper audit settings.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254403","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254403","rule_id_src":"SV-254403r958732_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A458E89-6E2B-1014-AB2B-F970E1C94B7C","group_id_src":"V-254403","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254403r958732"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:33101","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the auditing configuration for the Domain Controller OU object.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect the \"Domain Controllers OU\" under the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the \"Domain Controllers OU\" object and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nIf the audit settings on the Domain Controllers OU object are not at least as inclusive as those below, this is a finding:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object and all descendant objects\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n(Access - Special = Permissions: all create, delete and modify permissions)\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Write all properties\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object and all descendant objects\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - (CN of domain)\nApplies to - Descendant Organizational Unit objects","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Open \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect the \"Domain Controllers OU\" under the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the \"Domain Controllers OU\" object and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nConfigure the audit settings for Domain Controllers OU object to include the following:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n(Access - Special = Permissions: all create, delete and modify permissions)\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Write all properties\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object and all descendant objects\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - (CN of domain)\nApplies to - Descendant Organizational Unit objects","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000200","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"When inappropriate audit settings are configured for directory service database objects, it may be possible for a user or process to update the data without generating any tracking data. The impact of missing audit data is related to the type of object. A failure to capture audit data for objects used by identification, authentication, or authorization functions could degrade or eliminate the ability to track changes to access policy for systems or data. \n\nFor Active Directory (AD), there are a number of critical object types in the domain naming context of the AD database for which auditing is essential. This includes the Domain Controller OU object. Because changes to these objects can significantly impact access controls or the availability of systems, the absence of auditing data makes it impossible to identify the source of changes that impact the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data and systems throughout an AD domain. The lack of proper auditing can result in insufficient forensic evidence needed to investigate an incident and prosecute the intruder.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Domain Controllers Organizational Unit (OU) object must be configured with proper audit settings.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254404","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254404","rule_id_src":"SV-254404r958732_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45A4E3-6E2B-1014-9597-94EF64E787A7","group_id_src":"V-254404","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254404r958732"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:33301","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the auditing configuration for the \"AdminSDHolder\" object.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect \"System\" under the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the \"AdminSDHolder\" object in the right pane and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nIf the audit settings on the \"AdminSDHolder\" object are not at least as inclusive as those below, this is a finding:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n(Access - Special = Write all properties, Modify permissions, Modify owner)\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - (CN of domain)\nApplies to - Descendant Organizational Unit objects","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Open \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect \"System\" under the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the \"AdminSDHolder\" object in the right pane and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nConfigure the audit settings for AdminSDHolder object to include the following:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n(Access - Special = Write all properties, Modify permissions, Modify owner)\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - (CN of domain)\nApplies to - Descendant Organizational Unit objects","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000210","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"When inappropriate audit settings are configured for directory service database objects, it may be possible for a user or process to update the data without generating any tracking data. The impact of missing audit data is related to the type of object. A failure to capture audit data for objects used by identification, authentication, or authorization functions could degrade or eliminate the ability to track changes to access policy for systems or data. \n\nFor Active Directory (AD), there are a number of critical object types in the domain naming context of the AD database for which auditing is essential. This includes the AdminSDHolder object. Because changes to these objects can significantly impact access controls or the availability of systems, the absence of auditing data makes it impossible to identify the source of changes that impact the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data and systems throughout an AD domain. The lack of proper auditing can result in insufficient forensic evidence needed to investigate an incident and prosecute the intruder.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory AdminSDHolder object must be configured with proper audit settings.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254405","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254405","rule_id_src":"SV-254405r958732_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45AC29-6E2B-1014-8C1F-F63441B67885","group_id_src":"V-254405","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254405r958732"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:33501","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the auditing configuration for the \"RID Manager$\" object.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect \"System\" under the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the \"RID Manager$\" object in the right pane and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nIf the audit settings on the \"RID Manager$\" object are not at least as inclusive as those below, this is a finding:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\n (Access - Special = Write all properties, All extended rights, Change RID master)\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - (CN of domain)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Open \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect \"System\" under the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the \"RID Manager$\" object in the right pane and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nConfigure the audit settings for RID Manager$ object to include the following:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\n (Access - Special = Write all properties, All extended rights, Change RID master)\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - (CN of domain)","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000220","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"When inappropriate audit settings are configured for directory service database objects, it may be possible for a user or process to update the data without generating any tracking data. The impact of missing audit data is related to the type of object. A failure to capture audit data for objects used by identification, authentication, or authorization functions could degrade or eliminate the ability to track changes to access policy for systems or data. \n\nFor Active Directory (AD), there are a number of critical object types in the domain naming context of the AD database for which auditing is essential. This includes the RID Manager$ object. Because changes to these objects can significantly impact access controls or the availability of systems, the absence of auditing data makes it impossible to identify the source of changes that impact the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data and systems throughout an AD domain. The lack of proper auditing can result in insufficient forensic evidence needed to investigate an incident and prosecute the intruder.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory RID Manager$ object must be configured with proper audit settings.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254406","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254406","rule_id_src":"SV-254406r958732_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45B0FC-6E2B-1014-A4D3-B1B4105D92C3","group_id_src":"V-254406","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254406r958732"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254407","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nSecurity Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nAccount Management &gt;&gt; Computer Account Management - Success","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Account Management &gt;&gt; Audit Computer Account Management with Success selected.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000230","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nComputer Account Management records events such as creating, changing, deleting, renaming, disabling, or enabling computer accounts.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004, SRG-OS-000239-GPOS-00089, SRG-OS-000240-GPOS-00090, SRG-OS-000241-GPOS-00091, SRG-OS-000303-GPOS-00120, SRG-OS-000476-GPOS-00221","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit Account Management - Computer Account Management successes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000018","CCI-000172","CCI-001403","CCI-001404","CCI-001405","CCI-002130"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254407","title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254407","rule_id_src":"SV-254407r958368_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45B58C-6E2B-1014-8CC0-A0626C3321C4","group_id_src":"V-254407","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254407r958368"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254408","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nSecurity Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nDS Access &gt;&gt; Directory Service Access - Success","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; DS Access &gt;&gt; Directory Service Access with Success selected.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000240","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Directory Service Access records events related to users accessing an Active Directory object.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit DS Access - Directory Service Access successes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254408","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254408","rule_id_src":"SV-254408r958732_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45BA1F-6E2B-1014-8A0D-D96DD00BDBE8","group_id_src":"V-254408","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254408r958732"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254409","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nSecurity Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nDS Access &gt;&gt; Directory Service Access - Failure","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; DS Access &gt;&gt; Directory Service Access with \"Failure\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000250","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Directory Service Access records events related to users accessing an Active Directory object.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit DS Access - Directory Service Access failures.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254409","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254409","rule_id_src":"SV-254409r958732_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45BEA5-6E2B-1014-9157-FA7244BEC922","group_id_src":"V-254409","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254409r958732"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254410","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nSecurity Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nDS Access &gt;&gt; Directory Service Changes - Success","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; DS Access &gt;&gt; Directory Service Changes with \"Success\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000260","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Directory Service Changes records events related to changes made to objects in Active Directory Domain Services.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit DS Access - Directory Service Changes successes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254410","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254410","rule_id_src":"SV-254410r958732_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45C2AA-6E2B-1014-A297-85A20BC76645","group_id_src":"V-254410","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254410r958732"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254412","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"Add/Remove Snap-in\" from the \"File\" menu.\n\nSelect \"Certificates\" in the left pane and click \"Add &gt;\".\n\nSelect \"Computer Account\" and click \"Next\".\n\nSelect the appropriate option for \"Select the computer you want this snap-in to manage\" and click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nSelect and expand the Certificates (Local Computer) entry in the left pane.\n\nSelect and expand the Personal entry in the left pane.\n\nSelect the Certificates entry in the left pane.\n\nIf no certificate for the domain controller exists in the right pane, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Obtain a server certificate for the domain controller.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000280","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Domain controllers are part of the chain of trust for PKI authentications. Without the appropriate certificate, the authenticity of the domain controller cannot be verified. Domain controllers must have a server certificate to establish authenticity as part of PKI authentications in the domain.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 domain controllers must have a PKI server certificate.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254412","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254412","rule_id_src":"SV-254412r958448_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45C875-6E2B-1014-8B73-F609FA425301","group_id_src":"V-254412","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254412r958448"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:34701","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"Add/Remove Snap-in\" from the \"File\" menu.\n\nSelect \"Certificates\" in the left pane, and then click \"Add &gt;\".\n\nSelect \"Computer Account\", and then click \"Next\".\n\nSelect the appropriate option for \"Select the computer you want this snap-in to manage\", and then click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nSelect and expand the \"Certificates (Local Computer)\" entry in the left pane.\n\nSelect and expand the \"Personal\" entry in the left pane.\n\nSelect the \"Certificates\" entry in the left pane.\n\nIn the right pane, examine the \"Issued By\" field for the certificate to determine the issuing CA.\n\nIf the \"Issued By\" field of the PKI certificate being used by the domain controller does not indicate the issuing CA is part of the DOD PKI or an approved ECA, this is a finding.\n\nIf the certificates in use are issued by a CA authorized by the Component's CIO, this is a CAT II finding.\n\nThere are multiple sources from which lists of valid DOD CAs and approved ECAs can be obtained: \n\nThe Global Directory Service (GDS) website provides an online source. The address for this site is https://crl.gds.disa.mil.\n\nDOD Public Key Enablement (PKE) Engineering Support maintains the InstallRoot utility to manage DOD supported root certificates on Windows computers, which includes a list of authorized CAs. The utility package can be downloaded from the PKI and PKE Tools page on Cyber Exchange: https://www.cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Obtain a server certificate for the domain controller issued by the DOD PKI or an approved ECA.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000290","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"A PKI implementation depends on the practices established by the Certificate Authority (CA) to ensure the implementation is secure. Without proper practices, the certificates issued by a CA have limited value in authentication functions. The use of multiple CAs from separate PKI implementations results in interoperability issues. If servers and clients do not have a common set of root CA certificates, they are not able to authenticate each other.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 domain controller PKI certificates must be issued by the DOD PKI or an approved External Certificate Authority (ECA).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254413","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254413","rule_id_src":"SV-254413r1153446_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45CCD4-6E2B-1014-8537-9FF52C6DAC56","group_id_src":"V-254413","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254413r1153446"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:34901","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview user account mappings to PKI certificates.\n\nOpen \"Windows PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-ADUser -Filter * | FT Name, UserPrincipalName, Enabled\".\n\nExclude disabled accounts (e.g., DefaultAccount, Guest) and the krbtgt account.\n\nIf the User Principal Name (UPN) is not in the format of an individual's identifier for the certificate type and for the appropriate domain suffix, this is a finding.\n\nFor standard NIPRNet certificates, the individual's identifier is in the format of an Electronic Data Interchange - Personnel Identifier (EDI-PI).\n\nAlt Tokens and other certificates may use a different UPN format than the EDI-PI which vary by organization. Verified these with the organization.\n\nNIPRNet Example:\n\nName - User Principal Name\nUser1 - 1234567890@mil\n\nSee PKE documentation for other network domain suffixes.\n\nIf the mappings are to certificates issued by a CA authorized by the Component's CIO, this is a CAT II finding.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Map user accounts to PKI certificates using the appropriate User Principal Name (UPN) for the network. See PKE documentation for details.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000300","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"A PKI implementation depends on the practices established by the Certificate Authority (CA) to ensure the implementation is secure. Without proper practices, the certificates issued by a CA have limited value in authentication functions.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034, SRG-OS-000403-GPOS-00182","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 PKI certificates associated with user accounts must be issued by a DoD PKI or an approved External Certificate Authority (ECA).","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254414","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254414","rule_id_src":"SV-254414r958448_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45D0B7-6E2B-1014-9C4F-A5FA2294F614","group_id_src":"V-254414","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254414r958448"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254415","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000105-GPOS-00052","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter the following:\n\n\"Get-ADUser -Filter {(Enabled -eq $True) -and (SmartcardLogonRequired -eq $False)} | FT Name\"\n(\"DistinguishedName\" may be substituted for \"Name\" for more detailed output.)\n\nIf any user accounts, including administrators, are listed, this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\n\nTo view sample accounts in \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\"):\n\nSelect the Organizational Unit (OU) where the user accounts are located. (By default, this is the Users node; however, accounts may be under other organization-defined OUs.)\n\nRight-click the sample user account and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Account\" tab.\n\nIf any user accounts, including administrators, do not have \"Smart card is required for interactive logon\" checked in the \"Account Options\" area, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure all user accounts, including administrator accounts, in Active Directory to enable the option \"Smart card is required for interactive logon\".\n\nRun \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\"):\n\nSelect the OU where the user accounts are located. (By default this is the Users node; however, accounts may be under other organization-defined OUs.)\n\nRight-click the user account and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Account\" tab.\n\nCheck \"Smart card is required for interactive logon\" in the \"Account Options\" area.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000310","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Smart cards such as the CAC support a two-factor authentication technique. This provides a higher level of trust in the asserted identity than use of the username and password for authentication.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000105-GPOS-00052, SRG-OS-000106-GPOS-00053, SRG-OS-000107-GPOS-00054, SRG-OS-000108-GPOS-00055, SRG-OS-000375-GPOS-00160","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory user accounts, including administrators, must be configured to require the use of a Common Access Card (CAC), Personal Identity Verification (PIV)-compliant hardware token, or Alternate Logon Token (ALT) for user authentication.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000776","CCI-000767","CCI-000768","CCI-001948"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254415","title":"SRG-OS-000105-GPOS-00052"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254415","rule_id_src":"SV-254415r1081074_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45D4CE-6E2B-1014-A58C-DE31D3986A7A","group_id_src":"V-254415","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254415r1081074"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254416","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\NTDS\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: LDAPServerIntegrity\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Domain controller: LDAP server signing requirements to \"Require signing\".","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000320","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Unsigned network traffic is susceptible to man-in-the-middle attacks, where an intruder captures packets between the server and the client and modifies them before forwarding them to the client. In the case of an LDAP server, this means that an attacker could cause a client to make decisions based on false records from the LDAP directory. The risk of an attacker pulling this off can be decreased by implementing strong physical security measures to protect the network infrastructure. Furthermore, implementing Internet Protocol security (IPsec) authentication header mode (AH), which performs mutual authentication and packet integrity for Internet Protocol (IP) traffic, can make all types of man-in-the-middle attacks extremely difficult.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 domain controllers must require LDAP access signing.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254416","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254416","rule_id_src":"SV-254416r958908_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45D971-6E2B-1014-8B33-BF9B30D4DBA8","group_id_src":"V-254416","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254416r958908"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254417","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RefusePasswordChange\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Domain controller: Refuse machine account password changes to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000330","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Enabling this setting on all domain controllers in a domain prevents domain members from changing their computer account passwords. If these passwords are weak or compromised, the inability to change them may leave these computers vulnerable.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 domain controllers must be configured to allow reset of machine account passwords.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254417","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254417","rule_id_src":"SV-254417r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45DD94-6E2B-1014-8F5A-FFA9B2B45FB6","group_id_src":"V-254417","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254417r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254418","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Access this computer from the network\" right, this is a finding.\n\n- Administrators\n- Authenticated Users\n- Enterprise Domain Controllers\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeNetworkLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\nS-1-5-11 (Authenticated Users)\nS-1-5-9 (Enterprise Domain Controllers)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Access this computer from the network to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators\n- Authenticated Users\n- Enterprise Domain Controllers","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000340","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access this computer from the network\" right may access resources on the system, and this right must be limited to those requiring it.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254418","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254418","rule_id_src":"SV-254418r1137691_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45E431-6E2B-1014-B805-FC6FAD6560E6","group_id_src":"V-254418","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254418r1137691"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254419","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Add workstations to domain\" right, this is a finding.\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeMachineAccountPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Add workstations to domain to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000350","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Add workstations to domain\" right may add computers to a domain. This could result in unapproved or incorrectly configured systems being added to a domain.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Add workstations to domain user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group on domain controllers.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254419","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254419","rule_id_src":"SV-254419r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45E9B4-6E2B-1014-A150-8CA9A1E4918C","group_id_src":"V-254419","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254419r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254420","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers, it is NA for other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right, this is a finding.\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeRemoteInteractiveLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000360","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right can access a system through Remote Desktop.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group on domain controllers.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254420","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254420","rule_id_src":"SV-254420r1137691_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45EEF6-6E2B-1014-B379-C5C0AABE87E5","group_id_src":"V-254420","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254420r1137691"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254421","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. A separate version applies to other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Guests Group\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SIDs are not defined for the \"SeDenyNetworkLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nS-1-5-32-546 (Guests)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Deny access to this computer from the network to include the following:\n\n- Guests Group","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000370","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" user right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on from the network.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny access to this computer from the network user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254421","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254421","rule_id_src":"SV-254421r1137691_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45F2FF-6E2B-1014-AB15-B3010E853FB4","group_id_src":"V-254421","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254421r1137691"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254422","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. A separate version applies to other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on as a batch job\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Guests Group\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SID(s) are not defined for the \"SeDenyBatchLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-546 (Guests)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Deny log on as a batch job to include the following:\n\n- Guests Group","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000380","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on as a batch job\" user right defines accounts that are prevented from logging on to the system as a batch job, such as Task Scheduler.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned to prevent unauthenticated access.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny log on as a batch job user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254422","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254422","rule_id_src":"SV-254422r1137691_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45F6C4-6E2B-1014-B16B-D5826FD866B4","group_id_src":"V-254422","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254422r1137691"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254423","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. A separate version applies to other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are defined for the \"Deny log on as a service\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs are granted the \"SeDenyServiceLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Deny log on as a service to include no entries (blank).","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000390","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on as a service\" user right defines accounts that are denied logon as a service.\n\nIncorrect configurations could prevent services from starting and result in a denial of service.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny log on as a service user right must be configured to include no accounts or groups (blank) on domain controllers.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254423","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254423","rule_id_src":"SV-254423r1137691_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45FA80-6E2B-1014-B098-9DC876705C0E","group_id_src":"V-254423","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254423r1137691"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254424","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. A separate version applies to other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on locally\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Guests Group\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SID(s) are not defined for the \"SeDenyInteractiveLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-546 (Guests)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Deny log on locally to include the following:\n\n- Guests Group","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000400","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on locally\" user right defines accounts that are prevented from logging on interactively.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny log on locally user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254424","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254424","rule_id_src":"SV-254424r1137691_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A45FE3B-6E2B-1014-AF72-9C4055B205E6","group_id_src":"V-254424","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254424r1137691"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254425","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000297-GPOS-00115","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. A separate version applies to other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Guests Group\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SID(s) are not defined for the \"SeDenyRemoteInteractiveLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nS-1-5-32-546 (Guests)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services to include the following:\n\n- Guests Group","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000410","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on using Remote Desktop Services.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002314"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254425","title":"SRG-OS-000297-GPOS-00115"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254425","rule_id_src":"SV-254425r958672_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4601F1-6E2B-1014-A4F3-83524F8EB66F","group_id_src":"V-254425","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254425r958672"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254426","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. A separate version applies to other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right, this is a finding.\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeEnableDelegationPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000420","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right allows the \"Trusted for Delegation\" setting to be changed. This could allow unauthorized users to impersonate other users.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group on domain controllers.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254426","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254426","rule_id_src":"SV-254426r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4605BA-6E2B-1014-B8B0-80303CC11D5F","group_id_src":"V-254426","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254426r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254427","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain controllers; it is NA for other systems. \n\nOpen \"Windows PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-ADUser krbtgt -Property PasswordLastSet\".\n\nIf the \"PasswordLastSet\" date is more than 180 days old, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Reset the password for the krbtgt account a least every 180 days. The password must be changed twice to effectively remove the password history. Changing once, waiting for replication to complete and changing again reduces the risk of issues. Changing twice in rapid succession forces clients to re-authenticate (including application services) but is desired if a compromise is suspected.\n\nPowerShell scripts are available to accomplish this such as at the following link:\n\nhttps://gallery.technet.microsoft.com/Reset-the-krbtgt-account-581a9e51\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nSelect \"Advanced Features\" in the \"View\" menu if not previously selected.\n\nSelect the \"Users\" node.\n\nRight-click on the krbtgt account and select \"Reset password\".\n\nEnter a password that meets password complexity requirements.\n\nClear the \"User must change password at next logon\" check box.\n\nThe system will automatically change this to a system-generated complex password.","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000430","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The krbtgt account acts as a service account for the Kerberos Key Distribution Center (KDC) service. The account and password are created when a domain is created and the password is typically not changed. If the krbtgt account is compromised, attackers can create valid Kerberos Ticket Granting Tickets (TGT).\n\nThe password must be changed twice to effectively remove the password history. Changing once, waiting for replication to complete and the amount of time equal to or greater than the maximum Kerberos ticket lifetime, and changing again reduces the risk of issues.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"The password for the krbtgt account on a domain must be reset at least every 180 days.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254427","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254427","rule_id_src":"SV-254427r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4609B2-6E2B-1014-816A-EAE1E9F1C041","group_id_src":"V-254427","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254427r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows2022:questionnaire:37701","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_reviewed","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems. A separate version applies to domain controllers.\n\nOpen \"Computer Management\".\n\nNavigate to \"Groups\" under \"Local Users and Groups\".\n\nReview the local \"Administrators\" group.\n\nOnly administrator groups or accounts responsible for administration of the system may be members of the group.\n\nFor domain-joined member servers, the Domain Admins group must be replaced by a domain member server administrator group.\n\nStandard user accounts must not be members of the local Administrator group.\n\nIf accounts that do not have responsibility for administration of the system are members of the local Administrators group, this is a finding.\n\nIf the built-in Administrator account or other required administrative accounts are found on the system, this is not a finding.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the local \"Administrators\" group to include only administrator groups or accounts responsible for administration of the system.\n\nFor domain-joined member servers, replace the Domain Admins group with a domain member server administrator group. \n\nRemove any standard user accounts.","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000010","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"An account that does not have Administrator duties must not have Administrator rights. Such rights would allow the account to bypass or modify required security restrictions on that machine and make it vulnerable to attack.\n\nSystem administrators must log on to systems using only accounts with the minimum level of authority necessary.\n\nFor domain-joined member servers, the Domain Admins group must be replaced by a domain member server administrator group (see V-243468 in the Active Directory Domain STIG). Restricting highly privileged accounts from the local Administrators group helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nStandard user accounts must not be members of the built-in Administrators group.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-254428, SV-254428r958726, SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must only allow administrators responsible for the member server or standalone or nondomain-joined system to have Administrator rights on the system.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254428","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254428","rule_id_src":"SV-254428r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A461B93-6E2B-1014-B960-C61DD459BB30","group_id_src":"V-254428","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254428r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254429","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to member servers. For domain controllers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\n\nValue Name:  LocalAccountTokenFilterPolicy\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)\n\nThis setting may cause issues with some network scanning tools if local administrative accounts are used remotely. Scans must use domain accounts where possible. If a local administrative account must be used, temporarily enabling the privileged token by configuring the registry value to \"1\" may be required.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; MS Security Guide &gt;&gt; Apply UAC restrictions to local accounts on network logons to \"Enabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \" SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000020","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"A compromised local administrator account can provide means for an attacker to move laterally between domain systems.\n\nWith User Account Control enabled, filtering the privileged token for local administrator accounts will prevent the elevated privileges of these accounts from being used over the network.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 local administrator accounts must have their privileged token filtered to prevent elevated privileges from being used over the network on domain-joined member servers.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254429","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254429","rule_id_src":"SV-254429r958518_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A461F8C-6E2B-1014-8141-CF7DB5A18B9C","group_id_src":"V-254429","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254429r958518"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254430","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to member servers. For domain controllers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnumerateLocalUsers\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Logon &gt;&gt; Enumerate local users on domain-joined computers to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000030","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The username is one part of logon credentials that could be used to gain access to a system. Preventing the enumeration of users limits this information to authorized personnel.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 local users on domain-joined member servers must not be enumerated.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254430","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254430","rule_id_src":"SV-254430r958478_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A462331-6E2B-1014-A7C0-BEB956CD0E46","group_id_src":"V-254430","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254430r958478"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254431","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000379-GPOS-00164","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems, it is NA for domain controllers.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Rpc\\\n\nValue Name:  RestrictRemoteClients\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Remote Procedure Call &gt;&gt; Restrict Unauthenticated RPC clients to \"Enabled\" with \"Authenticated\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000040","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Unauthenticated RPC clients may allow anonymous access to sensitive information. Configuring RPC to restrict unauthenticated RPC clients from connecting to the RPC server will prevent anonymous connections.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Restrict Unauthenticated RPC clients' is set to 'Enabled' and 'Authenticated')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must restrict unauthenticated Remote Procedure Call (RPC) clients from connecting to the RPC server on domain-joined member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001967"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254431","title":"SRG-OS-000379-GPOS-00164"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254431","rule_id_src":"SV-254431r971545_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A462807-6E2B-1014-918C-EBA49A795396","group_id_src":"V-254431","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254431r971545"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254432","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to member servers. For domain controllers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name:  CachedLogonsCount\n\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  4 (or less)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Interactive Logon: Number of previous logons to cache (in case Domain Controller is not available) to \"4\" logons or less.","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000050","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The default Windows configuration caches the last logon credentials for users who log on interactively to a system. This feature is provided for system availability reasons, such as the user's machine being disconnected from the network or domain controllers being unavailable. Even though the credential cache is well protected, if a system is attacked, an unauthorized individual may isolate the password to a domain user account using a password-cracking program and gain access to the domain.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must limit the caching of logon credentials to four or less on domain-joined member servers.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254432","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254432","rule_id_src":"SV-254432r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A462C5E-6E2B-1014-B53E-E30FD153F0EC","group_id_src":"V-254432","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254432r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254433","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems; it is NA for domain controllers.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictRemoteSAM\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: O:BAG:BAD:(A;;RC;;;BA)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Navigate to the policy Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Network access: Restrict clients allowed to make remote calls to SAM. \n\nSelect \"Edit Security\" to configure the \"Security descriptor:\".\n\nAdd \"Administrators\" in \"Group or user names:\" if it is not already listed (this is the default).\n\nSelect \"Administrators\" in \"Group or user names:\".\n\nSelect \"Allow\" for \"Remote Access\" in \"Permissions for \"Administrators\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nThe \"Security descriptor:\" must be populated with \"O:BAG:BAD:(A;;RC;;;BA) for the policy to be enforced.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding. Vendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right. The requirement must be documented and approved by the information system security officer (ISSO).","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000060","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The Windows SAM stores users' passwords. Restricting Remote Procedure Call (RPC) connections to the SAM to Administrators helps protect those credentials.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Allow Administrators group to make remote calls to SAM)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must restrict remote calls to the Security Account Manager (SAM) to Administrators on domain-joined member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254433","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254433","rule_id_src":"SV-254433r1106522_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A463017-6E2B-1014-BC1D-C16CBE1D20B7","group_id_src":"V-254433","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254433r1106522"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254434","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems. A separate version applies to domain controllers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Access this computer from the network\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n- Authenticated Users\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeNetworkLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\nS-1-5-11 (Authenticated Users)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Access this computer from the network to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators\n- Authenticated Users","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000070","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access this computer from the network\" user right may access resources on the system, and this right must be limited to those requiring it.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The 'Access this computer from the network to include only the following accounts or groups' user right is assigned only to Administrators and Authenticated Users)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Access this computer from the network user right must only be assigned to the Administrators and Authenticated Users groups on domain-joined member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254434","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254434","rule_id_src":"SV-254434r1137691_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4633F2-6E2B-1014-920E-97D04E649F77","group_id_src":"V-254434","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254434r1137691"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254435","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems. A separate version applies to domain controllers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\n- Enterprise Admins group\n- Domain Admins group\n- \"Local account and member of Administrators group\" or \"Local account\" (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\n- Guests group\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SIDs are not defined for the \"SeDenyNetworkLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nS-1-5-root domain-519 (Enterprise Admins)\nS-1-5-domain-512 (Domain Admins)\nS-1-5-114 (\"Local account and member of Administrators group\") or S-1-5-113 (\"Local account\")\n\nAll Systems:\nS-1-5-32-546 (Guests)\n\nNote: These are built-in security groups. \"Local account\" is more restrictive but may cause issues on servers such as systems that provide failover clustering.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Deny access to this computer from the network to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\n- Enterprise Admins group\n- Domain Admins group\n- \"Local account and member of Administrators group\" or \"Local account\" (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\n- Guests group\n\nNote: These are built-in security groups. \"Local account\" is more restrictive but may cause issues on servers such as systems that provide failover clustering.","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000080","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" user right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on from the network.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower-trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks, which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nLocal accounts on domain-joined systems must also be assigned this right to decrease the risk of lateral movement resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :         false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :           false (Deny access to this computer from the network - Local account)\nResult Analysis :                Security Principle Not Found: '^(?i)(NT AUTHORITY\\\\)?Local account$'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :           false (Deny access to this computer from the network - Local account and member of Administrators group)\nResult Analysis :                Security Principle Not Found: '^(?i)(NT AUTHORITY\\\\)?Local account and member of Administrators group$'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :         false (Deny access to this computer from the network - Domain Admins)\nResult Analysis :              Security Principle Not Found: '^(?i)(.+\\\\)?Domain Admins$'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :         false (Deny access to this computer from the network - Enterprise Admins)\nResult Analysis :              Security Principle Not Found: '^(?i)(.+\\\\)?Enterprise Admins$'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nCriteria        :         false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :           false (The system is a Windows Domain Member Server)\nResult Analysis :                domainrole = '2' failed test of 'equals' compared to '3' \nCriteria        :       true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :         true (The system is a Windows Standalone Server)\nTest            :     false (Deny access to this computer from the network - Guests)\nResult Analysis :          sedenynetworklogonright : Guests = '0' failed test of 'equals' compared to '1' \n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny access to this computer from the network user right on domain-joined member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and local accounts and from unauthenticated access on all systems.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254435","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254435","rule_id_src":"SV-254435r1137691_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4637F5-6E2B-1014-8F3C-96C946E2840D","group_id_src":"V-254435","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254435r1137691"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254436","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems. A separate version applies to domain controllers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on as a batch job\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\n- Enterprise Admins Group\n- Domain Admins Group\n\nAll Systems:\n- Guests Group\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SIDs are not defined for the \"SeDenyBatchLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nS-1-5-root domain-519 (Enterprise Admins)\nS-1-5-domain-512 (Domain Admins)\n\nAll Systems:\nS-1-5-32-546 (Guests)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Deny log on as a batch job to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\n- Enterprise Admins Group\n- Domain Admins Group\n\nAll Systems:\n- Guests Group","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000090","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on as a batch job\" user right defines accounts that are prevented from logging on to the system as a batch job, such as Task Scheduler.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower-trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks, which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned to prevent unauthenticated access.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (Deny log on as a batch job is assigned to Guests)\nCriteria        :       true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :         true (The system is a Windows Standalone Server)\nCriteria        :     false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (Deny log on as a batch job is assigned to Guests)\nTest            :       false (The 'Deny log on as a batch job' user right is assigned to the Domain Admin groups.)\nTest            :       false (The 'Deny log on as a batch job' user right is assigned to the Enterprise Admin groups.)\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :         false (The system is a Windows Domain Member Server)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny log on as a batch job user right on domain-joined member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and from unauthenticated access on all systems.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254436","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254436","rule_id_src":"SV-254436r1137691_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A463BB8-6E2B-1014-9EA2-F0D3826872AD","group_id_src":"V-254436","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254436r1137691"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254437","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to member servers. A separate version applies to domain controllers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on as a service\" user right on domain-joined systems, this is a finding:\n\n- Enterprise Admins Group\n- Domain Admins Group\n\nIf any accounts or groups are defined for the \"Deny log on as a service\" user right on nondomain-joined systems, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SIDs are not defined for the \"SeDenyServiceLogonRight\" user right on domain-joined systems, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-root domain-519 (Enterprise Admins)\nS-1-5-domain-512 (Domain Admins)\n\nIf any SIDs are defined for the user right on nondomain-joined systems, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Deny log on as a service to include the following:\n\nDomain systems:\n- Enterprise Admins Group\n- Domain Admins Group","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000100","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on as a service\" user right defines accounts that are denied logon as a service.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower-trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks, which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nIncorrect configurations could prevent services from starting and result in a denial of service.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny log on as a service user right on domain-joined member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts. No other groups or accounts must be assigned this right.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254437","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254437","rule_id_src":"SV-254437r1137691_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A463F82-6E2B-1014-8FD0-D90BCC77AA19","group_id_src":"V-254437","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254437r1137691"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254438","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems. A separate version applies to domain controllers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on locally\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\n- Enterprise Admins Group\n- Domain Admins Group\n\nAll Systems:\n- Guests Group\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SIDs are not defined for the \"SeDenyInteractiveLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nS-1-5-root domain-519 (Enterprise Admins)\nS-1-5-domain-512 (Domain Admins)\n\nAll Systems:\nS-1-5-32-546 (Guests)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Deny log on locally to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\n- Enterprise Admins Group\n- Domain Admins Group\n\nAll Systems:\n- Guests Group","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000110","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on locally\" user right defines accounts that are prevented from logging on interactively.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower-trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks, which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :         false (Deny log on locally - Domain Admins)\nResult Analysis :              Security Principle Not Found: '^(?i)(.+\\\\)?Domain Admins$'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :         false (Deny log on as a locally - Enterprise Admins)\nResult Analysis :              Security Principle Not Found: '^(?i)(.+\\\\)?Enterprise Admins$'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :       true (System is not a member of a domain)\nTest            :     false (Deny log on locally - Guests)\nResult Analysis :          sedenyinteractivelogonright : Guests = '0' failed test of 'equals' compared to '1' \n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny log on locally user right on domain-joined member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and from unauthenticated access on all systems.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254438","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254438","rule_id_src":"SV-254438r1137691_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46433E-6E2B-1014-8191-A96D5C16ECF8","group_id_src":"V-254438","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254438r1137691"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254439","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000297-GPOS-00115","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems. A separate version applies to domain controllers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\n- Enterprise Admins group\n- Domain Admins group\n- Local account (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\n- Guests group\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SIDs are not defined for the \"SeDenyRemoteInteractiveLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nS-1-5-root domain-519 (Enterprise Admins)\nS-1-5-domain-512 (Domain Admins)\nS-1-5-113 (\"Local account\")\n\nAll Systems:\nS-1-5-32-546 (Guests)\n\nNote: \"Local account\" is referring to the Windows built-in security group.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\n- Enterprise Admins group\n- Domain Admins group\n- Local account (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\n- Guests group\n\nNote: \"Local account\" is referring to the Windows built-in security group.","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000120","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on using Remote Desktop Services.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower-trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks, which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nLocal accounts on domain-joined systems must also be assigned this right to decrease the risk of lateral movement resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :         false (Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services - Domain Admins)\nTest            :         false (Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services - Enterprise Admins)\nTest            :         false (Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services - Local account)\nTest            :         false (System is a Windows non-DC domain-joined system)\nTest            :       true (The system is a Windows Standalone Workstation or Server)\nTest            :     true (Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services - Guests)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services user right on domain-joined member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and all local accounts and from unauthenticated access on all systems.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002314"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254439","title":"SRG-OS-000297-GPOS-00115"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254439","rule_id_src":"SV-254439r958672_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A464707-6E2B-1014-B221-F1432BBAC96A","group_id_src":"V-254439","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254439r958672"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254440","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems. A separate version applies to domain controllers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs are granted the \"SeEnableDelegationPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000130","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right allows the \"Trusted for Delegation\" setting to be changed. This could allow unauthorized users to impersonate other users.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation - None)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts on domain-joined member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254440","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254440","rule_id_src":"SV-254440r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A464AB7-6E2B-1014-8DE8-BD6A207B7FBE","group_id_src":"V-254440","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254440r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254441","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"For domain controllers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter the following:\n\n\"Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_DeviceGuard -Namespace root\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\"\n\nIf \"SecurityServicesRunning\" does not include a value of \"1\" (e.g., \"{1, 2}\"), this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", verify the following:\n\nIf \"Device Guard Security Services Running\" does not list \"Credential Guard\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy settings referenced in the Fix section will configure the following registry value. However, due to hardware requirements, the registry value alone does not ensure proper function.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\\\n\nValue Name: LsaCfgFlags\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) (Enabled with UEFI lock)\n\nA Microsoft article on Credential Guard system requirement can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/security/identity-protection/credential-guard/credential-guard-requirements","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Device Guard &gt;&gt; Turn On Virtualization Based Security to \"Enabled\" with \"Enabled with UEFI lock\" selected for \"Credential Guard Configuration\".\n\nA Microsoft article on Credential Guard system requirement can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/security/identity-protection/credential-guard/credential-guard-requirements\n\nSeverity Override Guidance: The AO can allow the severity override if they have reviewed the overall protection provided to the affected servers that are not capable of complying with the Credential Guard requirement. Items that must be reviewed/considered for compliance or mitigation for non-Credential Guard compliance are:\n\nThe use of Microsoft Local Administrator Password Solution (LAPS) or similar products to control different local administrative passwords for all affected servers. This is to include a strict password change requirement (60 days or less).\n....\nStrict separation of roles and duties. Server administrator credentials cannot be used on Windows 10 desktop to administer it. Documentation of all exceptions must be supplied.\n....\nUse of a Privileged Access Workstation (PAW) and adherence to the Clean Source principle for administering affected servers. \n....\nBoundary Protection that is currently in place to protect from vulnerabilities in the network/servers.\n....\nWindows Defender rule block credential stealing from LSASS.exe is applied. This rule can only be applied if Windows Defender is in use.\n....\nThe overall number of vulnerabilities that are unmitigated on the network/servers.","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000140","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Credential Guard uses virtualization-based security to protect data that could be used in credential theft attacks if compromised. This authentication information, which was stored in the Local Security Authority (LSA) in previous versions of Windows, is isolated from the rest of operating system and can only be accessed by privileged system software.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be running Credential Guard on domain-joined member servers.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254441","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254441","rule_id_src":"SV-254441r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A464E88-6E2B-1014-B55E-BD051B0323FD","group_id_src":"V-254441","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254441r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254442","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","comments":null,"check_content":"The certificates and thumbprints referenced below apply to unclassified systems; refer to PKE documentation for other networks.\n\nOpen \"Windows PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\root | Where Subject -Like \"*DoD*\" | FL Subject, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\" and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding. \n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: D73CA91102A2204A36459ED32213B467D7CE97FB\nNotAfter: 12/30/2029\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 4, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: B8269F25DBD937ECAFD4C35A9838571723F2D026\nNotAfter: 7/25/2032\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 5, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 4ECB5CC3095670454DA1CBD410FC921F46B8564B\nNotAfter: 6/14/2041\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 6, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US \nThumbprint : D37ECF61C0B4ED88681EF3630C4E2FC787B37AEF\nNotAfter: 1/24/2053 11:36:17 AM\n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\" and click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\" and click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\" and click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to \"Trusted Root Certification Authorities &gt;&gt; Certificates\".\n\nFor each of the DoD Root CA certificates noted below:\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the DoD Root CA certificates below are not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nDoD Root CA 3\nThumbprint: D73CA91102A2204A36459ED32213B467D7CE97FB\nValid to: Sunday, December 30, 2029\n\nDoD Root CA 4\nThumbprint: B8269F25DBD937ECAFD4C35A9838571723F2D026\nValid to: Sunday, July 25, 2032\n\nDoD Root CA 5\nThumbprint: 4ECB5CC3095670454DA1CBD410FC921F46B8564B\nValid to: Friday, June 14, 2041\n\nDoD Root CA 6\nThumbprint: D37ECF61C0B4ED88681EF3630C4E2FC787B37AEFB\nValid to: Friday, January 24, 2053","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Install the DoD Root CA certificates:\n\nDoD Root CA 3\nDoD Root CA 4\nDoD Root CA 5\nDoD Root CA 6\n\nThe InstallRoot tool is available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. Certificate bundles published by the PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","rule_version":"WN22-PK-000010","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"To ensure secure DoD websites and DoD-signed code are properly validated, the system must trust the DoD Root CAs. The DoD root certificates will ensure that the trust chain is established for server certificates issued from the DoD CAs.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034, SRG-OS-000403-GPOS-00182","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The DoD Root CA 3 Certificate expiring 12/30/2029 is installed into the Trusted Root Store.)\nTest            :     false (The DoD Root CA 4 Certificate expiring 7/25/2032 is installed into the Trusted Root Store.)\nResult Analysis :          Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :     false (The DoD Root CA 5 Certificate expiring 6/14/2041 is installed into the Trusted Root Store.)\nResult Analysis :          Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :     false (The DoD Root CA 6 Certificate expiring 1/24/2053 is installed into the Trusted Root Store.)\nResult Analysis :          Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have the DoD Root Certificate Authority (CA) certificates installed in the Trusted Root Store.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254442","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254442","rule_id_src":"SV-254442r958448_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A465289-6E2B-1014-850C-9C7E4012B983","group_id_src":"V-254442","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254442r958448"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254443","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","comments":null,"check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. It is NA for others.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\disallowed | Where {$_.Issuer -Like \"*DoD Interoperability*\" -and $_.Subject -Like \"*DoD*\"} | FL Subject, Issuer, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\", \"Issuer\", and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding. \n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=DoD Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\nNotAfter: 11/16/2024 09:57:16 AM\n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\" and click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\" and click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\" and click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to Untrusted Certificates &gt;&gt; Certificates.\n\nFor each certificate with \"DoD Root CA...\" under \"Issued To\" and \"DoD Interoperability Root CA...\" under \"Issued By\":\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the certificates below are not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nIssued To: DoD Root CA 3\nIssued By: DoD Interoperability Root CA 2\nThumbprint: 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\nValid to: Wednesday, November 16, 2024","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Install the DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates on unclassified systems.\n\nIssued To - Issued By - Thumbprint\n\nDoD Root CA 3- DoD Interoperability Root CA 2 - 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\n\nAdministrators must run the Federal Bridge Certification Authority (FBCA) Cross-Certificate Removal Tool once as an administrator and once as the current user.\n\nThe FBCA Cross-Certificate Remover Tool and User Guide are available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. Certificate bundles published by the PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","rule_version":"WN22-PK-000020","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"To ensure users do not experience denial of service when performing certificate-based authentication to DoD websites due to the system chaining to a root other than DoD Root CAs, the DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificate Store. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034, SRG-OS-000403-GPOS-00182","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (DoD Interoperability Root CA 2 certificate expiring 11/16/2024 is installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store)\nResult Analysis :          Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have the DoD Interoperability Root Certificate Authority (CA) cross-certificates installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254443","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254443","rule_id_src":"SV-254443r958448_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A465684-6E2B-1014-A082-AF578F807122","group_id_src":"V-254443","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254443r958448"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254444","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","comments":null,"check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. It is NA for others.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\disallowed | Where Issuer -Like \"*CCEB Interoperability*\" | FL Subject, Issuer, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\", \"Issuer\", and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding.\n\nSubject: CN=DOD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\nNotAfter: 7/18/2025 9:56:22 AM\n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\" and click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\" and click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\" and click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to Untrusted Certificates &gt;&gt; Certificates.\n\nFor each certificate with \"US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA ...\" under \"Issued By\":\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the certificate below is not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nIssued To: DOD Root CA 3\nIssued By: US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2\nThumbprint: 9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\nNotAfter: 7/18/2025\nIssued to: DOD Root CA 6\nIssued By: US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2\nThumbprint: D471CA32F7A692CE6CBB6196BD3377FE4DBCD106\nNotAfter: 7/18/2026","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Install the US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificate on unclassified systems.\n\nIssued To - Issued By - Thumbprint\n\nDOD Root CA 3 - US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2 - 9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8 \nDOD Root CA 6 -US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2 - D471CA32F7A692CE6CBB6196BD3377FE4DBCD106\n\nAdministrators must run the Federal Bridge Certification Authority (FBCA) Cross-Certificate Removal Tool once as an administrator and once as the current user.\n\nThe FBCA Cross-Certificate Remover Tool and User Guide are available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","rule_version":"WN22-PK-000030","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"To ensure users do not experience denial of service when performing certificate-based authentication to DOD websites due to the system chaining to a root other than DOD Root CAs, the US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificate Store. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034, SRG-OS-000403-GPOS-00182","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2 cross-certificate expiring 7/18/2025 is installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store)\nResult Analysis :          Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :     false (US DoD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2 cross-certificate expiring 7/18/2026 is installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store)\nResult Analysis :          Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have the US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254444","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254444","rule_id_src":"SV-254444r1081077_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A465A62-6E2B-1014-988D-F3BEE7DD6270","group_id_src":"V-254444","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254444r1081077"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254445","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000121-GPOS-00062","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Guest account status\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"EnableGuestAccount\" equals \"1\" in the file, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Accounts: Guest account status to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000010","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"A system faces an increased vulnerability threat if the built-in guest account is not disabled. This is a known account that exists on all Windows systems and cannot be deleted. This account is initialized during the installation of the operating system with no password assigned.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Windows built-in guest account must be disabled.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have the built-in guest account disabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000804"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254445","title":"SRG-OS-000121-GPOS-00062"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254445","rule_id_src":"SV-254445r958504_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A465E1F-6E2B-1014-935B-EAD552F2D647","group_id_src":"V-254445","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254445r958504"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254446","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: LimitBlankPasswordUse\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Accounts: Limit local account use of blank passwords to console logon only to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000020","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"An account without a password can allow unauthorized access to a system as only the username would be required. Password policies must prevent accounts with blank passwords from existing on a system. However, if a local account with a blank password does exist, enabling this setting will prevent network access, limiting the account to local console logon only.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Accounts: Limit local account use of blank passwords to console logon only' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent local accounts with blank passwords from being used from the network.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254446","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254446","rule_id_src":"SV-254446r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46619B-6E2B-1014-B393-D8DBC0A60820","group_id_src":"V-254446","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254446r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254447","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Rename administrator account\" is not set to a value other than \"Administrator\", this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"NewAdministratorName\" is not something other than \"Administrator\" in the file, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Accounts: Rename administrator account to a name other than \"Administrator\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000030","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The built-in administrator account is a well-known account subject to attack. Renaming this account to an unidentified name improves the protection of this account and the system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Windows built-in administrator account must be renamed.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 built-in administrator account must be renamed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254447","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254447","rule_id_src":"SV-254447r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A466507-6E2B-1014-B4B6-8EFD1B222C3B","group_id_src":"V-254447","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254447r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254448","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Rename guest account\" is not set to a value other than \"Guest\", this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"NewGuestName\" is not something other than \"Guest\" in the file, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Accounts: Rename guest account to a name other than \"Guest\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000040","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The built-in guest account is a well-known user account on all Windows systems and, as initially installed, does not require a password. This can allow access to system resources by unauthorized users. Renaming this account to an unidentified name improves the protection of this account and the system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Windows built-in guest account must be renamed.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 built-in guest account must be renamed.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254448","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254448","rule_id_src":"SV-254448r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46687C-6E2B-1014-90D9-B220E9B25EDF","group_id_src":"V-254448","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254448r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254449","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: SCENoApplyLegacyAuditPolicy\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000050","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. This setting allows administrators to enable more precise auditing capabilities.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Audit policy using subcategories is enabled.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254449","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254449","rule_id_src":"SV-254449r958442_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A466BEB-6E2B-1014-8EFF-BFBFCF1D67CE","group_id_src":"V-254449","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254449r958442"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254450","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSignOrSeal\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Domain member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always) to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000060","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but not all information is encrypted. If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be encrypted and signed.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Domain member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always)' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 setting Domain member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always) must be configured to Enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254450","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254450","rule_id_src":"SV-254450r958908_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A466F79-6E2B-1014-894B-A7CE71412213","group_id_src":"V-254450","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254450r958908"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254451","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SealSecureChannel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Domain member: Digitally encrypt secure channel data (when possible) to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000070","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but not all information is encrypted. If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be encrypted.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Domain member: Digitally encrypt secure channel data (when possible)' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 setting Domain member: Digitally encrypt secure channel data (when possible) must be configured to Enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254451","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254451","rule_id_src":"SV-254451r958908_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4672FC-6E2B-1014-B6DB-E93F00298A51","group_id_src":"V-254451","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254451r958908"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254452","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SignSecureChannel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Domain member: Digitally sign secure channel data (when possible) to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000080","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but the channel is not integrity checked. If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be signed.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Outgoing secure channel traffic is signed.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 setting Domain member: Digitally sign secure channel data (when possible) must be configured to Enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254452","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254452","rule_id_src":"SV-254452r958908_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4677D1-6E2B-1014-A8C1-BA852AF97750","group_id_src":"V-254452","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254452r958908"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254453","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000379-GPOS-00164","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisablePasswordChange\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Domain member: Disable machine account password changes to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000090","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Computer account passwords are changed automatically on a regular basis. Disabling automatic password changes can make the system more vulnerable to malicious access. Frequent password changes can be a significant safeguard for the system. A new password for the computer account will be generated every 30 days.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Domain member: Disable machine account password changes' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 computer account password must not be prevented from being reset.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001967"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254453","title":"SRG-OS-000379-GPOS-00164"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254453","rule_id_src":"SV-254453r971545_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A467BD5-6E2B-1014-B37D-EF85172A24B0","group_id_src":"V-254453","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254453r971545"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254454","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"This is the default configuration for this setting (30 days).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: MaximumPasswordAge\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x0000001e (30) (or less, but not 0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"This is the default configuration for this setting (30 days).\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Domain member: Maximum machine account password age to \"30\" or less (excluding \"0\", which is unacceptable).","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000100","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Computer account passwords are changed automatically on a regular basis. This setting controls the maximum password age that a machine account may have. This must be set to no more than 30 days, ensuring the machine changes its password monthly.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Domain member: Maximum machine account password age' is set to 30 or less (but not 0).)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 maximum age for machine account passwords must be configured to 30 days or less.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254454","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254454","rule_id_src":"SV-254454r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A467F72-6E2B-1014-8171-C604B8460D1F","group_id_src":"V-254454","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254454r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254455","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireStrongKey\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n \nThis setting may prevent a system from being joined to a domain if not configured consistently between systems.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Domain member: Require strong (Windows 2000 or Later) session key to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000110","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"A computer connecting to a domain controller will establish a secure channel. The secure channel connection may be subject to compromise, such as hijacking or eavesdropping, if strong session keys are not used to establish the connection. Requiring strong session keys enforces 128-bit encryption between systems.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Domain member: Require strong (Windows 2000 or Later) session key' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to require a strong session key.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254455","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254455","rule_id_src":"SV-254455r958908_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4682F8-6E2B-1014-9ECB-DE0F9FBE3BAA","group_id_src":"V-254455","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254455r958908"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254456","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000028-GPOS-00009","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: InactivityTimeoutSecs\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000384 (900) (or less, excluding \"0\" which is effectively disabled)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Interactive logon: Machine inactivity limit to \"900\" seconds or less, excluding \"0\" which is effectively disabled.","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000120","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and must be locked when unattended. The screen saver must be set at a maximum of 15 minutes and be password protected. This protects critical and sensitive data from exposure to unauthorized personnel with physical access to the computer.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000028-GPOS-00009, SRG-OS-000029-GPOS-00010, SRG-OS-000031-GPOS-00012","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The machine inactivity limit is set to 15 minutes or less)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 machine inactivity limit must be set to 15 minutes or less, locking the system with the screen saver.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000056","CCI-000057","CCI-000060"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254456","title":"SRG-OS-000028-GPOS-00009"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254456","rule_id_src":"SV-254456r958400_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46868C-6E2B-1014-BC0B-E3E6652AA0B5","group_id_src":"V-254456","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254456r958400"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254457","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LegalNoticeText\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: See message text below\n\nYou are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only.\n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions:\n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations.\n\n-At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS.\n\n-Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose.\n\n-This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interests--not for your personal benefit or privacy.\n\n-Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants. Such communications and work product are private and confidential. See User Agreement for details.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Interactive Logon: Message text for users attempting to log on to the following:\n\nYou are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only.\n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions:\n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations.\n\n-At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS.\n\n-Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose.\n\n-This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interests--not for your personal benefit or privacy.\n\n-Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants. Such communications and work product are private and confidential. See User Agreement for details.","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000130","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Failure to display the logon banner prior to a logon attempt will negate legal proceedings resulting from unauthorized access to system resources.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006, SRG-OS-000024-GPOS-00007, SRG-OS-000228-GPOS-00088","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon - Message Content 1)\nTest            :   true (The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon - Message Content 2)\nTest            :   true (The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon - Message Content 3)\nTest            :   true (The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon - Message Content 4)\nTest            :   true (The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon - Message Content 5)\nTest            :   true (The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon - Message Content 6)\nTest            :   true (The required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon - Message Content 7)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000048","CCI-000050","CCI-001384","CCI-001385","CCI-001386","CCI-001387","CCI-001388"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254457","title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254457","rule_id_src":"SV-254457r958390_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A468BAE-6E2B-1014-A391-C399B9F86CBD","group_id_src":"V-254457","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254457r958390"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254458","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LegalNoticeCaption\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: See message title options below\n\n\"DoD Notice and Consent Banner\", \"US Department of Defense Warning Statement\", or an organization-defined equivalent. \n\nIf an organization-defined title is used, it can in no case contravene or modify the language of the banner text required in WN22-SO-000150.\n\nAutomated tools may only search for the titles defined above. If an organization-defined title is used, a manual review will be required.","severity":"low","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Interactive Logon: Message title for users attempting to log on to \"DoD Notice and Consent Banner\", \"US Department of Defense Warning Statement\", or an organization-defined equivalent. \n\nIf an organization-defined title is used, it can in no case contravene or modify the language of the message text required in WN22-SO-000150.","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000140","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Failure to display the logon banner prior to a logon attempt will negate legal proceedings resulting from unauthorized access to system resources.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006, SRG-OS-000228-GPOS-00088","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (The Windows dialog box title for the legal banner must be configured. Title Option 1)\nTest            :   true (The Windows dialog box title for the legal banner must be configured. Title Option 2)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 title for legal banner dialog box must be configured with the appropriate text.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000048","CCI-001384","CCI-001385","CCI-001386","CCI-001387","CCI-001388"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254458","title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254458","rule_id_src":"SV-254458r958390_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A468FB5-6E2B-1014-919E-967441F1296F","group_id_src":"V-254458","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254458r958390"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254459","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n \nValue Name: scremoveoption\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: 1 (Lock Workstation) or 2 (Force Logoff)\n\nIf configuring this on servers causes issues, such as terminating users' remote sessions, and the organization has a policy in place that any other sessions on the servers, such as administrative console logons, are manually locked or logged off when unattended or not in use, this would be acceptable. This must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Interactive logon: Smart card removal behavior to \"Lock Workstation\" or \"Force Logoff\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000150","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and must be locked. Configuring a system to lock when a smart card is removed will ensure the system is inaccessible when unattended.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Interactive logon: Smart card removal behavior' is set to 'Lock Workstation' or 'Force Logoff')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Smart Card removal option must be configured to Force Logoff or Lock Workstation.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254459","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254459","rule_id_src":"SV-254459r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A469366-6E2B-1014-B24C-E39D09CC55DF","group_id_src":"V-254459","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254459r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254460","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Microsoft network client: Digitally sign communications (always) to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000160","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The server message block (SMB) protocol provides the basis for many network operations. Digitally signed SMB packets aid in preventing man-in-the-middle attacks. If this policy is enabled, the SMB client will only communicate with an SMB server that performs SMB packet signing.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Microsoft Network Client: Digitally sign communications (always)' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 setting Microsoft network client: Digitally sign communications (always) must be configured to Enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254460","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254460","rule_id_src":"SV-254460r958908_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4696F4-6E2B-1014-85B3-8ADE81364E6F","group_id_src":"V-254460","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254460r958908"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254461","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Microsoft network client: Digitally sign communications (if server agrees) to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000170","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The server message block (SMB) protocol provides the basis for many network operations. If this policy is enabled, the SMB client will request packet signing when communicating with an SMB server that is enabled or required to perform SMB packet signing.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Microsoft network client: Digitally sign communications (if server agrees)' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 setting Microsoft network client: Digitally sign communications (if server agrees) must be configured to Enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254461","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254461","rule_id_src":"SV-254461r958908_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A469A79-6E2B-1014-8958-80C1900D882A","group_id_src":"V-254461","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254461r958908"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254462","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000074-GPOS-00042","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  EnablePlainTextPassword\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Microsoft Network Client: Send unencrypted password to third-party SMB servers to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000180","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Some non-Microsoft SMB servers only support unencrypted (plain-text) password authentication. Sending plain-text passwords across the network when authenticating to an SMB server reduces the overall security of the environment. Check with the vendor of the SMB server to determine if there is a way to support encrypted password authentication.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Microsoft Network Client: Send unencrypted password to connect to third-party SMB servers' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 unencrypted passwords must not be sent to third-party Server Message Block (SMB) servers.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000197"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254462","title":"SRG-OS-000074-GPOS-00042"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254462","rule_id_src":"SV-254462r987796_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A469E00-6E2B-1014-AA49-C68518B68623","group_id_src":"V-254462","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254462r987796"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254463","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Microsoft network server: Digitally sign communications (always) to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000190","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The server message block (SMB) protocol provides the basis for many network operations. Digitally signed SMB packets aid in preventing man-in-the-middle attacks. If this policy is enabled, the SMB server will only communicate with an SMB client that performs SMB packet signing.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false ('Microsoft network server: Digitally sign communications (always)' is set to 'Enabled')\nResult Analysis :          HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\RequireSecuritySignature\\value = '0' failed test of 'equals' compared to '1' \n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 setting Microsoft network server: Digitally sign communications (always) must be configured to Enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254463","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254463","rule_id_src":"SV-254463r958908_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46A185-6E2B-1014-9387-9F8EBC2D2BA5","group_id_src":"V-254463","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254463r958908"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254464","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Microsoft network server: Digitally sign communications (if client agrees) to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000200","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The server message block (SMB) protocol provides the basis for many network operations. Digitally signed SMB packets aid in preventing man-in-the-middle attacks. If this policy is enabled, the SMB server will negotiate SMB packet signing as requested by the client.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false ('Microsoft network server: Digitally sign communications (if client agrees)' is set to 'Enabled')\nResult Analysis :          HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\EnableSecuritySignature\\value = '0' failed test of 'equals' compared to '1' \n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 setting Microsoft network server: Digitally sign communications (if client agrees) must be configured to Enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254464","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254464","rule_id_src":"SV-254464r958908_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46A512-6E2B-1014-848E-B23F92AA750D","group_id_src":"V-254464","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254464r958908"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254465","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Network access: Allow anonymous SID/Name translation\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Network access: Allow anonymous SID/Name translation to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000210","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Allowing anonymous SID/Name translation can provide sensitive information for accessing a system. Only authorized users must be able to perform such translations.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Network access: Allow anonymous SID/Name translation is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must not allow anonymous SID/Name translation.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254465","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254465","rule_id_src":"SV-254465r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46A8F8-6E2B-1014-B865-C5B06B086B10","group_id_src":"V-254465","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254465r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254466","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictAnonymousSAM\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000220","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts allows anonymous logon users (null session connections) to list all accounts names, thus providing a list of potential points to attack the system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must not allow anonymous enumeration of Security Account Manager (SAM) accounts.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254466","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254466","rule_id_src":"SV-254466r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46AC93-6E2B-1014-A08D-887EBCF1F129","group_id_src":"V-254466","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254466r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254467","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictAnonymous\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts and shares to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000230","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Allowing anonymous logon users (null session connections) to list all account names and enumerate all shared resources can provide a map of potential points to attack the system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Network access: Do not allow anonymous enumeration of SAM accounts and shares' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must not allow anonymous enumeration of shares.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001090"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254467","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254467","rule_id_src":"SV-254467r1137695_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46B58E-6E2B-1014-93BC-C2C6076EA2C5","group_id_src":"V-254467","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254467r1137695"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254468","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: EveryoneIncludesAnonymous\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000240","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Access by anonymous users must be restricted. If this setting is enabled, anonymous users have the same rights and permissions as the built-in Everyone group. Anonymous users must not have these permissions or rights.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to prevent anonymous users from having the same permissions as the Everyone group.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254468","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254468","rule_id_src":"SV-254468r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46BBAD-6E2B-1014-932D-DAE454424FF9","group_id_src":"V-254468","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254468r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254469","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanManServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictNullSessAccess\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Network access: Restrict anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000250","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Allowing anonymous access to named pipes or shares provides the potential for unauthorized system access. This setting restricts access to those defined in \"Network access: Named Pipes that can be accessed anonymously\" and \"Network access: Shares that can be accessed anonymously\", both of which must be blank under other requirements.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Network access: Restrict anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must restrict anonymous access to Named Pipes and Shares.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001090"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254469","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254469","rule_id_src":"SV-254469r1137695_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46BFE4-6E2B-1014-B611-A834A3DD954F","group_id_src":"V-254469","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254469r1137695"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254470","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\\n\nValue Name: UseMachineId\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Network security: Allow Local System to use computer identity for NTLM to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000260","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Services using Local System that use Negotiate when reverting to NTLM authentication may gain unauthorized access if allowed to authenticate anonymously versus using the computer identity.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Network security: Allow Local System to use computer identity for NTLM' is set to 'Enabled'.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 services using Local System that use Negotiate when reverting to NTLM authentication must use the computer identity instead of authenticating anonymously.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254470","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254470","rule_id_src":"SV-254470r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46C3DB-6E2B-1014-A52C-F340E0CB9567","group_id_src":"V-254470","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254470r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254471","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: allownullsessionfallback\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Network security: Allow LocalSystem NULL session fallback to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000270","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"NTLM sessions that are allowed to fall back to Null (unauthenticated) sessions may gain unauthorized access.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Network security: Allow LocalSystem NULL session fallback' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent NTLM from falling back to a Null session.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254471","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254471","rule_id_src":"SV-254471r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46C7D4-6E2B-1014-9E33-EC42835F466B","group_id_src":"V-254471","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254471r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254472","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\LSA\\pku2u\\\n\nValue Name: AllowOnlineID\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Network security: Allow PKU2U authentication requests to this computer to use online identities to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000280","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"PKU2U is a peer-to-peer authentication protocol. This setting prevents online identities from authenticating to domain-joined systems. Authentication will be centrally managed with Windows user accounts.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Network Security: Allow PKU2U authentication requests to this computer to use online identities' is set to 'Disabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent PKU2U authentication using online identities.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254472","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254472","rule_id_src":"SV-254472r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46CBDA-6E2B-1014-B704-FC1F96A23CED","group_id_src":"V-254472","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254472r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254473","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Kerberos\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SupportedEncryptionTypes\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x7ffffff8 (2147483640)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Network security: Configure encryption types allowed for Kerberos to \"Enabled\" with only the following selected:\n\nAES128_HMAC_SHA1\nAES256_HMAC_SHA1\nFuture encryption types\n\nNote: Organizations with domain controllers running earlier versions of Windows where RC4 encryption is enabled, selecting \"The other domain supports Kerberos AES Encryption\" on domain trusts, may be required to allow client communication across the trust relationship.","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000290","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Certain encryption types are no longer considered secure. The DES and RC4 encryption suites must not be used for Kerberos encryption.\n\nNote: Organizations with domain controllers running earlier versions of Windows where RC4 encryption is enabled, selecting \"The other domain supports Kerberos AES Encryption\" on domain trusts, may be required to allow client communication across the trust relationship.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Network Security: Configure encryption types allowed for Kerberos' is set to 'Enabled' with 'AES128_HMAC_SHA1', 'AES256_HMAC_SHA1', 'Future encryption types')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Kerberos encryption types must be configured to prevent the use of DES and RC4 encryption suites.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000803"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254473","title":"SRG-OS-000120-GPOS-00061"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254473","rule_id_src":"SV-254473r971535_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46D03E-6E2B-1014-9C12-A25D31F623A2","group_id_src":"V-254473","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254473r971535"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254474","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: NoLMHash\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Network security: Do not store LAN Manager hash value on next password change to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000300","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The LAN Manager hash uses a weak encryption algorithm and there are several tools available that use this hash to retrieve account passwords. This setting controls whether a LAN Manager hash of the password is stored in the SAM the next time the password is changed.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Network security: Do not store LAN Manager hash value on next password change' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to prevent the storage of the LAN Manager hash of passwords.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-004062","CCI-000196"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254474","title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254474","rule_id_src":"SV-254474r1051107_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46D4A8-6E2B-1014-ACD5-FC766C5B0EAA","group_id_src":"V-254474","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254474r1051107"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254475","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: LmCompatibilityLevel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000005 (5)","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Network security: LAN Manager authentication level to \"Send NTLMv2 response only. Refuse LM &amp; NTLM\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000310","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"The Kerberos v5 authentication protocol is the default for authentication of users who are logging on to domain accounts. NTLM, which is less secure, is retained in later Windows versions for compatibility with clients and servers that are running earlier versions of Windows or applications that still use it. It is also used to authenticate logons to standalone or nondomain-joined computers that are running later versions.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Network security: LAN Manager authentication level' is set to 'Send NTLMv2 response only. Refuse LM &amp; NTLM' (Level 5))\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 LAN Manager authentication level must be configured to send NTLMv2 response only and to refuse LM and NTLM.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254475","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254475","rule_id_src":"SV-254475r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46EB75-6E2B-1014-8F76-98525BBD9EAB","group_id_src":"V-254475","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254475r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254476","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LDAP\\\n\nValue Name: LDAPClientIntegrity\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Network security: LDAP client signing requirements to \"Negotiate signing\" at a minimum.","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000320","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting controls the signing requirements for LDAP clients. This must be set to \"Negotiate signing\" or \"Require signing\", depending on the environment and type of LDAP server in use.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Network security: LDAP client signing requirements' is set to 'Negotiate signing' or 'Require signing')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to at least negotiate signing for LDAP client signing.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254476","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254476","rule_id_src":"SV-254476r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46EF92-6E2B-1014-AACB-F8DA354BFFB8","group_id_src":"V-254476","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254476r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254477","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: NTLMMinClientSec\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x20080000 (537395200)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) clients to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\" and \"Require 128-bit encryption\" (all options selected).","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000330","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Microsoft has implemented a variety of security support providers for use with Remote Procedure Call (RPC) sessions. All of the options must be enabled to ensure the maximum security level.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The system is configured to meet the minimum session security requirement for NTLM SSP based clients.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 session security for NTLM SSP-based clients must be configured to require NTLMv2 session security and 128-bit encryption.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254477","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254477","rule_id_src":"SV-254477r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46F319-6E2B-1014-8950-AAF0BF5AA651","group_id_src":"V-254477","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254477r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254478","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\MSV1_0\\\n\nValue Name: NTLMMinServerSec\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x20080000 (537395200)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) servers to \"Require NTLMv2 session security\" and \"Require 128-bit encryption\" (all options selected).","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000340","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Microsoft has implemented a variety of security support providers for use with Remote Procedure Call (RPC) sessions. All of the options must be enabled to ensure the maximum security level.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Network security: Minimum session security for NTLM SSP based (including secure RPC) servers' is set to 'Require NTLMv2 session security' and 'Require 128-bit encryption')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 session security for NTLM SSP-based servers must be configured to require NTLMv2 session security and 128-bit encryption.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254478","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254478","rule_id_src":"SV-254478r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46F824-6E2B-1014-ADA2-F52C4D30E762","group_id_src":"V-254478","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254478r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254479","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000067-GPOS-00035","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Cryptography\\\n\nValue Name:  ForceKeyProtection\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000002 (2)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; System cryptography: Force strong key protection for user keys stored on the computer to \"User must enter a password each time they use a key\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000350","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"If the private key is discovered, an attacker can use the key to authenticate as an authorized user and gain access to the network infrastructure.\n\nThe cornerstone of the PKI is the private key used to encrypt or digitally sign information.\n\nIf the private key is stolen, this will lead to the compromise of the authentication and nonrepudiation gained through PKI because the attacker can use the private key to digitally sign documents and pretend to be the authorized user.\n\nBoth the holders of a digital certificate and the issuing authority must protect the computers, storage devices, or whatever they use to keep the private keys.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Users are required to enter a password to access private keys stored on the computer.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 users must be required to enter a password to access private keys stored on the computer.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000186"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254479","title":"SRG-OS-000067-GPOS-00035"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254479","rule_id_src":"SV-254479r958450_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A46FC67-6E2B-1014-8CBD-F9E45DBCD432","group_id_src":"V-254479","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254479r958450"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254480","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000478-GPOS-00223","comments":null,"check_content":"This is NA if the host is running SharePoint.                                                                               If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\FIPSAlgorithmPolicy\\\n\nValue Name: Enabled\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n \nClients with this setting enabled will not be able to communicate via digitally encrypted or signed protocols with servers that do not support these algorithms. Both the browser and web server must be configured to use TLS; otherwise the browser will not be able to connect to a secure site.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; System cryptography: Use FIPS compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000360","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"This setting ensures the system uses algorithms that are FIPS-compliant for encryption, hashing, and signing. FIPS-compliant algorithms meet specific standards established by the U.S. Government and must be the algorithms used for all OS encryption functions.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('System cryptography: Use FIPS compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to use FIPS-compliant algorithms for encryption, hashing, and signing.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002450"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254480","title":"SRG-OS-000478-GPOS-00223"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254480","rule_id_src":"SV-254480r1137699_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A470012-6E2B-1014-A825-D7084147DB15","group_id_src":"V-254480","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254480r1137699"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254481","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\\n\nValue Name: ProtectionMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"low","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; System objects: Strengthen default permissions of internal system objects (e.g., Symbolic Links) to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000370","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Windows systems maintain a global list of shared system resources such as DOS device names, mutexes, and semaphores. Each type of object is created with a default Discretionary Access Control List (DACL) that specifies who can access the objects with what permissions. When this policy is enabled, the default DACL is stronger, allowing nonadministrative users to read shared objects but not to modify shared objects they did not create.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('System objects: Strengthen default permissions of internal system objects (e.g. Symbolic links)' is set to 'Enabled'.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 default permissions of global system objects must be strengthened.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254481","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254481","rule_id_src":"SV-254481r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4703AB-6E2B-1014-94F4-A90E96FD3BFE","group_id_src":"V-254481","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254481r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254482","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","comments":null,"check_content":"UAC requirements are NA for Server Core installations (this is the default installation option for Windows Server 2022 versus Server with Desktop Experience).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: FilterAdministratorToken\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; User Account Control: Admin Approval Mode for the Built-in Administrator account to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000380","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"UAC is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting configures the built-in Administrator account so that it runs in Admin Approval Mode.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156, SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Verifies 'User Account Control: Admin Approval Mode for the Built-in Administrator account' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) approval mode for the built-in Administrator must be enabled.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002038"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254482","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254482","rule_id_src":"SV-254482r1051108_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A470745-6E2B-1014-95E5-DBE189500DE2","group_id_src":"V-254482","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254482r1051108"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254483","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","comments":null,"check_content":"UAC requirements are NA for Server Core installations (this is the default installation option for Windows Server 2022 versus Server with Desktop Experience).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableUIADesktopToggle\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; User Account Control: Allow UIAccess applications to prompt for elevation without using the secure desktop to \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000390","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"User Account Control (UAC) is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting prevents User Interface Accessibility programs from disabling the secure desktop for elevation prompts.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (UIAccess applications is not allowed to prompt for elevation without using the secure desktop.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 UIAccess applications must not be allowed to prompt for elevation without using the secure desktop.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254483","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254483","rule_id_src":"SV-254483r958518_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A470AD5-6E2B-1014-AFAA-A3087D9AC47D","group_id_src":"V-254483","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254483r958518"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254484","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","comments":null,"check_content":"UAC requirements are NA for Server Core installations (this is default installation option for Windows Server 2022 versus Server with Desktop Experience).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ConsentPromptBehaviorAdmin\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2) (Prompt for consent on the secure desktop)\n0x00000001 (1) (Prompt for credentials on the secure desktop)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for administrators in Admin Approval Mode to \"Prompt for consent on the secure desktop\".\n\nThe more secure option for this setting, \"Prompt for credentials on the secure desktop\", would also be acceptable.","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000400","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"UAC is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting configures the elevation requirements for logged-on administrators to complete a task that requires raised privileges.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false ('User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for administrators in Admin Approval Mode' is set to 'Prompt for consent on the secure desktop' or 'Prompt for credentials on the secure desktop')\nResult Analysis :          HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\ConsentPromptBehaviorAdmin\\value = '0' failed test of 'equals' compared to '2' \n                : HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\ConsentPromptBehaviorAdmin\\value = '0' failed test of 'equals' compared to '1' \n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must, at a minimum, prompt administrators for consent on the secure desktop.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254484","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254484","rule_id_src":"SV-254484r958518_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A470E65-6E2B-1014-B480-E1A720B9D1C7","group_id_src":"V-254484","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254484r958518"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254485","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","comments":null,"check_content":"UAC requirements are NA for Server Core installations (this is the default installation option for Windows Server 2022 versus Server with Desktop Experience).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: ConsentPromptBehaviorUser\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for standard users to \"Automatically deny elevation requests\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000410","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"UAC is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting controls the behavior of elevation when requested by a standard user account.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156, SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (Verifies 'User Account Control: Behavior of the elevation prompt for standard users' is set to 'Automatically deny elevation requests')\nResult Analysis :          HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\ConsentPromptBehaviorUser\\value = '3' failed test of 'equals' compared to '0' \n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must automatically deny standard user requests for elevation.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002038"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254485","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254485","rule_id_src":"SV-254485r1051109_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A47121C-6E2B-1014-B7C1-F2F44E17A998","group_id_src":"V-254485","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254485r1051109"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254486","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","comments":null,"check_content":"UAC requirements are NA for Server Core installations (this is the default installation option for Windows Server 2022 versus Server with Desktop Experience).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableInstallerDetection\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; User Account Control: Detect application installations and prompt for elevation to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000420","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"UAC is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting requires Windows to respond to application installation requests by prompting for credentials.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('User Account Control: Detect application installations and prompt for elevation' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must be configured to detect application installations and prompt for elevation.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254486","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254486","rule_id_src":"SV-254486r958518_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A47159C-6E2B-1014-A024-F121D951678E","group_id_src":"V-254486","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254486r958518"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254487","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","comments":null,"check_content":"UAC requirements are NA for Server Core installations (this is the default installation option for Windows Server 2022 versus Server with Desktop Experience).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSecureUIAPaths\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; User Account Control: Only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000430","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"UAC is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting configures Windows to only allow applications installed in a secure location on the file system, such as the Program Files or the Windows\\System32 folders, to run with elevated privileges.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('User Account Control: Only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must only elevate UIAccess applications that are installed in secure locations.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254487","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254487","rule_id_src":"SV-254487r958518_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A47191D-6E2B-1014-9A36-FED53082180E","group_id_src":"V-254487","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254487r958518"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254488","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","comments":null,"check_content":"UAC requirements are NA for Server Core installations (this is the default installation option for Windows Server 2022 versus Server with Desktop Experience).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableLUA\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; User Account Control: Run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000440","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"UAC is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting enables UAC.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156, SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Verifies 'User Account Control: Run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must run all administrators in Admin Approval Mode, enabling UAC.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002038"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254488","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254488","rule_id_src":"SV-254488r1051110_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A471E12-6E2B-1014-B53C-AD125A64D74E","group_id_src":"V-254488","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254488r1051110"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254489","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","comments":null,"check_content":"UAC requirements are NA for Server Core installations (this is the default installation option for Windows Server 2022 versus Server with Desktop Experience).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableVirtualization\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; Security Options &gt;&gt; User Account Control: Virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000450","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"UAC is a security mechanism for limiting the elevation of privileges, including administrative accounts, unless authorized. This setting configures non-UAC-compliant applications to run in virtualized file and registry entries in per-user locations, allowing them to run.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('User Account Control: Virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations' is set to 'Enabled')\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 User Account Control (UAC) must virtualize file and registry write failures to per-user locations.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254489","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254489","rule_id_src":"SV-254489r958518_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4721D7-6E2B-1014-9FA7-DE978410084C","group_id_src":"V-254489","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254489r958518"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:254490","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","comments":null,"check_content":"The default behavior is for Windows to mark file attachments with their zone information.\n\nIf the registry Value Name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"2\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Attachments\\\n\nValue Name: SaveZoneInformation\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Windows to mark file attachments with their zone information.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for User Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Attachment Manager &gt;&gt; Do not preserve zone information in file attachments to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-UC-000010","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Attachments from outside sources may contain malicious code. Preserving zone of origin (internet, intranet, local, restricted) information on file attachments allows Windows to determine risk.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Zone information must be preserved when saving attachments.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must preserve zone information when saving attachments.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254490","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254490","rule_id_src":"SV-254490r991589_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A47258C-6E2B-1014-A862-B0539D5512E6","group_id_src":"V-254490","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254490r991589"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254491","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs are granted the \"SeTrustedCredManAccessPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000010","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller\" user right may be able to retrieve the credentials of other accounts from Credential Manager.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller - None)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Access Credential Manager as a trusted caller user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254491","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254491","rule_id_src":"SV-254491r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A47292F-6E2B-1014-86EC-DA7FE374790D","group_id_src":"V-254491","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254491r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254492","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups (to include administrators), are granted the \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs are granted the \"SeTcbPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).\n\nPasswords for accounts with this user right must be protected as highly privileged accounts.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Act as part of the operating system to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000020","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Act as part of the operating system\" user right can assume the identity of any user and gain access to resources that the user is authorized to access. Any accounts with this right can take complete control of a system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (No users have the privilege to act as part of the operating system.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Act as part of the operating system user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254492","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254492","rule_id_src":"SV-254492r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A472D4C-6E2B-1014-8F0F-BD7E0E92C33D","group_id_src":"V-254492","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254492r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254493","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Allow log on locally\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeInteractiveLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Allow log on locally to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000030","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Allow log on locally\" user right can log on interactively to a system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Allow log on locally - Administrators)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Allow log on locally user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254493","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254493","rule_id_src":"SV-254493r1137691_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A47312B-6E2B-1014-A195-8A2A47B404C4","group_id_src":"V-254493","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254493r1137691"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254494","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Back up files and directories\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeBackupPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Back up files and directories to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000040","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Back up files and directories\" user right can circumvent file and directory permissions and could allow access to sensitive data.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Back up files and directories - Administrators)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 back up files and directories user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254494","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254494","rule_id_src":"SV-254494r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4734F3-6E2B-1014-A6A0-F6B287FF3E9A","group_id_src":"V-254494","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254494r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254495","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Create a pagefile\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeCreatePagefilePrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Create a pagefile to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000050","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create a pagefile\" user right can change the size of a pagefile, which could affect system performance.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Create a pagefile - Administrators)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 create a pagefile user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254495","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254495","rule_id_src":"SV-254495r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4738CE-6E2B-1014-A955-FC268A73A390","group_id_src":"V-254495","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254495r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254496","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Create a token object\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs are granted the \"SeCreateTokenPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).\n\nPasswords for application accounts with this user right must be protected as highly privileged accounts.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Create a token object to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000060","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Create a token object\" user right allows a process to create an access token. This could be used to provide elevated rights and compromise a system.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Create a token object - None)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 create a token object user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254496","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254496","rule_id_src":"SV-254496r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A473CA7-6E2B-1014-94A8-D608873EC8F7","group_id_src":"V-254496","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254496r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254497","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Create global objects\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n- Service\n- Local Service\n- Network Service\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeCreateGlobalPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\nS-1-5-6 (Service)\nS-1-5-19 (Local Service)\nS-1-5-20 (Network Service)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Create global objects to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators\n- Service\n- Local Service\n- Network Service","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000070","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create global objects\" user right can create objects that are available to all sessions, which could affect processes in other users' sessions.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Create global objects - Administrators, Service, Local Service, Network Service)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 create global objects user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254497","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254497","rule_id_src":"SV-254497r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4741F6-6E2B-1014-BD90-933D2AE83110","group_id_src":"V-254497","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254497r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254498","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Create permanent shared objects\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs are granted the \"SeCreatePermanentPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Create permanent shared objects to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000080","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create permanent shared objects\" user right could expose sensitive data by creating shared objects.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (No groups or accounts are granted the 'Create permanent shared objects' user right.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 create permanent shared objects user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254498","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254498","rule_id_src":"SV-254498r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A47470A-6E2B-1014-B2A4-9C7B9CAEACEE","group_id_src":"V-254498","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254498r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254499","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Create symbolic links\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeCreateSymbolicLinkPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\n\nSystems that have the Hyper-V role will also have \"Virtual Machines\" given this user right (this may be displayed as \"NT Virtual Machine\\Virtual Machines\", SID S-1-5-83-0). This is not a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Create symbolic links to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators\n\nSystems that have the Hyper-V role will also have \"Virtual Machines\" given this user right. If this needs to be added manually, enter it as \"NT Virtual Machine\\Virtual Machines\".","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000090","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Create symbolic links\" user right can create pointers to other objects, which could expose the system to attack.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (Create symbolic links - Administrators, Virtual Machines)\nTest            :       true (Hyper-V Role is installed)\nTest            :     true (Create symbolic links - Administrators)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 create symbolic links user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254499","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254499","rule_id_src":"SV-254499r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A474C1A-6E2B-1014-B2B3-E5835B222DF8","group_id_src":"V-254499","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254499r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254500","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Debug programs\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeDebugPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).\n\nPasswords for application accounts with this user right must be protected as highly privileged accounts.","severity":"high","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Debug programs to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000100","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Debug programs\" user right can attach a debugger to any process or to the kernel, providing complete access to sensitive and critical operating system components. This right is given to Administrators in the default configuration.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Debug Programs - Administrators)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 debug programs user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254500","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254500","rule_id_src":"SV-254500r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A475105-6E2B-1014-8892-8BA6973C56A8","group_id_src":"V-254500","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254500r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254501","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeRemoteShutdownPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Force shutdown from a remote system to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000110","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Force shutdown from a remote system\" user right can remotely shut down a system, which could result in a denial of service.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Force shutdown from a remote system - Administrators)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 force shutdown from a remote system user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254501","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254501","rule_id_src":"SV-254501r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A475553-6E2B-1014-A902-E486EE126C60","group_id_src":"V-254501","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254501r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254502","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Generate security audits\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Local Service\n- Network Service\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeAuditPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-19 (Local Service)\nS-1-5-20 (Network Service)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Generate security audits to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Local Service\n- Network Service","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000120","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Generate security audits\" user right specifies users and processes that can generate Security Log audit records, which must only be the system service accounts defined.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Generate security audits - Local Service, Network Service)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 generate security audits user right must only be assigned to Local Service and Network Service.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254502","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254502","rule_id_src":"SV-254502r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A475986-6E2B-1014-B4F9-B60D4F1A9EBC","group_id_src":"V-254502","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254502r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254503","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n- Service\n- Local Service\n- Network Service\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeImpersonatePrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\nS-1-5-6 (Service)\nS-1-5-19 (Local Service)\nS-1-5-20 (Network Service)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Impersonate a client after authentication to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators\n- Service\n- Local Service\n- Network Service","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000130","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Impersonate a client after authentication\" user right allows a program to impersonate another user or account to run on their behalf. An attacker could use this to elevate privileges.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (No groups or accounts are granted the 'Impersonate a client after authentication' user right.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 impersonate a client after authentication user right must only be assigned to Administrators, Service, Local Service, and Network Service.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254503","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254503","rule_id_src":"SV-254503r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A475E46-6E2B-1014-8EF1-D5C8E41044EF","group_id_src":"V-254503","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254503r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254504","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Increase scheduling priority\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeIncreaseBasePriorityPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Increase scheduling priority to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000140","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Increase scheduling priority\" user right can change a scheduling priority, causing performance issues or a denial of service.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Increase scheduling priority - Administrators)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 increase scheduling priority: user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254504","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254504","rule_id_src":"SV-254504r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A476287-6E2B-1014-B65C-8A2FC0A68258","group_id_src":"V-254504","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254504r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254505","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Load and unload device drivers\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeLoadDriverPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Load and unload device drivers to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000150","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Load and unload device drivers\" user right allows a user to load device drivers dynamically on a system. This could be used by an attacker to install malicious code.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Load and unload device drivers - Administrators)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 load and unload device drivers user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254505","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254505","rule_id_src":"SV-254505r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A47663E-6E2B-1014-9354-E59446D14ACE","group_id_src":"V-254505","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254505r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254506","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Lock pages in memory\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs are granted the \"SeLockMemoryPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Lock pages in memory to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000160","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Lock pages in memory\" user right allows physical memory to be assigned to processes, which could cause performance issues or a denial of service.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125, SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00193","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Lock pages in memory - None)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 lock pages in memory user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235","CCI-002824"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254506","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254506","rule_id_src":"SV-254506r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A476A29-6E2B-1014-A937-BE9CC1620B1C","group_id_src":"V-254506","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254506r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254507","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Manage auditing and security log\" user right, this is a finding.\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeSecurityPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\n\nIf the organization has an Auditors group, the assignment of this group to the user right would not be a finding.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Manage auditing and security log to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000170","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Manage auditing and security log\" user right can manage the security log and change auditing configurations. This could be used to clear evidence of tampering.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027, SRG-OS-000058-GPOS-00028, SRG-OS-000059-GPOS-00029, SRG-OS-000063-GPOS-00032, SRG-OS-000337-GPOS-00129","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The 'Manage auditing and security log' user right is only assigned to the Administrators group.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 manage auditing and security log user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000162","CCI-000163","CCI-000164","CCI-000171","CCI-001914"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254507","title":"SRG-OS-000057-GPOS-00027"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254507","rule_id_src":"SV-254507r958434_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A476E3C-6E2B-1014-ADDB-BFCFEDC351DD","group_id_src":"V-254507","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254507r958434"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254508","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Modify firmware environment values\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeSystemEnvironmentPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Modify firmware environment values to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000180","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Modify firmware environment values\" user right can change hardware configuration environment variables. This could result in hardware failures or a denial of service.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Modify firmware environment values - Administrators)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 modify firmware environment values user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254508","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254508","rule_id_src":"SV-254508r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A477236-6E2B-1014-A6F7-97601383916A","group_id_src":"V-254508","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254508r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254509","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Perform volume maintenance tasks\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeManageVolumePrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Perform volume maintenance tasks to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000190","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Perform volume maintenance tasks\" user right can manage volume and disk configurations. This could be used to delete volumes, resulting in data loss or a denial of service.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Perform volume maintenance tasks - Administrators)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 perform volume maintenance tasks user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254509","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254509","rule_id_src":"SV-254509r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A477606-6E2B-1014-98BE-AD821B306F08","group_id_src":"V-254509","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254509r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254510","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Profile single process\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeProfileSingleProcessPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Profile single process to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000200","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Profile single process\" user right can monitor nonsystem processes performance. An attacker could use this to identify processes to attack.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The 'Profile single process' user right is only assigned to the Administrators group.)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 profile single process user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254510","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254510","rule_id_src":"SV-254510r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4779AD-6E2B-1014-9585-B2AE37F938B3","group_id_src":"V-254510","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254510r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254511","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Restore files and directories\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeRestorePrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Restore files and directories to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000210","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Restore files and directories\" user right can circumvent file and directory permissions and could allow access to sensitive data. It could also be used to overwrite more current data.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Restore files and directories - Administrators)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 restore files and directories user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254511","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254511","rule_id_src":"SV-254511r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A477D5A-6E2B-1014-AC8B-92FBCA197B55","group_id_src":"V-254511","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254511r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:254512","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Take ownership of files or other objects\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeTakeOwnershipPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment &gt;&gt; Take ownership of files or other objects to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","rule_version":"WN22-UR-000220","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Take ownership of files or other objects\" user right can take ownership of objects and make changes.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Take ownership of files or other objects - Administrators)\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 take ownership of files or other objects user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-254512","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-254512","rule_id_src":"SV-254512r958726_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A4780E1-6E2B-1014-B45F-D7F725FF2FA8","group_id_src":"V-254512","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-254512r958726"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:271426","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. This is not applicable for member servers.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Kdc\n \nValue Name: StrongCertificateBindingEnforcement\n \nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) or 0x00000002 (2)","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the registry value.\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Kdc\n \nValue Name: StrongCertificateBindingEnforcement\n \nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) or 0x00000002 (2)","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000405","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Active Directory domain services elevation of privilege vulnerability could allow a user rights to the system, such as administrative and other high-level capabilities.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured for certificate-based authentication for domain controllers.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-271426","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-271426","rule_id_src":"SV-271426r1137691_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A478618-6E2B-1014-975E-C3E91F3E66B6","group_id_src":"V-271426","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-271426r1137691"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:271427","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"not_applicable","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","comments":null,"check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. This is not applicable for member servers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Template &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; KDC &gt;&gt; Allow name-based strong mappings for certificates.\n\nIf \"Allow name-based strong mappings for certificates\" is not \"Enabled\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Template &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; KDC &gt;&gt; Allow name-based strong mappings for certificates to \"Enabled\".","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000406","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Weak mappings give rise to security vulnerabilities and demand hardening measures. Certificate names must be correctly mapped to the intended user account in Active Directory. A lack of strong name-based mappings allows certain weak certificate mappings, such as Issuer/Subject AltSecID and User Principal Names (UPN) mappings, to be treated as strong mappings.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured for name-based strong mappings for certificates.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-271427","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-271427","rule_id_src":"SV-271427r1137691_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A478A4E-6E2B-1014-9B5B-F94BE1D936CB","group_id_src":"V-271427","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-271427r1137691"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:278942","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify that Audit File System auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Object Access &gt;&gt; Audit File System. \n\nIf \"Audit File System\" is not set to \"Failure\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Object Access &gt;&gt; \"Audit File System\" with \"Failure\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000581","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit File System' is set to 'Failure')\nResult Analysis :          file_system = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_FAILURE' \nTest            :     false ('Audit File System' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\nResult Analysis :          file_system = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS_FAILURE' \n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit file system failures.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-278942","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-278942","rule_id_src":"SV-278942r1135355_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A478E5E-6E2B-1014-B323-B30D1F70984E","group_id_src":"V-278942","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-278942r1135355"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:278943","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify that Audit File System auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Object Access &gt;&gt; Audit File System. \n\nIf \"Audit File System\" is not set to \"Success\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Object Access &gt;&gt; \"Audit File System\" with \"Success\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000582","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","security_override_guidance":"","third_party_tools":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T11:39:56\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit File System' is set to 'Success')\nResult Analysis :          file_system = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS' \nTest            :     false ('Audit File System' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\nResult Analysis :          file_system = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS_FAILURE' \n","documentable":"false","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit file system successes.","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-278943","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031"},"weight":"10.0","false_positives":"","mitigations":"","group_id":"V-278943","rule_id_src":"SV-278943r1135358_rule","ia_controls":"","uuid":"0A479701-6E2B-1014-807D-E69E105B0FEA","group_id_src":"V-278943","potential_impacts":"","rule_id":"SV-278943r1135358"},{"reference_identifier":"5485","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows2022:def:278944","href":"U_MS_Windows_Server_2022_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval.xml"},"responsibility":"","legacy_ids":[],"status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","comments":null,"check_content":"Verify that Audit Handle Manipulation auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Object Access &gt;&gt; Audit Handle Manipulation. \n\nIf \"Audit Handle Manipulation\" is not set to \"Failure\", this is a finding.","severity":"medium","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Object Access &gt;&gt; \"Audit Handle Manipulation\" with \"Failure\" selected.","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000583","stig_uuid":"0A0B2612-6E2B-1014-AB22-D1F66DE0327A","classification":"Unclassified","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this